INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (494001, 'The ''self-image'' is the key to human personality and human behavior. Change the self image and you change the personality and the behavior.', 1572, 0), (494002, 'Failed plans should not be interpreted as a failed vision. Visions don''t change, they are only refined. Plans rarely stay the same, and are scrapped or adjusted as needed. Be stubborn about the vision, but flexible with your plan.', 1810, 0), (494003, 'When the seasons shift, even the subtle beginning, the scent of a promised change, I feel something stir inside me. Hopefulness? Gratitude? Openness? Whatever it is, it''s welcome.', 12208, 0), (494004, 'My moms always told me, ''How long you gonna play the victim?'' I can say I''m mad and I hate everything, but nothing really changes until I change myself.', 22894, 0), (494005, 'Miracles happen everyday, change your perception of what a miracle is and you''ll see them all around you.', 2385, 0), (494006, 'You cannot change your destination overnight, but you can change your direction overnight.', 1295, 0), (494007, 'Don''t change on me. Don''t extort me unless you intend to do it forever.', 1097, 0), (494008, 'We cannot change the cards we are dealt, just how we play the game.', 1057, 0), (494009, 'We shall never change our political leaders until we change the people who elect them.', 16058, 0), (494010, 'There are big problems that change the world. If we are working together, that will make us understand each other, appreciate each other, help each other.', 66598, 0), (494011, 'If we each take responsibility in shifting our own behavior, we can trigger the type of change that is necessary to achieve sustainability for our race or this planet. We change our planet, our environment, our humanity every day, every year, every decade, and every millennia.', 11977, 0), (494012, 'Climate change is the environmental challenge of this generation, and it is imperative that we act before it''s too late.', 71180, 0), (494013, 'People don''t realize what''s really going on in this country. There are a lot things that are going on that are unjust. People aren''t being held accountable for. And that''s something that needs to change. That''s something that this country stands for: freedom, liberty and justice for all.', 66725, 0), (494014, 'The older I get, the more I''m conscious of ways very small things can make a change in the world. Tiny little things, but the world is made up of tiny matters, isn''t it?', 26083, 0), (494015, 'Some people change when they think they''re a star or something.', 50391, 0), (494016, 'I''m not going to change I''m very stubborn in this way. I am what I am. ', 68910, 0), (494017, 'Every few years, I change my look for the simple reason that I get bored. If you Google Image me, you will see so many different looks: long hair, short hair, clean shaven, beard, etc.', 67634, 0), (494018, 'This stand wasn''t because I feel like I''m being put down in any kind of way. This is because I''m seeing things happen to people that don''t have a voice: people that don''t have a platform to talk and have their voices heard and affect change. So I''m in the position where I can do that, and I''m going to do that for people that can''t.', 66725, 0), (494019, 'Metamorphosis has always been the greatest symbol of change for poets and artists. Imagine that you could be a caterpillar one moment and a butterfly the next.', 70785, 0), (494020, 'I don''t think people change. I think they definitely mature. But I think the essence of what I am today is the same as when I was five years old. It''s just maturity. I''ve become a healthier, fuller expression of that essence.', 69753, 0), (494021, 'My style is definitely schizophrenic; it does change from day to day a lot. It depends on my mood: sometimes I''ll be going through a girly, childlike stage and wear a pretty lace dress with a bow in my hair. Then sometimes I''ll be moody and just wear black.', 70327, 0), (494022, 'When you start in life, if you find you are wrongly placed, don''t hesitate to change, but don''t change because troubles come up and difficulties arise. You must meet and overcome and conquer them. And in meeting and overcoming and conquering them, you will make yourself stronger for the future.', 63087, 0), (494023, 'Climate change is a terrible problem, and it absolutely needs to be solved. It deserves to be a huge priority.', 1133, 0), (494024, 'I was willing to accept what I couldn''t change.', 1798, 0), (494025, 'It may be hard for an egg to turn into a bird: it would be a jolly sight harder for it to learn to fly while remaining an egg. We are like eggs at present. And you cannot go on indefinitely being just an ordinary, decent egg. We must be hatched or go bad.', 26, 0), (494026, 'I realized if you can change a classroom, you can change a community, and if you change enough communities you can change the world.', 30637, 0), (494027, 'We cannot change anything until we accept it. Condemnation does not liberate, it oppresses.', 28934, 0), (494028, 'Goals allow you to control the direction of change in your favor.', 697, 0), (494029, 'Research has shown that it takes 31 days of conscious effort to make or break a habit. That means, if one practices something consistently for 31 days, on the 32nd day it does become a habit. Information has been internalised into behavioural change, which is called transformation.', 1998, 0), (494030, 'Things don''t have to change the world to be important.', 1064, 0), (494031, 'There is nothing so stable as change.', 289, 0), (494032, 'Ethics and equity and the principles of justice do not change with the calendar.', 178, 0), (494033, 'A change of scenery can help everything.', 72550, 0), (494034, 'As engineers, we were going to be in a position to change the world - not just study it.', 67673, 0), (494035, 'I think you should always bear in mind that entropy is not on your side.', 10864, 0), (494036, 'Isn''t life a series of images that change as they repeat themselves?', 321, 0), (494037, 'People with high blood pressure, diabetes - those are conditions brought about by life style. If you change the life style, those conditions will leave.', 39403, 0), (494038, 'This past year has been something else... it''s opened my eyes to many things and many people. It''s had its ups and downs and ins and outs. And I believe we''ve all been able to take something from that and grow in our own imparticular ways. We''ve over come obstacles, and set in motion opportunities that can change our own individual lives.', 75987, 0), (494039, 'Help young people. Help small guys. Because small guys will be big. Young people will have the seeds you bury in their minds, and when they grow up, they will change the world.', 66598, 0), (494040, 'I believe people change. I think that they can learn from mistakes.', 67039, 0), (494041, 'The ones who are crazy enough to think that they can change the world are the ones who do.', 53514, 0), (494042, 'Journalism is what maintains democracy. It''s the force for progressive social change.', 10851, 0), (494043, 'We live in a changing world, but we need to be reminded that the important things have not changed, and the important things will not change if we keep our priorities in proper order.', 66997, 0), (494044, 'You''re only as young as the last time you changed your mind.', 2932, 0), (494045, 'On climate change, we often don''t fully appreciate that it is a problem. We think it is a problem waiting to happen.', 29992, 0), (494046, 'My greatest challenge has been to change the mindset of people. Mindsets play strange tricks on us. We see things the way our minds have instructed our eyes to see.', 3626, 0), (494047, 'Change happens by listening and then starting a dialogue with the people who are doing something you don''t believe is right.', 2086, 0), (494048, 'Climate change is a global problem. The planet is warming because of the growing level of greenhouse gas emissions from human activity. If this trend continues, truly catastrophic consequences are likely to ensue from rising sea levels, to reduced water availability, to more heat waves and fires.', 72454, 0), (494049, 'It takes but one person, one moment, one conviction, to start a ripple of change.', 67006, 0), (494050, 'Change, like sunshine, can be a friend or a foe, a blessing or a curse, a dawn or a dusk.', 1820, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (494051, 'There are always people who are into the old way of doing things. I don''t think it''s a bad thing necessarily, but things change - nothing stays the same. If you can stay true to yourself, you''re always going to be legendary.', 69206, 0), (494052, 'First rule of change is controversy. You can''t get away from it for the simple reason all issues are controversial. Change means movement, and movement means friction, and friction means heat, and heat means controversy.', 48660, 0), (494053, 'There''s a lot of things that need to change. One specifically? Police brutality.', 66725, 0), (494054, 'The reality is that the only way change comes is when you lead by example.', 68910, 0), (494055, 'Excellent firms don''t believe in excellence - only in constant improvement and constant change.', 19479, 0), (494056, 'The rules of survival never change, whether you''re in a desert or in an arena.', 9272, 0), (494057, 'Wind and other clean, renewable energy will help end our reliance on fossil fuels and combat the severe threat that climate change poses to humans and wildlife alike.', 67862, 0), (494058, 'If you ask what you are going to do about global warming, the only rational answer is to change the way in which we do transportation, energy production, agriculture and a good deal of manufacturing. The problem originates in human activity in the form of the production of goods.', 63450, 0), (494059, 'I imagine an America that can actually change. That we become a nation that prospers again but without pillaging the resources of nations that make their people hate us. That we become a nation that, as the constitution says in its preamble, its very first paragraph, ''promotes the general welfare'' of its people.', 24349, 0), (494060, 'People think that you have to do something huge, like go to Africa and build a school, but you can make a small change in a day. If you change Wednesday, then you change Thursday. Pretty soon it''s a week, then a month, then a year. It''s bite-size, as opposed to feeling like you have to turn your life inside out to make changes.', 22721, 0), (494061, 'A lot of people resist transition and therefore never allow themselves to enjoy who they are. Embrace the change, no matter what it is; once you do, you can learn about the new world you''re in and take advantage of it.', 491, 0), (494062, 'You change the world by being yourself.', 1121, 0), (494063, 'Every successful organization has to make the transition from a world defined primarily by repetition to one primarily defined by change. This is the biggest transformation in the structure of how humans work together since the Agricultural Revolution.', 73935, 0), (494064, 'I''m not going to change the world. You''re not going to change the world. But we can help - we can all help.', 5874, 0), (494065, 'Real, sustainable community change requires the initiative and engagement of community members.', 74218, 0), (494066, 'I know my soul is beautiful I know I''m a good person. And that will never change for me. ', 66708, 0), (494067, 'You will not solve global climate change by hitting the delete button.', 11429, 0), (494068, 'With a fixed mindset, you believe you are who you are and you cannot change. This creates problems when you''re challenged because anything that appears to be more than you can handle is bound to make you feel hopeless and overwhelmed.', 68087, 0), (494069, 'The ultimate end of all revolutionary social change is to establish the sanctity of human life, the dignity of man, the right of every human being to liberty and well-being.', 805, 0), (494070, 'What''s dangerous is not to evolve.', 22320, 0), (494071, 'We don''t need no more danger, we don''t need no more difficulties, we don''t need no more misunderstanding, and we don''t need no more violence. We need the people to see each other and know of each other, feel each other, touch each other, share with each other, and change hearts with each other.', 71331, 0), (494072, 'Constitutions should consist only of general provisions; the reason is that they must necessarily be permanent, and that they cannot calculate for the possible change of things.', 16733, 0), (494073, 'What I learned in jail is that I can''t change. I can''t live a different lifestyle - this is it. This is the life that they gave and this is the life that I made.', 1097, 0), (494074, 'You have to modernise you have to change - you can''t just be traditional for the fun of being traditional. ', 69885, 0), (494075, 'One thing modeling taught me is that the spotlight can change everything.', 71869, 0), (494076, 'You collect people to take with you. Some people change, other people don''t... it''s wonderful because I''ve met some incredible friends.', 72218, 0), (494077, 'For too long, our society has shrugged off bullying by labeling it a ''rite of passage'' and by asking students to simply ''get over it.'' Those attitudes need to change. Every day, students are bullied into silence and are afraid to speak up. Let''s break this silence and end school bullying.', 71499, 0), (494078, 'If only 7 percent of the 2 billion Christians in the world would care for a single orphan in distress, there would effectively be no more orphans. If everybody would be willing to simply do something to care for one of these precious treasures, I think we would be amazed by just how much we could change the world.', 31701, 0), (494079, 'Don''t manage - lead change before you have to.', 10103, 0), (494080, 'To some extent, Seattle remains a frontier metropolis, a place where people can experiment with their lives, and change and grow and make things happen.', 105, 0), (494081, 'Things do not change we change. ', 1049, 0), (494082, 'Effectively, change is almost impossible without industry-wide collaboration, cooperation and consensus.', 66797, 0), (494083, 'All relationships change the brain - but most important are the intimate bonds that foster or fail us, altering the delicate circuits that shape memories, emotions and that ultimate souvenir, the self.', 8213, 0), (494084, 'Change in all things is sweet.', 1116, 0), (494085, 'Audiences change because life changes. Countries change geographically, climatically, socially and morally. Many things happen, and cinema, in a sense, reflects what''s happening in the world.', 68907, 0), (494086, 'The Framers of the Constitution knew that free speech is the friend of change and revolution. But they also knew that it is always the deadliest enemy of tyranny.', 69807, 0), (494087, 'The way to change the world is through individual responsibility and taking local action in your own community.', 67519, 0), (494088, 'The world is changing very fast. Big will not beat small anymore. It will be the fast beating the slow.', 15116, 0), (494089, 'Most people don''t want to change. They''re comfortable and set in their ways. But in order to change, you have to be able to agitate people at times. And I think that''s something that''s very necessary for us to improve as a country.', 66725, 0), (494090, 'If you want to change the world, start off by making your bed.', 70511, 0), (494091, 'If you want to have clean ideas, change them as often as your shirt.', 51603, 0), (494092, 'A small group of thoughtful people could change the world. Indeed, it''s the only thing that ever has.', 992, 0), (494093, 'As a leader, the first person I need to lead is me. The first person that I should try to change is me.', 1810, 0), (494094, 'I don''t know if my hairstyles reflect that, but I am someone who enjoys change.', 72841, 0), (494095, 'I feel confident imposing change on myself. It''s a lot more fun progressing than looking back. That''s why I need to throw curve balls.', 1232, 0), (494096, 'Bravery is the engine of change.', 61882, 0), (494097, 'If your life changes, we can change the world, too.', 1121, 0), (494098, 'I love what I do, and when I don''t love what I do, I''ll make a change.', 746, 0), (494099, 'One volcano puts out more toxic gases - one volcano - than man makes in a whole year. And when you look at this ''climate change,'' and when you look at the regular climate change that we all have in the world, we have warm and we have cooling spells.', 75988, 0), (494100, 'Being ready isn''t enough you have to be prepared for a promotion or any other significant change. ', 44727, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (494101, 'Become a student of change. It is the only thing that will remain constant.', 57097, 0), (494102, 'It is not necessary to change. Survival is not mandatory.', 11418, 0), (494103, 'Excess generally causes reaction, and produces a change in the opposite direction, whether it be in the seasons, or in individuals, or in governments.', 51, 0), (494104, 'Change is inevitable. Change is constant.', 1827, 0), (494105, 'The way to bring about change is to be proactive and active.', 67336, 0), (494106, 'You can''t change the world you can''t fix the whole environment. But you can recycle. You can turn the water off when you''re brushing your teeth. You can do small things. ', 1883, 0), (494107, 'I know I''m a good professional, I know that no one''s harder on me than myself and that''s never going to change, under any circumstances.', 5874, 0), (494108, 'There is no question that climate change is happening the only arguable point is what part humans are playing in it. ', 3969, 0), (494109, 'I''m on a constant path of self-discovery and change. I''m trying to become a better person, a nicer person. I love therapy - it''s brilliant.', 75989, 0), (494110, 'Maybe you''re not perfect, but you''re willing to actually look at yourself and take some kind of accountability. That''s a change. It might not mean that you can turn everything around, but I think there''s something incredibly hopeful about that.', 46525, 0), (494111, 'It is not strange... to mistake change for progress.', 58652, 0), (494112, 'People change, they grow.', 75990, 0), (494113, 'I don''t think anyone is black and white and I think we change our minds and our attitudes about certain things as we grow to our maturity.', 67894, 0), (494114, 'I''ve reached the point where I hardly care whether I live or die. The world will keep on turning without me, and I can''t do anything to change events anyway.', 986, 0), (494115, 'If we go on the way we have, the fault is our greed and if we are not willing to change, we will disappear from the face of the globe, to be replaced by the insect.', 21403, 0), (494116, 'If you get stuck, draw with a different pen. Change your tools; it may free your thinking.', 2085, 0), (494117, 'Change is vital, improvement the logical form of change.', 51966, 0), (494118, 'Climate change knows no borders. It will not stop before the Pacific islands and the whole of the international community here has to shoulder a responsibility to bring about a sustainable development.', 67556, 0), (494119, 'We are a party of innovation. We do not reject our traditions, but we are willing to adapt to changing circumstances, when change we must. We are willing to suffer the discomfort of change in order to achieve a better future.', 17554, 0), (494120, 'I just feel like I''m such a normal person in an industry that is so chaotic and crazy. I am what I am, and I can''t change it. And I don''t want to change it.', 75991, 0), (494121, 'Pop culture is a reflection of social change, not a cause of social change.', 68723, 0), (494122, 'People can try to reinvent themselves. I don''t think you can really change who you are, though, because who you are is pretty much where you came from and what you''ve done up to now.', 392, 0), (494123, 'We can have no progress without change, whether it be basketball or anything else.', 1721, 0), (494124, 'But change must always be balanced with some degree of consistency.', 73757, 0), (494125, 'A change in the weather is sufficient to recreate the world and ourselves.', 450, 0), (494126, 'Progress is a nice word. But change is its motivator. And change has its enemies.', 60667, 0), (494127, 'A fanatic is one who can''t change his mind and won''t change the subject.', 3621, 0), (494128, 'Studies have shown that 90% of error in thinking is due to error in perception. If you can change your perception, you can change your emotion and this can lead to new ideas.', 26588, 0), (494129, 'Becoming a mother cannot help but change things. An author''s life is reflected in their writing, whether they want it to be or not, and parenthood is one of the biggest life changes there is.', 28461, 0), (494130, 'It''s a philosophy of life. A practice. If you do this, something will change, what will change is that you will change, your life will change, and if you can change you, you can perhaps change the world.', 13967, 0), (494131, 'Sometimes if you want to see a change for the better, you have to take things into your own hands.', 2269, 0), (494132, 'To change ones life: Start immediately. Do it flamboyantly.', 1782, 0), (494133, 'Like it or not, the world evolves, priorities change and so do you.', 66921, 0), (494134, 'No change of circumstances can repair a defect of character.', 760, 0), (494135, 'I''m not going to change the way I look or the way I feel to conform to anything. I''ve always been a freak. So I''ve been a freak all my life and I have to live with that, you know. I''m one of those people.', 46, 0), (494136, 'Face the facts of being what you are, for that is what changes what you are.', 3131, 0), (494137, 'I can''t really change my life to accommodate people who are jealous. I don''t see why I should.', 9151, 0), (494138, 'Berlin is all about volatility. Its identity is based not on stability but on change.', 69566, 0), (494139, 'Hair color is the easiest way to change your appearance, but a bad dye job might draw more attention to you.', 2479, 0), (494140, 'I believe we are on an irreversible trend toward more freedom and democracy - but that could change.', 17186, 0), (494141, 'If anything is certain, it is that change is certain. The world we are planning for today will not exist in this form tomorrow.', 72586, 0), (494142, 'It''s always the small people who change things. It''s never the politicians or the big guys. I mean, who pulled down the Berlin wall? It was all the people in the streets. The specialists didn''t have a clue the day before.', 75992, 0), (494143, 'You don''t change your style by changing your bag. You change it with your clothes.', 68143, 0), (494144, 'As an organizer, I start from where the world is, as it is, not as I would like it to be. That we accept the world as it is does not in any sense weaken our desire to change it into what we believe it should be - it is necessary to begin where the world is if we are going to change it to what we think it should be. That means working in the system.', 48660, 0), (494145, 'Our dilemma is that we hate change and love it at the same time what we really want is for things to remain the same but get better. ', 4317, 0), (494146, 'You have to have sharp elbows if you want to change something.', 70628, 0), (494147, 'I''m living with every step. I can''t live with regret. The past is the past. I''m not worried about it. I can''t change it. I can''t fix it. It is what it is. I''m just living.', 67889, 0), (494148, 'The universe is change our life is what our thoughts make it. ', 267, 0), (494149, 'The key is to embrace disruption and change early. Don''t react to it decades later. You can''t fight innovation.', 75993, 0), (494150, 'We teach people that they upset themselves. We can''t change the past, so we change how people are thinking, feeling and behaving today.', 22518, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (494151, 'Unfortunately, some of our poor choices are irreversible, but many are not. Often, we can change course and get back on the right track.', 9153, 0), (494152, 'Television is like the invention of indoor plumbing. It didn''t change people''s habits. It just kept them inside the house.', 2186, 0), (494153, 'If you realize that all things change, there is nothing you will try to hold on to. If you are not afraid of dying, there is nothing you cannot achieve.', 15, 0), (494154, 'All is connected... no one thing can change by itself.', 21310, 0), (494155, 'Pick up a rifle and you change instantly from a subject to a citizen.', 16746, 0), (494156, 'By the time we see that climate change is really bad, your ability to fix it is extremely limited... The carbon gets up there, but the heating effect is delayed. And then the effect of that heat on the species and ecosystem is delayed. That means that even when you turn virtuous, things are actually going to get worse for quite a while.', 1133, 0), (494157, 'The more things change, the more they are the same.', 26458, 0), (494158, 'He who is fixed to a star does not change his mind.', 1386, 0), (494159, 'The garden is growth and change and that means loss as well as constant new treasures to make up for a few disasters.', 996, 0), (494160, 'Relentless, repetitive self talk is what changes our self-image.', 1391, 0), (494161, 'I believe global warming and climate change are real threats to our planet.', 71502, 0), (494162, 'Don''t ever forget that a small group of thoughtful people can change the world, it''s the only thing that ever has.', 1482, 0), (494163, 'If you want to change the world, find someone to help you paddle.', 70511, 0), (494164, 'You cannot expect to achieve new goals or move beyond your present circumstances unless you change.', 1873, 0), (494165, 'There are things I can''t force. I must adjust. There are times when the greatest change needed is a change of my viewpoint.', 2879, 0), (494166, 'Americans have so far put up with inequality because they felt they could change their status. They didn''t mind others being rich, as long as they had a path to move up as well. The American Dream is all about social mobility in a sense - the idea that anyone can make it.', 11721, 0), (494167, 'The world changes, but I want that change to be necessary or respectful of what has happened before. Everything changes, and that''s quite right.', 26227, 0), (494168, 'I have a low tolerance for people who complain about things but never do anything to change them. This led me to conclude that the single largest pool of untapped natural resources in this world is human good intentions that are never translated into actions.', 75994, 0), (494169, 'I want to change the bad boy image that has stuck for a bit because I don''t think I am at all how I have been portrayed. I would like that to change because it''s awful to hear and read what is said of you.', 75995, 0), (494170, 'As another has well said, to handicap a student by teaching him that his black face is a curse and that his struggle to change his condition is hopeless is the worst sort of lynching.', 3302, 0), (494171, 'Everything changes but change.', 4298, 0), (494172, 'Logic will never change emotion or perception.', 26588, 0), (494173, 'I firmly believe that every six years, a person goes through a serious change. Think about it: At 6, you start school. At about 12, you start hitting puberty. And then it goes on. You start hitting these different mental levels, and people change. I think that''s part of the reason the divorce rate is so high.', 75996, 0), (494174, 'Style can change your look, certainly, but it can also change your life.', 36959, 0), (494175, 'The proud do not change to improve, but defend their position by rationalizing. Repentance means change, and it takes a humble person to change.', 1826, 0), (494176, 'When you talk about change, you know what makes it really tough for people is on the one hand you''ve got tradition, and on the other hand you''ve got change; in many people''s mind, change equals modernization. Tradition, however. I''m a big tradition guy.', 17531, 0), (494177, 'I believe climate change is real and that we can save our planet while creating millions of good-paying clean energy jobs.', 66567, 0), (494178, 'In a bid for change, we have to take off our coats, be prepared to lose our comfort and security, our jobs and positions of prestige, and our families... A struggle without casualties is no struggle.', 66913, 0), (494179, 'I like working with people. I believe change can only come through collaboration.', 639, 0), (494180, 'Man can certainly flee from God... but he cannot escape him. He can certainly hate God and be hateful to God, but he cannot change into its opposite the eternal love of God which triumphs even in his hate.', 4281, 0), (494181, 'Our conscience is not the vessel of eternal verities. It grows with our social life, and a new social condition means a radical change in conscience.', 3643, 0), (494182, 'Winners must learn to relish change with the same enthusiasm and energy that we have resisted it in the past.', 19479, 0), (494183, 'It''s not the destination that matters. It''s the change of scene.', 18504, 0), (494184, 'While the river of life glides along smoothly, it remains the same river; only the landscape on either bank seems to change.', 69005, 0), (494185, 'Change brings opportunities. On the other hand, change can be confusing.', 66809, 0), (494186, 'In order to change the world, you have to get your head together first.', 92, 0), (494187, 'I try to contrast life today is full of contrast... We have to change. ', 55176, 0), (494188, 'I do think that you can dress yourself out of a problem. The way that a haircut and a new pair of pants can make you feel is better than any therapist, because when you look in the mirror, you see a different person - you are a different person. It''s superficial change that can lead to real change.', 71, 0), (494189, 'Climate change is the Everest of all problems, the thorniest challenge facing humankind.', 74892, 0), (494190, 'Once I find a bag that I love, I wear it always. I just don''t change my bags. I literally find one and stay with it.', 68038, 0), (494191, 'Scientists use satellites to track weather, map ice sheet melting, detect diseases, show ecosystem change... the list goes on and on. I think nearly every scientific field benefits or could benefit from satellite imagery analysis.', 69935, 0), (494192, 'Remember that life''s big changes rarely give advance warning.', 63634, 0), (494193, 'Nobody knows the future with certainty. We can, however, identify ongoing patterns of change.', 28611, 0), (494194, 'I am a free lover. I have an inalienable, constitutional and natural right to love whom I may, to love as long or short a period as I can; to change that love every day if I please.', 68309, 0), (494195, 'Change is always tough. Even for those who see themselves as agents of change, the process of starting a new thing can cause times of disorientation, uncertainty and insecurity.', 1206, 0), (494196, 'I think comedy is a good way to help people change their minds. I think that if you''re laughing and getting a message across, it''s a lot easier than when somebody is screaming in your face.', 50659, 0), (494197, 'Our only security is our ability to change.', 52093, 0), (494198, 'Those people in New York are not gonna change me none.', 1120, 0), (494199, 'You can look for external sources of motivation and that can catalyze a change, but it won''t sustain one. It has to be from an internal desire.', 1860, 0), (494200, 'When you read the New Testament, you see the Holy Spirit was supposed to change everything so that this gathering of people who call themselves Christians had this supernatural element about them.', 730, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (494201, 'The World Wide Web went from zero to millions of web pages in a few years. Many revolutions look irrelevant just before they change everything swiftly.', 68237, 0), (494202, 'Citizens victimized by genocide or abandoned by the international community do not make good neighbors, as their thirst for vengeance, their irredentism and their acceptance of violence as a means of generating change can turn them into future threats.', 17792, 0), (494203, 'If you believe that feeling bad or worrying long enough will change a past or future event, then you are residing on another planet with a different reality system.', 1782, 0), (494204, 'My own eyes are no more than scouts on a preliminary search, for the camera''s eye may entirely change my idea.', 19743, 0), (494205, 'When I was in first grade, everyone made fun of my name, of course. I think it''s kind of a big name to hold up when you''re nine years old. It seemed goofy. I used to tell people I wanted to change the world and they used to think, ''This kid''s really weird''.', 3877, 0), (494206, 'I shall always be consistent and never change my ways so long as I am in my senses; but for the sake of precedent the Senate should beware of binding itself to support the acts of any man, since he might through some mischance suffer a change.', 67737, 0), (494207, 'When you are through changing, you are through.', 43653, 0), (494208, 'We won''t be able to stop disasters from happening. On the contrary, climate change may increase the frequency and severity of floods, droughts and storms. But we are better equipped today to prepare for them and reduce their impact.', 71491, 0), (494209, 'Future shock is the shattering stress and disorientation that we induce in individuals by subjecting them to too much change in too short a time.', 28611, 0), (494210, 'The world hates change, yet it is the only thing that has brought progress.', 66718, 0), (494211, 'Change occurs in direct proportion to dissatisfaction, but dissatisfaction never changes.', 67402, 0), (494212, 'He that will not apply new remedies must expect new evils for time is the greatest innovator. ', 1035, 0), (494213, 'All things must change to something new, to something strange.', 147, 0), (494214, 'Change alone is unchanging.', 1083, 0), (494215, 'Just because everything is different doesn''t mean anything has changed.', 63141, 0), (494216, 'It is change, continuing change, inevitable change, that is the dominant factor in society today. No sensible decision can be made any longer without taking into account not only the world as it is, but the world as it will be.', 988, 0), (494217, 'Ignorance is always afraid of change.', 8325, 0), (494218, 'Everything in life that we really accept undergoes a change.', 3172, 0), (494219, 'The changes in our life must come from the impossibility to live otherwise than according to the demands of our conscience not from our mental resolution to try a new form of life.', 93, 0), (494220, 'I have noticed even people who claim everything is predestined, and that we can do nothing to change it, look before they cross the road.', 1222, 0), (494221, 'For changes to be of any true value, they''ve got to be lasting and consistent.', 5675, 0), (494222, 'As with anything creative, change is inevitable.', 70718, 0), (494223, 'If you want to change the culture, you will have to start by changing the organization.', 70952, 0), (494224, 'Win as if you were used to it, lose as if you enjoyed it for a change.', 760, 0), (494225, 'An Internet meme is a hijacking of the original idea. Instead of mutating by random change and spreading by a form of Darwinian selection, Internet memes are altered deliberately by human creativity. There is no attempt at accuracy of copying, as with genes - and as with memes in their original version.', 1716, 0), (494226, 'Today in America, we are trying to prepare students for a high tech world of constant change, but we are doing so by putting them through a school system designed in the early 20th Century that has not seen substantial change in 30 years.', 70324, 0), (494227, 'The question is not whether we are able to change but whether we are changing fast enough.', 67556, 0), (494228, 'Redemption just means you just make a change in your life and you try to do right, versus what you were doing, which was wrong.', 11834, 0), (494229, 'Urbanization is not about simply increasing the number of urban residents or expanding the area of cities. More importantly, it''s about a complete change from rural to urban style in terms of industry structure, employment, living environment and social security.', 72471, 0), (494230, 'I''m not a proper traveler. I don''t like to be challenged or have too much of a change and prefer a week away just to relax.', 1566, 0), (494231, 'I was born not knowing and have had only a little time to change that here and there.', 66888, 0), (494232, 'Integrity is not a conditional word. It doesn''t blow in the wind or change with the weather. It is your inner image of yourself, and if you look in there and see a man who won''t cheat, then you know he never will.', 8000, 0), (494233, 'I want to be able to look back and say, ''I''ve done everything I can, and I was successful.'' I don''t want to look back and say I should have done this or that. I''d like to change things for the younger generation of swimmers coming along.', 30837, 0), (494234, 'We cannot erase what has been done. We can apologize for it. We can express our outrage. We can say to the American people and to the people of the world, this is not our way and we do not condone it, but we cannot change it and we cannot erase it.', 71230, 0), (494235, 'A change in bad habits leads to a change in life.', 75997, 0), (494236, 'There''s no reason to change what you are, but if you''re not being you, then you need to acknowledge that.', 2519, 0), (494237, 'I change during the course of a day. I wake and I''m one person, and when I go to sleep I know for certain I''m somebody else.', 289, 0), (494238, 'Cubism was an attack on the perspective that had been known and used for 500 years. It was the first big, big change. It confused people: they said, ''Things don''t look like that!''', 69898, 0), (494239, 'One game, one pitch can change everything for a hitter. The way I like to approach it is that every at-bat is its own unique opportunity to go out there and do something really good.', 67689, 0), (494240, 'In a liquid modern life there are no permanent bonds, and any that we take up for a time must be tied loosely so that they can be untied again, as quickly and as effortlessly as possible, when circumstances change - as they surely will in our liquid modern society, over and over again.', 33120, 0), (494241, 'People change. I wouldn''t like to be accountable for the interviews I''ve done, or the person I was when I was 20, 21.', 70674, 0), (494242, 'When we are no longer able to change a situation - just think of an incurable disease such as an inoperable cancer - we are challenged to change ourselves.', 855, 0), (494243, 'Culture change means we will do things differently.', 54622, 0), (494244, 'Let us take things as we find them: let us not attempt to distort them into what they are not... We cannot make facts. All our wishing cannot change them. We must use them.', 170, 0), (494245, 'All conservatism is based upon the idea that if you leave things alone you leave them as they are. But you do not. If you leave a thing alone you leave it to a torrent of change.', 67663, 0), (494246, 'Vengeance is not the point change is. But the trouble is that in most people''s minds the thought of victory and the thought of punishing the enemy coincide. ', 49452, 0), (494247, 'The rate of change is not going to slow down anytime soon. If anything, competition in most industries will probably speed up even more in the next few decades.', 68859, 0), (494248, 'I don''t think the human mind can comprehend the past and the future. They are both just illusions that can manipulate you into thinking theres some kind of change.', 289, 0), (494249, 'Do not let circumstances control you. You change your circumstances.', 67756, 0), (494250, 'Complainers change their complaints, but they never reduce the amount of time spent in complaining.', 12469, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (494251, 'The storm came. Lives were washed away. Ancient pains resurfaced. Now it is time for a sea of change.', 42974, 0), (494252, 'Change is not an event, it''s a process.', 67179, 0), (494253, 'I think the tiniest little thing can change the course of your day, which can change the course of your year, which can change who you are.', 100, 0), (494254, 'Great companies start because the founders want to change the world... not make a fast buck.', 5456, 0), (494255, 'I''ve never stopped being Argentine, and I''ve never wanted to. I feel very proud of being Argentine, even though I left there. I''ve been clear about this since I was very young, and I never wanted to change. Barcelona is my home because both the club and the people here have given me everything, but I won''t stop being Argentine.', 6325, 0), (494256, 'I was taught over and over again that the accumulation of random mutations led to evolutionary change - led to new species. I believed it until I looked for evidence.', 13557, 0), (494257, 'First of all, Greece won''t go down. We''re talking about a country that is capable of making change. Europe will not allow the destabilization of the 27-country euro zone. But if there were no action, then markets would start becoming jittery about other countries - and not only Spain and Portugal, but other countries in the European Union.', 71248, 0), (494258, 'There''s a magic that comes from playing entirely to who you are. I''ve got my specialist subject - in the Mastermind sense - and I wouldn''t change it, or who I am.', 75998, 0), (494259, 'Fraud is common when you give away billions. Fraud related to Hurricane Katrina spending is estimated to top $2 billion. In addition, debit cards provided to hurricane victims were used to pay for Caribbean vacations, NFL tickets, Dom Perignon champagne, ''Girls Gone Wild'' videos, and at least one sex change operation.', 16058, 0), (494260, 'Guns are part of the American psyche, aren''t they? This is collateral damage for having a Wild West mentality. It''s intrinsic to the American psyche. It''s never going to change.', 2317, 0), (494261, 'My feeling about seeing the world is that it''s going to change you necessarily, just the very fact of being out there and meeting people from different cultures and different ways of life.', 7878, 0), (494262, 'A boycott is directed against a policy and the institutions which support that policy either actively or tacitly. Its aim is not to reject, but to bring about change.', 1307, 0), (494263, 'Two places are ordained for man to dwell in after this life. While he is here, he may choose, by God''s mercy, which he will; but once he is gone from here, he may not do so. For whichever he first goes to, whether he like it well or ill, there he must dwell forevermore. He shall never after change his dwelling, though he hates it ever so badly.', 50946, 0), (494264, 'People change their opinion according to your position. And both politicians and bureaucrats begin to take you more seriously, as they suddenly feel you have become more important.', 75999, 0), (494265, 'Every different social group that I encountered had its different set of rules, so you learn very quickly how to pick up the nuances and change yourself accordingly. When you are not from anywhere, you have to try to find what''s universal. You are always trying to fit in.', 433, 0), (494266, 'Change is always a little bit strange.', 22990, 0), (494267, 'All time is all time. It does not change. It does not lend itself to warnings or explanations. It simply is.', 13666, 0), (494268, 'It''s quite normal to hear of a change and see it as a problem, but it''s probably an opportunity, depending on how quickly you can adjust.', 70338, 0), (494269, 'There was something undifferentiated and yet complete, which existed before Heaven and Earth. Soundless and formless, it depends on nothing and does not change. It operates everywhere and is free from danger. It may be considered the mother of the universe. I do not know its name; I call it Tao.', 15, 0), (494270, 'I am a big proponent of character arcs that show us how people change over time.', 13502, 0), (494271, 'We can change the direction of the country with our vote.', 74653, 0), (494272, 'I was the biggest liar for no reason, and then as I got older, I thought, ''Why am I lying to everybody?'' I would hear other people lie and be like, ''You sound so stupid.'' So then I would just change my lies. The only person I lie to is my little sister, when I steal her clothes.', 68261, 0), (494273, 'If you compare Everest photographs in 1953 with its current state, things are melting. I imagine if I were a golfer in Indiana, I''d be hard-pressed to believe in climate change because nothing''s going on there. But when you''re up in the mountains and seeing the glaciers melt away, it''s an obvious physical manifestation of a warming planet.', 61808, 0), (494274, 'Early in life I had to choose between honest arrogance and hypocritical humility. I chose the former and have seen no reason to change.', 1836, 0), (494275, 'If you don''t like the way the world is, you change it. You have an obligation to change it. You just do it one step at a time.', 7224, 0), (494276, 'The range of what we think and do is limited by what we fail to notice. And because we fail to notice that we fail to notice, there is little we can do to change; until we notice how failing to notice shapes our thoughts and deeds.', 2799, 0), (494277, 'For time and the world do not stand still. Change is the law of life. And those who look only to the past or the present are certain to miss the future.', 1680, 0), (494278, 'Change means movement. Movement means friction. Only in the frictionless vacuum of a nonexistent abstract world can movement or change occur without that abrasive friction of conflict.', 48660, 0), (494279, 'The need for change bulldozed a road down the center of my mind.', 74, 0), (494280, 'Artists to my mind are the real architects of change, and not the political legislators who implement change after the fact.', 320, 0), (494281, 'Human memory is a marvelous but fallacious instrument. The memories which lie within us are not carved in stone; not only do they tend to become erased as the years go by, but often they change, or even increase by incorporating extraneous features.', 5991, 0), (494282, 'Are creeds such simple things like the clothes which a man can change at will and put on at will? Creeds are such for which people live for ages and ages.', 32, 0), (494283, 'So the next thing I assume I''ll be hearing from Republicans, they want to change rules some way, as they do on the House when you get a problem with ethics, they just change the rules.', 48859, 0), (494284, 'Sometimes we look for those thunderous things to happen in our life for our lives to change or go in the other direction. We seek the miracle. We seek the parting of the seas, the moving of the mountains. But no, it''s a quiet thing. At least for me it was.', 71130, 0), (494285, 'Everything I do in my life is very instinctual and in the moment. If I''m attracted to something, that''s it. If I have reservations, those don''t change till they''re resolved. My first impression is how I go.', 72891, 0), (494286, 'I accepted a change in my life. I didn''t choose that change and those are the best changes to make.', 55545, 0), (494287, 'For a change, lady luck seemed to be smiling on me. Then again, maybe the fickle wench was just lulling me into a false sense of security while she reached for a rock.', 7772, 0), (494288, 'For people who have... had curve balls thrown at them, it is easier to digest change and digest change in other people. Change only scares the small-minded. The small-minded and me.', 68511, 0), (494289, 'Activists are generally doers - rather than watching television and thinking about the world they will put there energies into doing something ''active'' to change the (political) situation.', 76000, 0), (494290, 'What I worry about is climate change, because that would have untold effects that we can''t even measure yet.', 75067, 0), (494291, 'You realize you can''t change the world but it shouldn''t stop you from trying.', 76001, 0), (494292, 'It''s generally much easier to kill an organization than to change it substantially.', 14847, 0), (494293, 'With a painter or a sculptor, one cannot begin to alter his works, but an architect has to put up with anything, because he makes utility objects - the building is there to be used, and times change.', 72348, 0), (494294, 'Geological change usually takes thousands of years to happen but we are seeing the climate changing not just in our lifetimes but also year by year.', 56748, 0), (494295, 'A visit to a cinema is a little outing in itself. It breaks the monotony of an afternoon or evening; it gives a change from the surroundings of home, however pleasant.', 74330, 0), (494296, 'It is nonsense to say that Germans are unable to change.', 67556, 0), (494297, 'I tend to arrive in the rehearsal process with very strongly developed ideas about what I want to do. But I don''t like those ideas to be things that are not subject to change, or subject to development, or subject to challenge.', 71114, 0), (494298, 'Countries such as the U.S. and Britain have taken it upon themselves to decide for us in the developing world, even to interfere in our domestic affairs and to bring about what they call regime change.', 32803, 0), (494299, 'Which goes to show you, you can make all the laws you want, but you cannot change people''s ways. If you must change them, you have to understand that it will take a long time.', 64289, 0), (494300, 'If you never change your mind, why have one?', 26588, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (494301, 'One new feature or fresh take can change everything.', 1082, 0), (494302, 'A zebra does not change its spots.', 13473, 0), (494303, 'The spirit of democracy is not a mechanical thing to be adjusted by abolition of forms. It requires change of heart.', 32, 0), (494304, 'Social change isn''t something you should do just to help pad a resume. Follow your passion.', 69966, 0), (494305, 'In a progressive country change is constant change is inevitable. ', 1827, 0), (494306, 'What we call progress is the exchange of one nuisance for another nuisance.', 62533, 0), (494307, 'Mathematicians are like managers - they want improvement without change.', 67499, 0), (494308, 'There''s an old saying, this too shall pass, and change is good.', 73238, 0), (494309, 'Hip-hop is supposed to uplift and create, to educate people on a larger level and to make a change.', 67916, 0), (494310, 'If you feel like it''s difficult to change, you will probably have a harder time succeeding.', 66601, 0), (494311, 'We all know that change is inevitable. It provides us with a challenge and an opportunity to grow and improve and to attract new members with new ideas.', 73757, 0), (494312, 'Wealth brings with it refinement, the spirit of conservation, while poverty inspires adventurous ideas, the desire to change things, and has little care for life.', 3961, 0), (494313, 'Some scientists believe climate change is the cause of unprecedented melting of the North Pole, and that effects these very uncertain weather patterns. I think we should listen to those scientists and experts.', 5025, 0), (494314, 'Only idiots refuse to change their minds.', 15813, 0), (494315, 'If the shoe doesn''t fit, must we change the foot?', 1739, 0), (494316, 'One change always leaves the way open for the establishment of others.', 947, 0), (494317, 'Words are powerful; if you change your words, you can change your life.', 1206, 0), (494318, 'I never blame myself when I''m not hitting. I just blame the bat and if it keeps up, I change bats. After all, if I know it isn''t my fault that I''m not hitting, how can I get mad at myself?', 1896, 0), (494319, 'You''ve got to change incentives for good behavior as opposed to just disincentivizing bad behavior.', 49967, 0), (494320, 'Character isn''t something you were born with and can''t change, like your fingerprints. It''s something you weren''t born with and must take responsibility for forming.', 1295, 0), (494321, 'I''m a Gemini, so I change my mind every day.', 26614, 0), (494322, 'Things of this world are in so constant a flux, that nothing remains long in the same state.', 2375, 0), (494323, 'In times of change learners inherit the earth while the learned find themselves beautifully equipped to deal with a world that no longer exists. ', 2567, 0), (494324, 'Change alone is eternal, perpetual, immortal.', 1304, 0), (494325, 'If you want to make enemies, try to change something.', 1970, 0), (494326, 'Passion has always been important to me. That won''t change. What changes in a woman''s perspective. I mean, I have two kids now. I''m a single parent balancing motherhood and my career. That changes the equation.', 74921, 0), (494327, 'Good intentions never change anything. They only become a deeper and deeper rut.', 1206, 0), (494328, 'No one can persuade another to change. Each of us guards a gate of change that can only be opened from the inside. We cannot open the gate of another, either by argument or emotional appeal.', 62855, 0), (494329, 'I still believe that if your aim is to change the world, journalism is a more immediate short-term weapon.', 408, 0), (494330, 'Religions cannot change you. If you are angry, you will become an angry Muslim or Hindu. If you are righteous, you will become a righteous Christian or Jew.', 21209, 0), (494331, 'The ability to change constantly and effectively is made easier by high-level continuity.', 66809, 0), (494332, 'I wouldn''t change a thing about what I''ve done in the past because what may have been bad choices have all led me to this moment.', 75416, 0), (494333, 'It behooves every man who values liberty of conscience for himself, to resist invasions of it in the case of others: or their case may, by change of circumstances, become his own.', 1207, 0), (494334, 'My goal was never to just create a company. A lot of people misinterpret that, as if I don''t care about revenue or profit or any of those things. But what not being just a company means to me is not being just that - building something that actually makes a really big change in the world.', 5553, 0), (494335, 'There''s no sense in going to a tournament if you don''t believe that you can win it. And that is the belief I have always had. And that is not going to change.', 11163, 0), (494336, 'Everybody talks about wanting to change things and help and fix, but ultimately all you can do is fix yourself. And that''s a lot. Because if you can fix yourself, it has a ripple effect.', 22523, 0), (494337, 'There are two kinds of fools: those who can''t change their opinions and those who won''t.', 3355, 0), (494338, 'I would tell 17-year-olds to be proud of who you are. Don''t try to change yourself for others. Focus on school and your future. Boys and friends will come and go, just focus on you and your future.', 10135, 0), (494339, 'One of my favorite philosophical tenets is that people will agree with you only if they already agree with you. You do not change people''s minds.', 1022, 0), (494340, 'It''s better to get smart than to get mad. I try not to get so insulted that I will not take advantage of an opportunity to persuade people to change their minds.', 68178, 0), (494341, 'And Seaman, just like a falling oak, manages to change direction.', 76002, 0), (494342, 'Routines are normal, natural, healthy things. Most of us take a shower and brush our teeth every day. That is a good routine. Spiritual disciplines are routines. That is a good thing. But once routines become routine you need to change your routine.', 5298, 0), (494343, 'I was wired to be intense. I don''t think that''s ever going to change.', 71285, 0), (494344, 'I think it''s an actor''s responsibility to change every time. Not only for himself and the people he''s working with, but for the audience. If you just go out and deliver the same dish every time... it''s meat loaf again... you''d get bored. I''d get bored.', 148, 0), (494345, 'I want to inspire people to change the world. That''s something that I feel that I''m meant to do here... really going to change the world. I asked God to make me immortal so I can do it.', 69359, 0), (494346, 'When a plan or strategy fails, people are tempted to assume it was the wrong vision. Plans and strategies can always be changed and improved. But vision doesn''t change. Visions are simply refined with time.', 4279, 0), (494347, 'Is there climate change? I live in the shadow of some of the greatest climate change the world has ever seen. It''s called the Rocky Mountains. When the glaciers went back.', 50236, 0), (494348, 'I would point out that if you''re a believer in the Bible, one would have to say the Great Flood is an example of climate change and that certainly wasn''t because mankind had overdeveloped hydrocarbon energy.', 72869, 0), (494349, 'One must change one''s tactics every ten years if one wishes to maintain one''s superiority.', 1702, 0), (494350, 'The why is what makes journalism an adult game. The why is what makes policy coherent and useful. The why is what transforms bureaucrats and foot soldiers and political leaders into viable instruments of rational and affirmative change. The why is everything and without it, the very suggestion of human progress becomes a cosmic joke.', 28866, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (494351, 'Really, each era has its own false nostalgia. We all put a picket fence up around something. For my generation it was the ''50s, and for other generations it will be something else. Change is scary for everyone, as is complexity, contradiction, and an uncertain future.', 68157, 0), (494352, 'For good and evil, man is a free creative spirit. This produces the very queer world we live in, a world in continuous creation and therefore continuous change and insecurity.', 3449, 0), (494353, 'The faults of a superior person are like the sun and moon. They have their faults, and everyone sees them; they change and everyone looks up to them.', 819, 0), (494354, 'Nothing remains great without a capacity to change and to accommodate the conditions of a changing world.', 35052, 0), (494355, 'The 200 years when Britain and the US were the top two economies were an aberration and that will change. The decline of empires has happened much faster than folks think. I believe that gold will be a far better bet in 20 years than the dollar.', 76003, 0), (494356, 'At a time when the GOP is playing games with the debt limit, a member of the Supreme Court is refusing to recuse himself from matters he has a financial interest in, and middle class incomes are stagnant, many want to change the subject. I don''t. This was a prank, and a silly one. I''m focused on my work.', 74724, 0), (494357, 'I have a way of filming things and staging them and designing sets. There were times when I thought I should change my approach, but in fact, this is what I like to do. It''s sort of like my handwriting as a movie director. And somewhere along the way, I think I''ve made the decision: I''m going to write in my own handwriting.', 74494, 0), (494358, 'When I was 13, I was in my tent at Girl Scout camp, trying to change out of my bathing suit and talking at the same time. I fell out of the tent in front of everyone with my bathing suit around my ankles. I was humiliated - but no amount of humiliation has ever seemed to stop me.', 72056, 0), (494359, 'The important thing to remember, if you are trying something that is an innovation, is not to think too much about it. Because if you take too long, by the time you get there, the world will have changed. You take a risk, and if it doesn''t work, you make a change. We are not betting our lives on it.', 3720, 0), (494360, 'As human beings we do change, grow, adapt, perhaps even learn and become wiser.', 72952, 0), (494361, 'There are many things we do not want about the world. Let us not just mourn them. Let us change them.', 72448, 0), (494362, 'Friendships that have stood the test of time and change are surely best.', 76004, 0), (494363, 'If there is anything that we wish to change in the child, we should first examine it and see whether it is not something that could better be changed in ourselves.', 28934, 0), (494364, 'People are always looking for the single magic bullet that will totally change everything. There is no single magic bullet.', 11095, 0), (494365, 'In our view, successful reform is not an event. It is a sustainable process that will build on its own successes - a virtuous cycle of change.', 30519, 0), (494366, 'To me, eyewear goes way beyond being a prescription. It''s like makeup. It''s the most incredible accessory. The shape of a frame or the color of lenses can change your whole appearance.', 66693, 0), (494367, 'Words have meaning. And their meaning doesn''t change.', 21037, 0), (494368, 'The difference between political terror and ordinary crime becomes clear during the change of regimes, in which former terrorists become well-regarded representatives of their country.', 13787, 0), (494369, 'You put high heels on and you change.', 57401, 0), (494370, 'If you really want change, you really want it to be inclusive, where everyone''s included, otherwise you''re just going to have more of the same in the future.', 32686, 0), (494371, 'I think change needs to be egoless. It''s not about my leaving my fingerprints or a legacy. It''s more important to be part of a process by rolling up your sleeves, being on the ground, initiating projects, starting campaigns - you know, building stuff.', 67571, 0), (494372, 'You can''t build an adaptable organization without adaptable people - and individuals change only when they have to, or when they want to.', 30035, 0), (494373, 'I think the NRA, they got it half-right when they say, ''Guns don''t kill people, people kill people.'' I change it to, ''Guns don''t kill people, Americans kill people.''', 17499, 0), (494374, 'You can talk yourself into a good emotional state. I stop for a second, take a deep breath, and think about something that''s beautiful. A beautiful thought for me is cutting the umbilical cord for my child. I can guarantee you that your emotional state will change.', 72059, 0), (494375, 'A lot can change in the editing room.', 67021, 0), (494376, 'As life runs on, the road grows strange with faces new - and near the end. The milestones into headstones change, Neath every one a friend.', 1247, 0), (494377, 'You know, Motorcycle Diaries has no incredible stories, no sudden plot twists, it doesn''t play that way. It''s about recognizing that instance of change and embracing it.', 67800, 0), (494378, 'We think the whole world''s going to change, and forget that human beings are still human beings; we have the same five senses, we still interact the same way, we still love and hate the same way, but marketers lose track of that. But then it comes down to earth.', 69564, 0), (494379, 'A hero is someone right who doesn''t change.', 26132, 0), (494380, 'Change is not made without inconvenience, even from worse to better.', 10703, 0), (494381, 'Change is unavoidable. You change either to stay ahead or to catch up.', 68343, 0), (494382, 'I don''t see a sea change by 2020, but I see migration in the direction of modernization and more flexibility in t