se myself in another character and actually get paid for it... It''s a great outlet. I''m not really sure who I am - it seems I change every day.', 68700, 0), (494427, 'I would change policy, bring back natural grass and nickel beer. Baseball is the belly-button of our society. Straighten out baseball, and you straighten out the rest of the world.', 76007, 0), (494428, 'The only change is that baseball has turned Paige from a second class citizen to a second class immortal.', 5228, 0), (494429, 'The customs and fashions of men change like leaves on the bough, some of which go and others come.', 849, 0), (494430, 'It seems to me that any sensible person must see that violence does not change the world and if it does, then only temporarily.', 21702, 0), (494431, 'The most useless are those who never change through the years.', 64116, 0), (494432, 'With me a change of trouble is as good as a vacation.', 55270, 0), (494433, 'Man has a limited biological capacity for change. When this capacity is overwhelmed, the capacity is in future shock.', 28611, 0), (494434, 'Most of the change we think we see in life is due to truths being in and out of favor.', 35, 0), (494435, 'I want to test my maximum and see how much I can do. And I want to change the world of swimming.', 30837, 0), (494436, 'Our decade of change has unleashed the ingenuity, creativity, and character of the most extraordinary people in the world - the people of this state, who come from every corner of the globe.', 73779, 0), (494437, 'We don''t change what we are, we change what we think what we are.', 72982, 0), (494438, 'Life has got a habit of not standing hitched. You got to ride it like you find it. You got to change with it. If a day goes by that don''t change some of your old notions for new ones, that is just about like trying to milk a dead cow.', 2473, 0), (494439, 'I write a lot, and very often I write a couple of lines that are particularly revealing in some kind of way. And then as a few more lines get added and a piece gets added, eventually the song pretty much takes over and you can''t really find a way to change those things.', 2317, 0), (494440, 'Nothing is as real as a dream. The world can change around you, but your dream will not. Your life may change, but your dream doesn''t have to. Responsibilities need not erase it. Duties need not obscure it.', 1046, 0), (494441, 'Change is good. And in fact unavoidable.', 74002, 0), (494442, 'We have nothing less to do than to get inside of whole peoples and change their motives and dispositions.', 73822, 0), (494443, 'Dressing up. People just don''t do it anymore. We have to change that.', 72906, 0), (494444, 'I don''t think anything changes until ideas change. The usual American viewpoint is to believe that something is wrong with the person.', 7176, 0), (494445, 'Given that, and assuming that we begin to adjust to issues like climate change and the greenhouse effect, Denver''s location in the center of the country becomes a tremendous advantage.', 75395, 0), (494446, 'The only people available to change the world are the people now living in it, with all the beliefs they bring along - however retrograde those beliefs may appear to those of us who see ourselves as enlightened.', 73320, 0), (494447, 'The prize seemed to change my professional life very little.', 72365, 0), (494448, 'On The Practice, I get to do what I love to do, and I am making a contribution that will, in the end, help raise social consciousness, dispel some of the myths about being large, and change the way that people view and interact with large people.', 28565, 0), (494449, 'When you play against different people from all walks of life you can''t do the same thing against every player defensively or offensively. You have to change up the way you go at a player.', 75216, 0), (494450, 'Technological discoveries are the spermatozoa of social change.', 3002, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (494451, 'I am a contradictory mess but I see it as my prerogative to change my mood like the weather.', 28855, 0), (494452, 'My grandfather taught me generosity. He sold snow cones in Harlem. I went with him at 5 and he let me hand out the change and snow cones. I learned a lot in the couple of years that we did that.', 74413, 0), (494453, 'As a consequence, geneticists described evolution simply as a change in gene frequencies in populations, totally ignoring the fact that evolution consists of the two simultaneous but quite separate phenomena of adaptation and diversification.', 75156, 0), (494454, 'If you marry the wrong person for the wrong reasons, then no matter how hard you work, it''s never going to work, because then you have to completely change yourself, completely change them, completely - by that time, you''re both dead.', 73123, 0), (494455, 'My disorder has been attended with several symptoms of a consumption; and I have been at times apprehensive that my great change was at hand: yet blessed be God, I have never been affrighted; but, on the contrary, at times much delighted with a view of its approach.', 67770, 0), (494456, 'Yet, despite our many advances, our environment is still threatened by a range of problems, including global climate change, energy dependence on unsustainable fossil fuels, and loss of biodiversity.', 72463, 0), (494457, 'The thing that surprises me most is, you cannot change who you are.', 76008, 0), (494458, 'I am an optimist because I want to change things for the better and I know that blood has to be spilled and disharmony and cruelty are necessary to do that.', 68, 0), (494459, 'The conservative who resists change is as valuable as the radical who proposes it.', 74183, 0), (494460, 'You have to change your mind with every orchestra because every orchestra has a different character.', 71124, 0), (494461, 'Sometimes I think change is a good thing.', 10113, 0), (49446