y process provides for political and social change without violence.', 5358, 0), (494476, 'I believe that history has shape, order, and meaning; that exceptional men, as much as economic forces, produce change; and that passe abstractions like beauty, nobility, and greatness have a shifting but continuing validity.', 1920, 0), (494477, 'Change is such hard work.', 22849, 0), (494478, 'It''s quite nice to see that I didn''t have to change who I was to reach two very different types of people.', 19768, 0), (494479, 'You hold the keys of change within you. You be the change you want to see.', 58655, 0), (494480, 'Change will come slowly, across generations, because old beliefs die hard even when demonstrably false.', 44747, 0), (494481, 'How many Republicans does it take to change a light bulb? Three. One to mix the martinis, one to change the light bulb, and one to reminisce about how good the old one was.', 20608, 0), (494482, 'I have a resistance to change in things that I feel comfortable with and that I''m used to.', 70669, 0), (494483, 'I''m a catalyst for change. You can''t be an outsider and be successful over 30 years without leaving a certain amount of scar tissue around the place.', 15116, 0), (494484, 'Things change. I used to have a real resistance to it and hold on to things, but let things happen and go with it, and you will actually go through it, and it''s a lot less stressful.', 69505, 0), (494485, 'Change is inevitable. Change for the better is a full-time job.', 69260, 0), (494486, 'The foolish and the dead alone never change their opinions.', 1247, 0), (494487, 'Let the great world spin for ever down the ringing grooves of change.', 63203, 0), (494488, 'To change what you get, you must change who you are.', 1508, 0), (494489, 'Each child is an adventure into a better life - an opportunity to change the old pattern and make it new.', 15498, 0), (494490, 'I don''t know if you can change things, but it''s a drop in the ocean.', 66805, 0), (494491, 'Il