INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (494501, 'No change in musical style will survive unless it is accompanied by a change in clothing style. Rock is to dress up to.', 1022, 0), (494502, 'The cartoon is a metaphor really for the fact that it''s almost impossible in our celebrity obsessed culture to move around genres and sort of change you ideas, change your face, you know?', 67504, 0), (494503, 'With all the highs and lows I''ve had in my life, I wouldn''t change anything. So no, I don''t, this is what I''m supposed to be doing.', 70998, 0), (494504, 'Change, when it comes, cracks everything open.', 3167, 0), (494505, 'The consideration of change over the century is about loss, though I think that social change is gain rather than loss.', 11995, 0), (494506, 'We want the facts to fit the preconceptions. When they don''t it is easier to ignore the facts than to change the preconceptions.', 3164, 0), (494507, 'You know, I change my hair color a lot, I do all sorts of different things.', 73178, 0), (494508, 'The typical journalist''s typical lead for the typical Canadian story nowadays is along this line: that Canadians are hard at work trying to gain a reputation as a nation of rapid social change.', 67782, 0), (494509, 'Some players are more physical than others, some play with more finesse. Some are just really great all-around players. So you have to change your game.', 75216, 0), (494510, 'What we can do as individuals may not be very much on the global scale, but we have to start the change by living as we are teaching.', 74084, 0), (494511, 'I''ve been a Dolphin for 17 years, and I''ll be a Dolphin for the rest of my life. That will never change.', 67164, 0), (494512, 'Christians are supposed not merely to endure change, nor even to profit by it, but to cause it.', 51228, 0), (494513, 'I have a tendency to go through my life at full speed and as a one-man band, and so I don''t generally stop and take in other people enough to develop many relationships. I''m starting to regret that a bit. I want to change it.', 87, 0), (494514, 'I don''t have ideas so much as there are things which constantly evolve... there are various threads or layers, if you like, which change.', 67171, 0), (494515, 'One reason we resist making deliberate choices is that choice equals change and most of us, feeling the world is unpredictable enough, try to minimise the trauma of change in our personal lives.', 73329, 0), (494516, 'Some programming languages manage to absorb change, but withstand progress.', 67173, 0), (494517, 'Even if I know I shall never change the masses, never transform anything permanent, all I ask is that the good things also have their place, their refuge.', 4756, 0), (494518, 'Without change, something sleeps inside us, and seldom awakens. The sleeper must awaken.', 1265, 0), (494519, 'To change a habit, make a conscious decision, then act out the new behavior.', 1572, 0), (494520, 'Any change, even a change for the better, is always accompanied by drawbacks and discomforts.', 7164, 0), (494521, 'Remember before nineteen seventy two Olympic Games I was total skinny, I was small, very strong, they may be don''t like to see a gymnastics like that. I don''t know but, gymnastics, might. Nineteen seventy two supposed to be change somewhere.', 74302, 0), (494522, 'Philosophies change by the day while God never changes, simply because, being perfect, He does not have to change!', 73512, 0), (494523, 'Weep not that the world changes - did it keep a stable, changeless state, it were cause indeed to weep.', 70801, 0), (494524, 'In a change of masters the poor change nothing except their master''s name.', 62869, 0), (494525, 'I found a sound that people really liked - I found this basic concept and all I did was change the lyrics and the melody a little bit. My songs, if you listen to them, they''re quite a lot alike, like Chuck Berry.', 72077, 0), (494526, 'You must change in order to survive.', 27040, 0), (494527, 'I was away from the front lines for a while this spring, living with other troops, and considerable fighting took place while I was gone. When I got ready to return to my old friends at the front I wondered if I would sense any change in them.', 9247, 0), (494528, 'If you can change three lives in 10, three lives in a hundred, that''s got to be good, hasn''t it?', 69648, 0), (494529, 'Slowness to change usually means fear of the new.', 72586, 0), (494530, 'Change is not only likely, it''s inevitable.', 30125, 0), (494531, 'When it becomes more difficult to suffer than to change... you will change.', 5857, 0), (494532, 'Things change all the time, and they''ll probably never be the same again. It''s just the natural evolution of the human condition. Things change, and whatever it is is what it is. I mean, you try to start second guessing that, you either get rich or die broke.', 16932, 0), (494533, 'As every new breed of virus is conceived, created and released into the wild, another small change is made to the anti-virus software to combat the new threat.', 74283, 0), (494534, 'The main dangers in this life are the people who want to change everything... or nothing.', 22265, 0), (494535, 'I am sorry to upset my colleagues by saying we wasted four years in opposition, but if you do get so badly defeated as a party you do have to face up to some painful facts and you do have to change.', 76010, 0), (494536, 'Look at all the buses now that want exact change, exact change. I figure if I give them exact change, they should take me exactly where I want to go.', 50687, 0), (494537, 'Buddhism teaches you to embrace change.', 67281, 0), (494538, 'Serve the dinner backward, do anything - but for goodness sake, do something weird.', 64259, 0), (494539, 'Our fathers valued change for the sake of its results we value it in the act. ', 62853, 0), (494540, 'That man is a creature who needs order yet yearns for change is the creative contradiction at the heart of the laws which structure his conformity and define his deviancy.', 73554, 0), (494541, 'Yet what you need is not marches, demonstrations, rallies or wide associations, all of them are important. What you need is direct action. The sooner people understand that, the sooner we''ll begin to change things.', 71218, 0), (494542, 'Change is tough, people don''t like it, but it is necessary. Take two aspirins and call me in the morning.', 74207, 0), (494543, 'Not only is women''s work never done, the definition keeps changing.', 37846, 0), (494544, 'Perfection is immutable. But for things imperfect, change is the way to perfect them.', 43019, 0), (494545, 'In not my, but our collective hands, is held the promise of change.', 76011, 0), (494546, 'The moral world is as little exempt as the physical world from the law of ceaseless change, of perpetual flux.', 70866, 0), (494547, 'We emphasize that we believe in change because we were born of it, we have lived by it, we prospered and grew great by it. So the status quo has never been our god, and we ask no one else to bow down before it.', 10272, 0), (494548, 'I have the ability to create and be in touch with God. I can''t change bread and wine into body and blood, but I can take the scum or the slime of the earth and make it into a man or woman.', 76012, 0), (494549, 'Change is the only constant. Hanging on is the only sin.', 76013, 0), (494550, 'The veterans of our military services have put their lives on the line to protect the freedoms that we enjoy. They have dedicated their lives to their country and deserve to be recognized for their commitment.', 76014, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (494551, 'True heroism is remarkably sober, very undramatic. It is not the urge to surpass all others at whatever cost, but the urge to serve others at whatever cost.', 52297, 0), (494552, 'While only one day of the year is dedicated solely to honoring our veterans, Americans must never forget the sacrifices that many of our fellow countrymen have made to defend our country and protect our freedoms.', 76015, 0), (494553, 'Honoring the sacrifices many have made for our country in the name of freedom and democracy is the very foundation of Veterans Day.', 41313, 0), (494554, 'Duty, Honor, Country. Those three hallowed words reverently dictate what you ought to be, what you can be, what you will be.', 2273, 0), (494555, 'On this Veterans Day, let us remember the service of our veterans, and let us renew our national promise to fulfill our sacred obligations to our veterans and their families who have sacrificed so much so that we can live free.', 72463, 0), (494556, 'The Lord gets his best soldiers out of the highlands of affliction.', 36532, 0), (494557, 'Our soldiers have nobly fought to protect freedom since our country''s birth, and have fought to protect those that could not protect themselves, even in foreign lands when called upon.', 67592, 0), (494558, 'Because all of us believe and understand in the fabric of the common bond of why we call ourselves American is to care for the men and women who wear the uniform; and when they take off the uniform, we care for them when they are veterans.', 68764, 0), (494559, 'The only thing that makes battle psychologically tolerable is the brotherhood among soldiers. You need each other to get by.', 14639, 0), (494560, 'America''s Veterans have served their country with the belief that democracy and freedom are ideals to be upheld around the world.', 68704, 0), (494561, 'Tragically, the effort to make America and the world safer and to defend freedom around the world is not without an enormous cost to this Nation in terms primarily of lost lives and those who bear the scars and the wounds of war, and their families who must bear these losses.', 71144, 0), (494562, 'Spending time with America''s soldiers is always inspiring.', 66633, 0), (494563, 'The U.S. Military is us. There is no truer representation of a country than the people that it sends into the field to fight for it. The people who wear our uniform and carry our rifles into combat are our kids, and our job is to support them, because they''re protecting us.', 1046, 0), (494564, 'The precondition to freedom is security.', 76016, 0), (494565, 'Well, look at what people are doing for returned veterans now. The wounded warriors. They''re working hard to make the wounded veterans feel that they are loved and welcomed home, unlike Vietnam. It was not a very kind, gentle world then. I think we are kinder and gentler.', 11962, 0), (494566, 'America''s trying to do the best for its veterans.', 70440, 0), (494567, 'The reward of one duty is the power to fulfill another.', 215, 0), (494568, 'I go where the sound of thunder is.', 76017, 0), (494569, 'When soldiers have been baptized in the fire of a battle-field, they have all one rank in my eyes.', 1702, 0), (494570, 'A few honest men are better than numbers.', 3851, 0), (494571, 'Perfect Valor is to do, without a witness, all that we could do before the whole world.', 154, 0), (494572, 'The thing is this: You got to have fun while you''re fightin'' for freedom, ''cause you don''t always win.', 2253, 0), (494573, 'As a former veteran, I understand the needs of veterans, and have been clear - we will work together, stand together with the Administration, but we will also question their policies when they shortchange veterans and military retirees.', 70980, 0), (494574, 'There is nothing like staying at home for real comfort.', 24, 0), (494575, 'We are a country where people of all backgrounds, all nations of origin, all languages, all religions, all races, can make a home. America was built by immigrants.', 66567, 0), (494576, 'Home is where children find safety and security, where we find our identities, where citizenship starts. It usually starts with believing you''re part of a community, and that is essential to having a stable home.', 11679, 0), (494577, 'If you go anywhere, even paradise, you will miss your home.', 1851, 0), (494578, 'When everyone at school is speaking one language, and a lot of your classmates'' parents also speak it, and you go home and see that your community is different -there is a sense of shame attached to that. It really takes growing up to treasure the specialness of being different.', 11622, 0), (494579, 'When I come home, my daughter will run to the door and give me a big hug, and everything that''s happened that day just melts away.', 43985, 0), (494580, 'The ache for home lives in all of us, the safe place where we can go as we are and not be questioned.', 74, 0), (494581, 'America''s future will be determined by the home and the school. The child becomes largely what he is taught; hence we must watch what we teach, and how we live.', 21138, 0), (494582, 'On the battlefield, the military pledges to leave no soldier behind. As a nation, let it be our pledge that when they return home, we leave no veteran behind.', 72463, 0), (494583, 'The American People will come first once again. My plan will begin with safety at home - which means safe neighborhoods, secure borders, and protection from terrorism. There can be no prosperity without law and order.', 64643, 0), (494584, 'And when the day arrives I''ll become the sky and I''ll become the sea and the sea will come to kiss me for I am going home. Nothing can stop me now.', 60178, 0), (494585, 'Charity begins at home, and justice begins next door.', 96, 0), (494586, 'My parents said that sitting at home playing video games all day won''t bring you anywhere in life.', 13042, 0), (494587, 'Language, identity, place, home: these are all of a piece - just different elements of belonging and not-belonging.', 1590, 0), (494588, 'If you go back to your home town or you''re reunited with school friends, its always slightly bittersweet because as much as there''s nice things in terms of seeing them again, the town has changed without you, and you''re no longer a part of it.', 10032, 0), (494589, 'Most people, if you live in a big city, you see some form of schizophrenia every day, and it''s always in the form of someone homeless. ''Look at that guy - he''s crazy. He looks dangerous.'' Well, he''s on the streets because of mental illness. He probably had a job and a home.', 69134, 0), (494590, 'The beach is definitely where I feel most at home. It''s my oxygen. I forget how much I need it sometimes when I''m away working.', 72271, 0), (494591, 'I have two homes, like someone who leaves their hometown and/or parents and then establishes a life elsewhere. They might say that they''re going home when they return to see old friends or parents, but then they go home as well when they go to where they live now. Sarajevo is home, Chicago is home.', 1327, 0), (494592, 'Have nothing in your house that you do not know to be useful, or believe to be beautiful.', 7389, 0), (494593, 'I train and I go home, and when I''m home, I think about training. That''s my life every day, and that''s it.', 56476, 0), (494594, 'Every time I slip into the ocean, it''s like going home.', 67053, 0), (494595, 'Home is where one starts from.', 1067, 0), (494596, 'Bride and groom are not just two contracting parties but two loving and beloved companions, joined in establishing a home that will be nothing less than a source of immortality.', 70703, 0), (494597, 'The thrill of coming home has never changed.', 69518, 0), (494598, 'Every dog is a lion at home.', 71366, 0), (494599, 'A home without books is a body without soul.', 1306, 0), (494600, 'Life is hard, and a lot of people come home tired from work. If they''re gonna spend half an hour reading, they want some entertainment and a sense of achievement. So that''s what I give them. That''s all I''m trying to do. Is that really so wrong?', 285, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (494601, 'I am not going to die, I''m going home like a shooting star.', 2013, 0), (494602, 'Here''s kind of my motto - if you''re not happy at home, you''re not happy anywhere else.', 71860, 0), (494603, 'Yes, your home is your castle, but it is also your identity and your possibility to be open to others.', 72727, 0), (494604, 'It may be that the satisfaction I need depends on my going away, so that when I''ve gone and come back, I''ll find it at home.', 20453, 0), (494605, 'I long, as does every human being, to be at home wherever I find myself.', 74, 0), (494606, 'A good wife is someone who thinks she has done everything right: raising the kids, being there for the husband, being home, trying to do it all.', 69053, 0), (494607, 'After school, I''d wait for someone to pick me up and no one would, so I''d be like, ''I guess I''ll walk home.'' I had to be a hustler, because nobody did anything for me.', 75440, 0), (494608, 'There are a thousand ways to kneel and kiss the ground there are a thousand ways to go home again. ', 20453, 0), (494609, 'To meditate means to go home to yourself. Then you know how to take care of the things that are happening inside you, and you know how to take care of the things that happen around you.', 394, 0), (494610, 'My restless, roaming spirit would not allow me to remain at home very long.', 69032, 0), (494611, 'Home is, I suppose just a child''s idea. A house at night, and a lamp in the house. A place to feel safe.', 14772, 0), (494612, 'When we rebuild a house, we are rebuilding a home. When we recover from disaster, we are rebuilding lives and livelihoods.', 71491, 0), (494613, 'Of all the home remedies, a good wife is best.', 14120, 0), (494614, 'You can have more than one home. You can carry your roots with you, and decide where they grow.', 3753, 0), (494615, 'Child abuse and neglect offend the basic values of our state. We have a responsibility to provide safe settings for at-risk children and facilitate permanent placement for children who cannot return home.', 73325, 0), (494616, 'You spend your whole lifetime in your occupation, actually making life clever, easy and convenient for white people. But when you have to get transportation home, you are denied an equal accommodation. Our existence was for the white man''s comfort and well-being; we had to accept being deprived of just being human.', 19482, 0), (494617, 'But I do believe that a woman''s truest place is in a home, with a husband and with children, and with large freedom, pecuniary freedom, personal freedom, and the right to vote.', 63996, 0), (494618, 'Home is where you feel at home and are treated well.', 5025, 0), (494619, 'It''s 5 P.M. at the office. Working fast, you''ve finished your tasks for the day and want to go home. But none of your colleagues have left yet, so you stay another hour or two, surfing the Web and reading your e-mails again, so you don''t come off as a slacker. It''s an unfortunate reality that efficiency often goes unrewarded in the workplace.', 74246, 0), (494620, 'After a century of trying, we declared that healthcare in America is not a privilege for a few, it is a right for everybody. After decades of talk, we finally began to wean ourselves off foreign oil. We doubled our production of clean energy. We brought more of our troops home to their families, and we delivered justice to Osama bin Laden.', 1693, 0), (494621, 'You never know what events are going to transpire to get you home.', 1369, 0), (494622, 'There are only two things we should fight for. One is the defense of our homes and the other is the Bill of Rights.', 66579, 0), (494623, 'The prospect of going home is very appealing.', 75969, 0), (494624, 'The only foes that threaten America are the enemies at home, and these are ignorance, superstition and incompetence.', 4, 0), (494625, 'I don''t think I''m a workaholic. Every weekend, I invite my colleagues and friends to my home to play cards. And people, my neighbors, are always surprised because I live on the second floor apartment, and there are usually 40 pairs of shoes in front of my gate, and people play cards inside and play chess. We have a lot of fun.', 66598, 0), (494626, 'It is often easier to become outraged by injustice half a world away than by oppression and discrimination half a block from home.', 10272, 0), (494627, 'I believe in exploration, and I will miss being on the front lines of that endeavor. On one hand, I look forward to going home, but it''s something that''s been a big part of my life, and I''m going to miss it.', 51306, 0), (494628, 'Home is any four walls that enclose the right person.', 2362, 0), (494629, 'Life doesn''t get more real than having a newborn at home.', 60213, 0), (494630, 'After a really hectic week, I hate going out on a Friday evening, so I''ll always opt for a night at home.', 76018, 0), (494631, 'My dinners at home are startlingly simple. Every night, I stop at the market near my hotel and pick up a steak, lamb chops or some liver, which I broil in the electric oven in my room. I usually eat four or five raw carrots with my meat, and that is all. I must be part rabbit; I never get bored with raw carrots.', 1, 0), (494632, 'After I hit a home run I had a habit of running the bases with my head down. I figured the pitcher already felt bad enough without me showing him up rounding the bases.', 51167, 0), (494633, 'The perfect date for me would be staying at home, making a big picnic in bed, eating Wotsits and cookies while watching cable TV.', 34530, 0), (494634, 'For humans, the Arctic is a harshly inhospitable place, but the conditions there are precisely what polar bears require to survive - and thrive. ''Harsh'' to us is ''home'' for them. Take away the ice and snow, increase the temperature by even a little, and the realm that makes their lives possible literally melts away.', 67053, 0), (494635, 'I like to feel the butterflies in the stomach, I like to go home and have a restless night and wonder how I''m going to be able to accomplish this feat, get jittery. That hunger and those butterflies in the stomach are very essential for all creative people.', 68907, 0), (494636, 'We need to have a strong economy that can create employment opportunities and that can also produce the revenue that we need to defend our country at home and abroad.', 72232, 0), (494637, 'Breathe in deeply to bring your mind home to your body. Then look at, or think of, the person triggering this emotion: With mindfulness, you can see that she is unhappy, that she is suffering. You can see her wrong perceptions. You can see that she is not beautiful when she says things that are unkind.', 394, 0), (494638, 'Your best T-shirt should be like your bed it just feels like you are home when you are in it. ', 20099, 0), (494639, 'Theatre was my first love. I can''t take the theatre out of me. And I wouldn''t want to. To me, it''s home.', 71316, 0), (494640, 'We need sex education in schools, but we need it at home first. We need parents to learn the names of the teachers who are teaching their children. We need families to question day-care centers, to question other children and their own as to what goes on.', 8750, 0), (494641, 'I''m a very private person. I like staying home and doing my stuff. I hate people invading on my privacy. I hate talking about my private life.', 47135, 0), (494642, 'One never reaches home, but wherever friendly paths intersect the whole world looks like home for a time.', 305, 0), (494643, 'A girl phoned me the other day and said... ''Come on over, there''s nobody home.'' I went over. Nobody was home.', 2242, 0), (494644, 'Charity begins at home, but should not end there.', 1348, 0), (494645, 'Hypocrites in the Church? Yes, and in the lodge and at the home. Don''t hunt through the Church for a hypocrite. Go home and look in the mirror. Hypocrites? Yes. See that you make the number one less.', 2172, 0), (494646, 'Africa for the Africans... at home and abroad!', 1353, 0), (494647, 'All I did was pray to God, every day. In prison camp, the main prayer was, ''Get me home alive, God, and I''ll seek you and serve you.'' I came home, got wrapped up in the celebration, and forgot about the hundreds of promises I''d made to God.', 3981, 0), (494648, 'The lonely wanderer, who watches by the seashore the waves that roll between him and his home, talks of cruel facts, material barriers that, just because they are material, and not ideal, shall be the irresistible foes of his longing heart.', 62954, 0), (494649, 'There is one timeless way of building. It is a thousand years old, and the same today as it has ever been. The great traditional buildings of the past, the villages and tents and temples in which man feels at home, have always been made by people who were very close to the center of this way.', 72320, 0), (494650, 'Home is where you are appreciated, safe and protected, creative, and where you are loved - not where you are put in prison.', 8072, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (494651, 'I love my family, my wife, my kids, my dogs, my home, my life. I am a very happy and contented man.', 1287, 0), (494652, 'Children used to get bullied at school. Now they go home, and that''s where the problem starts - because they sit on their phones all night, thinking about who''s ''liked'' a photo of them, who hates them, who loves them. They don''t know what''s real and what''s not, editing their lives constantly to fit other people''s views.', 23445, 0), (494653, 'I tend to be so lost in the work that I don''t notice the weather. My partner will come home and say, ''Beautiful day, wasn''t it?'' and I''ll say, ''Was it?'' as I won''t have noticed the real world at all.', 1308, 0), (494654, 'It''s more pressure on women to - if they marry or partner with someone, to partner with the right person. Because you cannot have a full career and a full life at home with your children if you are also doing all of the housework and child care.', 1770, 0), (494655, 'I''m really quite simple. I plant flowers and watch them grow... I stay at home and watch the river flow.', 987, 0), (494656, 'I remembered some people who lived across the street from our home as we were being taken away. When I was a teenager, I had many after-dinner conversations with my father about our internment. He told me that after we were taken away, they came to our house and took everything. We were literally stripped clean.', 45192, 0), (494657, 'The killer app that got the world ready for appliances was the light bulb. So the light bulb is what wired the world. And they weren''t thinking about appliances when they wired the world. They were really thinking about - they weren''t putting electricity into the home. They were putting lighting into the home.', 22320, 0), (494658, 'We love our planet Earth. We should - it is our home, and there''s no place like home. There can''t ever be a better place than Earth.', 69981, 0), (494659, 'We are living in very challenging times. Pressured in the workplace and stressed out at home, people are trying to make sense of their lives.', 1873, 0), (494660, 'I just like sitting at home, chilling and watching a movie.', 387, 0), (494661, 'Let architects sing of aesthetics that bring Rich clients in hordes to their knees; Just give me a home, in a great circle dome Where stresses and strains are at ease.', 11496, 0), (494662, 'The instruction we find in books is like fire. We fetch it from our neighbours, kindle it at home, communicate it to others, and it becomes the property of all.', 808, 0), (494663, 'I think the great thing about grandparents is seeing another home, realising that people you love can have different priorities, different diversions, different opinions and lead quite different lives from the ones you see every day, and that is immensely valuable.', 62731, 0), (494664, 'Sometimes I can''t think of a better way to end my day than coming home and just strumming my ukulele for a few minutes. I mean, I joke around and tell people that it''s an entire yoga session in one strum, you know?', 71108, 0), (494665, 'I told my mother-in-law that my house was her house, and she said, ''Get the hell off my property.''', 17330, 0), (494666, 'Whether rich or poor, a home is not a home unless the roots of love are ever striking deeper through the crust of the earthly and the conventional, into the very realities of being, not consciously always; seldom, perhaps; the simplicity of loving grows by living simply near nature and God.', 7253, 0), (494667, 'You don''t have to swing hard to hit a home run. If you got the timing, it''ll go.', 1896, 0), (494668, 'Everybody thinks I''m, like, a bad boy. I''ve had my day, but I just sit at home and play the blues mostly.', 76019, 0), (494669, 'You can fool people. You can fool anybody anytime of the day, but you can''t fool yourself. At night, when you go home, you''ve got to be straight up with you.', 15469, 0), (494670, 'Whether at work, at home or in public, we have been trained to believe that who we are at the core of our being is often unacceptable. As a result, we work diligently to live up to - and sometimes down to - what others have made us out to be, whether or not it is an accurate reflection of who we are.', 634, 0), (494671, 'I''m one of the most adaptable guys I know in as much as travelling is my favourite thing to do in life. With every place I go, I try to stay there long enough to do it justice, long enough so that I can at least imagine what it would be like to live there. Once I imagine that, then it''s OK for me to return home.', 2387, 0), (494672, 'No matter what happens in a child''s home, no matter what other social and economic factors may impede a child, there''s no question in my mind that a first-rate school can transform almost everything.', 11500, 0), (494673, 'I am not Superwoman. The reality of my daily life is that I''m juggling a lot of balls in the air trying to be a good wife and mother, trying to be the prime-ministerial consort at home and abroad, barrister and charity worker, and sometimes one of the balls gets dropped.', 71511, 0), (494674, 'Somebody once asked me if I ever went up to the plate trying to hit a home run. I said, ''Sure, every time.''', 51167, 0), (494675, 'My wife met me at the door the other night in a sexy negligee. Unfortunately, she was just coming home.', 2242, 0), (494676, 'Oh, my ways are strange ways and new ways and old ways, And deep ways and steep ways and high ways and low, I''m at home and at ease on a track that I know not, And restless and lost on a road that I know.', 72509, 0), (494677, 'I''ve always looked for the perfect life to step into. I''ve taken all the paths to get where I wanted. But no matter where I go, I still come home.', 52964, 0), (494678, 'Home ownership is the cornerstone of a strong community.', 76020, 0), (494679, 'I watched Titanic when I got back home from the hospital, and cried. I knew that my IQ had been damaged.', 578, 0), (494680, 'It''s not about finding a home so much as finding yourself.', 75604, 0), (494681, 'New England is the home of all that is good and noble with all her sternness and uncompromising opinions.', 74224, 0), (494682, 'Price is rarely the most important thing. A cheap product might sell some units. Somebody gets it home and they feel great when they pay the money, but then they get it home and use it and the joy is gone.', 71501, 0), (494683, 'What I''ve learned in my life, it''s a very interesting social study for me, to go back and forth between being the guy at home and being the guy on the road and being the guy in studio and being the guy in the interview. The environment around you has so much to do with your character, and when I''m home, my character really changes quite a bit.', 861, 0), (494684, 'I''m a firm believer that lighting affects mood, and twinkly lights on strings bring something magical to occasions ranging from concerts to weddings, though I''m fond of using them as year-round home decor. There''s a reason why they''re sometimes called fairy lights. When the night is right, there aren''t any strings at all.', 520, 0), (494685, 'Most people know that forests are the lungs of our planet, literally playing a critical role in every breath we take. And that they''re also home to incredible animals like the orangutan and elephant, which will go extinct if we keep cutting down their forests.', 72207, 0), (494686, 'I am alone a lot, which is good. I need that time to just be alone after a long day, just decompress. So, I go to either my house or the hotel, or my apartment, or whatever - wherever I am, I go home and I watch TV and I sit there, with my cat, and I just watch TV or go online, check my emails.', 100, 0), (494687, 'Think you''re escaping and run into yourself. Longest way round is the shortest way home.', 265, 0), (494688, 'If your neighbors think you''re a detective because a cop always brings you home, you might be a redneck.', 1491, 0), (494689, 'An oligarchy of race, where the Saxon rules the African, might be endured; but this oligarchy of sex which makes father, brothers, husband, sons, the oligarchs over the mother and sisters, the wife and daughters of every household... carries discord and rebellion into every home of the nation.', 2137, 0), (494690, 'I hate leaving home. I love what I do, but I''d love to go home every night.', 76021, 0), (494691, 'In my own home, where I''ve been able to create an environment that works for me, I''m hardly disabled at all. I still have an impairment, and there are obviously some very restrictive things about that, but the impact of disability is less.', 67675, 0), (494692, 'Delhi is my emotional home. I still dream of owning a home there.', 72693, 0), (494693, 'I daresay one good concert justifies a week of satisfaction at home.', 22771, 0), (494694, 'A well-designed home has to be very comfortable. I can''t stand the aesthetes, the minimal thing. I can''t live that way. My home has to be filled with stuff - mostly paintings, sculpture, my fish lamps, cardboard furniture, lots of books.', 67568, 0), (494695, 'My kids are just waiting for me at home. I''m their father. They''re wondering, ''When''s Daddy coming home?''', 2614, 0), (494696, 'I''m still living the life where you get home and open the fridge and there''s half a pot of yogurt and a half a can of flat Coca-Cola.', 11118, 0), (494697, 'Home is one''s birthplace, ratified by memory.', 76022, 0), (494698, 'Palestine is our unforgettable historic home. The very name would be a force of marvelous potency for summoning our people together.', 17762, 0), (494699, 'Going home helps the content.', 23049, 0), (494700, 'I have no idea how to get in touch with anyone anymore. Everyone, it seems, has a home phone, a cell phone, a regular e-mail account, a Facebook account, a Twitter account, and a Web site. Some of them also have a Google Voice number. There are the sentimental few who still have fax machines.', 38818, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (494701, 'I love traveling all over the world but it''s true: there''s nothing like home. ', 1300, 0), (494702, 'Anytime you''re in West Virginia or near it, and you sing, ''Take Me Home, Country Roads,'' it''s a sight to behold.', 34097, 0), (494703, 'I just owe almost everything to my father and it''s passionately interesting for me that the things that I learned in a small town, in a very modest home, are just the things that I believe have won the election.', 1945, 0), (494704, 'The coolest thing, and I have it at home, is a huge Hulk Hogan, normal-sized pinball machine. When people come over they play it for hours. When you hit the bumpers and the bells ring it goes, ''Oh yeah!'' The whole time you''re playing this machine it''s yelling and screaming at you, ''What you gonna do, brother?!'' I think that''s the coolest.', 66791, 0), (494705, 'Often I have heard the taunt that suffragists are women who have failed to find any normal outlet for their emotions, and are therefore soured and disappointed beings. This is probably not true of any suffragist, and it is most certainly not true of me. My home life and relations have been as nearly ideal as possible in this imperfect world.', 16347, 0), (494706, 'You create a world away from home and make new rooms for yourself. But when you arrive back home in your old rooms, the world you''ve made for yourself ceases to be real. Everything seems to crumble. Anyone who''s been sent away to boarding school can understand that.', 27793, 0), (494707, 'Be nice to your children. After all, they are going to choose your nursing home.', 922, 0), (494708, 'Decorate your home. It gives the illusion that your life is more interesting than it really is.', 151, 0), (494709, 'The home should be the treasure chest of living.', 60507, 0), (494710, 'Any woman who understands the problems of running a home will be nearer to understanding the problems of running a country.', 1945, 0), (494711, 'God is at home, it''s we who have gone out for a walk.', 418, 0), (494712, 'When you finally go back to your old home, you find it wasn''t the old home you missed but your childhood.', 52193, 0), (494713, 'Home life ceases to be free and beautiful as soon as it is founded on borrowing and debt.', 845, 0), (494714, 'A man''s home is his wife''s castle.', 58721, 0), (494715, 'I''m lucky because I have a job I love. I really miss being away from home, being in my own bed, seeing my animals and siblings, having my moms cookies. I have a couple cats. I got a kitten about a year ago and now Im going on the road so I wont see him for a while. I feel bad.', 71599, 0), (494716, 'Owning a home is a keystone of wealth - both financial affluence and emotional security.', 10090, 0), (494717, 'As much as I would love to be a person that goes to parties and has a couple of drinks and has a nice time, that doesn''t work for me. I''d just rather sit at home and read, or go out to dinner with someone, or talk to someone I love, or talk to somebody that makes me laugh.', 1593, 0), (494718, 'Any old place I can hang my hat is home sweet home to me.', 76023, 0), (494719, 'A man''s house is his castle.', 16822, 0), (494720, 'We share one heart, one home, and one glorious destiny.', 64643, 0), (494721, 'Take, for example, the African jungle, the home of the cheetah. On whom does the cheetah prey? The old, the sick, the wounded, the weak, the very young, but never the strong. Lesson: If you would not be prey, you had better be strong.', 73110, 0), (494722, 'Canada will be a strong country when Canadians of all provinces feel at home in all parts of the country, and when they feel that all Canada belongs to them.', 17477, 0), (494723, 'I love being at home and cooking and baking.', 38496, 0), (494724, 'I''m just a normal person. It''s not like I come home and think about opera. My thoughts are about completely other things. Shoes! Dresses! Expensive ones: with a pretty silhouette, beautiful fabrics.', 71090, 0), (494725, 'When I was 10 years old, I loved - I loved books, and I used to haunt the secondhand bookshop. And I found a little book I could just afford, and I bought it, and I took it home. And I climbed up my favorite tree, and I read that book from cover to cover. And that was Tarzan of the Apes. I immediately fell in love with Tarzan.', 2086, 0), (494726, 'When memories fade, can one ever really return home?', 76024, 0), (494727, 'There are trees of a thousand sorts, and all have their several fruits; and I feel the most unhappy man in the world not to know them, for I am well assured that they are all valuable. I bring home specimens of them, and also of the land.', 70809, 0), (494728, 'If they had a social gospel in the days of the prodigal son, somebody would have given him a bed and a sandwich and he never would have gone home.', 1887, 0), (494729, 'If I was a book, I would like to be a library book, so I would be taken home by all different sorts of kids.', 786, 0), (494730, 'I chose America as my home because I value freedom and democracy, civil liberties and an open society.', 2935, 0), (494731, 'And, you know, being able to wear the stars and stripes, when you step up on one of the blocks or, you know, when you step off of an airplane or when you hear the national anthem play, you know, it''s one of the greatest feelings in the world because you know that there are people at home who are supporting you and watching you.', 30837, 0), (494732, 'There''s a lot more responsibility at home, so a tour is like the opposite for me. It''s like a breath of fresh air.', 71042, 0), (494733, 'When I was a child and they burned me out of my home, I was frightened and I ran away. Eventually I ran far away. It was to a place called France. Many of you have been there, and many have not. But I must tell you, ladies and gentlemen, in that country I never feared. It was like a fairyland place.', 52279, 0), (494734, 'I wanted to write something in a voice that was unique to who I was. And I wanted something that was accessible to the person who works at Dunkin Donuts or who drives a bus, someone who comes home with their feet hurting like my father, someone who''s busy and has too many children, like my mother.', 26083, 0), (494735, 'If we could make our house a home, and then make it a sanctuary, I think we could truly find paradise on Earth.', 30188, 0), (494736, 'I really enjoy spending time at home.', 76025, 0), (494737, 'I love modeling because I get to see everything that inspires me. Then I go home and sketch.', 69311, 0), (494738, 'I had a lot of dates but I decided to stay home and dye my eyebrows.', 321, 0), (494739, 'I have Social Disease. I have to go out every night. If I stay home one night I start spreading rumors to my dogs.', 321, 0), (494740, 'Most of American life consists of driving somewhere and then returning home, wondering why the hell you went.', 135, 0), (494741, 'The people recognize themselves in their commodities; they find their soul in their automobile, hi-fi set, split-level home, kitchen equipment.', 2718, 0), (494742, 'Everywhere you hang your hat is home. Home is the bright cave under the hat.', 16699, 0), (494743, 'Travelling''s so much better when you know you''ve got a lovely home to go back to.', 69083, 0), (494744, 'What I have always liked about Brighton is its impersonality. Since the 18th century, people have come, used the place and gone home again.', 8247, 0), (494745, 'I can''t tell you how many times I''ve gone to present at the Golden Globes, come home, whipped the dress off and read to my daughter wearing gazillion-dollar earrings. That''s how it goes in my house, and I wouldn''t have it any other way.', 68486, 0), (494746, 'The idea of prosthetics is a tool. Most people''s cell phones are prosthetics. If you leave your cell phone at home, you feel impacted by not having it. It''s an important part of your daily function and what you can do in a day.', 71813, 0), (494747, 'What makes me really happy is a walk in the English countryside. A nice sunset, that British countryside - it means I''m home.', 69331, 0), (494748, 'The whole idea is you can''t sit around and do nothing. You have to get up and start living one day at a time. That''s what I did my entire career. You can''t sit around and say, ''Oh, poor me. Nobody likes me. Nobody is giving me a job.'' You have to get up and go. If you sit at home and do nothing, that is what is going to happen.', 68221, 0), (494749, 'We turned the switch, saw the flashes, watched for ten minutes, then switched everything off and went home. That night I knew the world was headed for sorrow.', 48375, 0), (494750, 'Reading isn''t good for a ballplayer. Not good for his eyes. If my eyes went bad even a little bit I couldn''t hit home runs. So I gave up reading.', 2470, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (494751, 'Just take the ball and throw it where you want to. Throw strikes. Home plate don''t move.', 5228, 0), (494752, 'The means of defense against foreign danger historically have become the instruments of tyranny at home.', 2514, 0), (494753, 'We have weapons of mass destruction we have to address here at home. Poverty is a weapon of mass destruction. Homelessness is a weapon of mass destruction. Unemployment is a weapon of mass destruction.', 16105, 0), (494754, 'Analogies, it is true, decide nothing, but they can make one feel more at home.', 555, 0), (494755, 'It is better for a woman to compete impersonally in society, as men do, than to compete for dominance in her own home with her husband, compete with her neighbors for empty status, and so smother her son that he cannot compete at all.', 1773, 0), (494756, 'Words today are like the shells and rope of seaweed which a child brings home glistening from the beach and which in an hour have lost their luster.', 9518, 0), (494757, 'Firefighters are indispensable foot soldiers here at home.', 72725, 0), (494758, 'The juvenile sea squirt wanders through the sea searching for a suitable rock or hunk of coral to cling to and make its home for life. For this task, it has a rudimentary nervous system. When it finds its spot and takes root, it doesn''t need its brain anymore so it eats it!', 38978, 0), (494759, 'I''ll fill those canyons in your soul, like a river lead you home. And I''ll walk a step behind, in the shadows so you shine. Just ask, it will be done and I will prove my love, until you''re sure that I''m the one.', 70210, 0), (494760, 'Once you''re halfway home, you know that you can probably get the rest of the way there.', 37623, 0), (494761, 'Last winter when I was coming home from church one Thursday evening, I saw somebody run around the house again. I told my father of that.', 76026, 0), (494762, 'I was married to Margaret Joan Howe in 1940. Although not a scientist herself she has contributed more to my work than anyone else by providing a peaceful and happy home.', 60557, 0), (494763, 'Like after a nice walk when you have seen many lovely sights you decide to go home, after a while I decided it was time to go home, let us put the cubes back in order. And it was at that moment that I came face to face with the Big Challenge: What is the way home?', 69550, 0), (494764, 'You can''t do some of the things you used to do. I suppose you have to go at a gentler pace. I mean, God help us, you can''t sit at home being a Vicar or anything.', 76027, 0), (494765, 'But inspiration? - That''s when you come home from abroad and are asked: Well, have you found inspiration? - and fortunately you haven''t. But the impressions sink in, of course, and may emerge later: None of us has invented the house; that was done many thousands of years ago.', 72348, 0), (494766, 'Also, I walk and hike in several different nearby parks near our home several early mornings a week.', 65322, 0), (494767, 'I came into the game when I broke into the major leagues, the minimum salary was seven thousand dollars, and I''d have to go home in the wintertime and get a job.', 69692, 0), (494768, 'But if there''s an erosion at home, you know, Thomas Jefferson warned about a tyranny of an oligarchy and if we surrender our democracy to the tyranny of an oligarchy, we''ve made a terrible mistake.', 72469, 0), (494769, 'You come home, and you party. But after that, you get a hangover. Everything about that is negative.', 11133, 0), (494770, 'If an ass goes travelling he will not come home a horse.', 1348, 0), (494771, 'I never worry about being driven to drink I just worry about being driven home. ', 2165, 0), (494772, 'I''m no hero. Heroes don''t come back. Survivors return home. Heroes never come home. If anyone thinks I''m a hero, I''m not.', 20783, 0), (494773, 'If it''s far away, it''s news, but if it''s close at home, it''s sociology.', 63554, 0), (494774, 'One small cat changes coming home to an empty house to coming home.', 15447, 0), (494775, 'We all have times when we go home at night and pull out our hair and feel misunderstood and lonely and like we''re falling. I think the brain is such that there is always going to be something missing.', 70651, 0), (494776, 'I want to say a very sincere thank you for this welcome home - it is a wonderful welcome home. It is the place to where I return and where I will always return because it is of Galway that I am.', 67754, 0), (494777, 'Sometimes in the past when I played something might make me lose focus, or I would go home after a game where I thought I could have played better and I would let it hang over my head for a long time when it shouldn''t.', 11158, 0), (494778, 'In an ideal world, I''d spend every weekend at my home in Zermatt in Switzerland.', 75028, 0), (494779, 'I know people that could serve me canned tuna and saltine crackers and have me feel more at home at their table than some people who can cook circles around me. The more you try to impress people, generally the less you do.', 32294, 0), (494780, 'I''m always going to live in Texas. Texas is my home - it''ll be my home forever.', 9111, 0), (494781, 'I like being married. I''m at home with my wife and kids all the time now. I don''t go out for wild nights.', 57301, 0), (494782, 'As we try to compete in this global marketplace, we need to rebuild our infrastructure. We need to rebuild our schools. We need to make sure that teachers and first responders and veterans who are coming home from serving our country so proudly have jobs waiting for them.', 25710, 0), (494783, 'There is only one home to the life of a river-mussel; there is only one home to the life of a tortoise; there is only one shell to the soul of man: there is only one world to the spirit of our race. If that world leaves its course and smashes on boulders of the great void, whose world will give us shelter?', 6613, 0), (494784, 'Mr. Bean is at his best when he is not using words, but I am equally at home in both verbal and nonverbal expression.', 16706, 0), (494785, 'I think what is British about me is my feelings and awareness of others and their situations. English people are always known to be well mannered and cold but we are not cold - we don''t interfere in your situation. If we are heartbroken, we don''t scream in your face with tears - we go home and cry on our own.', 40738, 0), (494786, 'It''s easy to underestimate the real cost of home ownership.', 10090, 0), (494787, 'It''s not like I''m this glamour diva who hands everything over and I just sit on my throne at home.', 69264, 0), (494788, 'I actually haven''t been on many dates, but I like just chilling around at home and watching a movie with a girl.', 387, 0), (494789, 'I like my home and I like the nature.', 4019, 0), (494790, 'I don''t really remember the day we lost our home in the floods, but looking back I can understand how devastating it was for my parents. I was only six, so I remember us having to move to Adelaide - but not much of the actual day and night of the flood. We had to start all over again and my parents opened a cafe.', 70239, 0), (494791, 'I''m lucky my wife is a strong woman. She''s one of the stronger people I''ve ever met. It''s hard for me to be away, but I know my home life is fine because my wife is there.', 69332, 0), (494792, 'Sometimes when I get home after a long day, I''ll turn on music - I love Latin, disco, and pop - and do my own workout, even if it''s a short one. Know a good song to work out to? ''I Will Survive.''', 71164, 0), (494793, 'The world is my workshop. It is not my home.', 21523, 0), (494794, 'Our culture does not teach us this, but what happens in Vegas does not stay in Vegas. If you cheat in Vegas, it comes right home with you. If you cheat in Vegas, you walk home as a cheater. You lie awake at a night a cheater. You cannot escape it.', 70928, 0), (494795, 'The hardest thing about being a full time chef is leaving my work behind when I go home at night. I''ll toss and turn about a menu item or forget to order produce and wake up at 4 A.M. in a cold sweat over some artichokes.', 70438, 0), (494796, 'While I encourage people to save 100% down for a home, a mortgage is the one debt that I don''t frown upon.', 5846, 0), (494797, 'Long weekends at festivals, short weeks at home, all summer long: now that is surely preferable to the immense cost and headache of the nuclear family holiday in the sun?', 16461, 0), (494798, 'I can understand why a single parent, working two jobs, would find it easier to stop at McDonald''s with the kids rather than cook something from scratch at home.', 21365, 0), (494799, 'It''s impossible to change the social without changing the personal - you have to put your money where your mouth is. And if you''re not making those challenges at home, it''s unlikely you''ll make them in a larger setting.', 50218, 0), (494800, 'One of the things which make any company successful, in particular the Home Depot, was that we understood and catered to the customer. If it didn''t sell, it didn''t make a difference what we thought or our research told us. They told us if it was successful by buying it or not.', 76028, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (494801, 'In my songs, I''m not saying something that''s never been said before. The have lyrics aren''t going to blow people away. It''s the emotion and the melody that drive it home.', 22720, 0), (494802, 'If I''m in work mode and going to meetings, I''ll make an effort and dress up, but when I''m at home or just chilling, I''m in beanies and jeans and sneakers.', 75308, 0), (494803, 'Guns go home with the soldiers, but landmines are designed to kill - mindlessly, out of control, for years.', 76029, 0), (494804, 'I don''t think about tennis 24/7. I enjoy time on the lake at my Florida home and just being lazy on the sofa.', 67530, 0), (494805, 'There is a strong side to me, that is of a homemaker. I look forward to spending time at home in the evenings, cooking a meal, chatting with my parents and inviting friends over.', 69743, 0), (494806, 'When I get home, I''m not the boss like I am at work - I slip into a more feminine role. I take everything off and put on my Stella McCartney silk robe. I''ll put on a red lip or red nails, and it lifts my mood. Sexy underwear also gives you a spark.', 18360, 0), (494807, 'At home in Ghaziabad, everyone is a pure vegetarian. In fact, when I want to cook non-veg there, my mum shoos me out on the terrace where I have my cooking utensils. I''m told categorically that whatever non-veg or egg, etc., that I have to cook, I should do upstairs and not enter her kitchen at all.', 67900, 0), (494808, 'It''s particularly hard to take being stabbed in the back close to home. There''s always a feeling of betrayal when people of your own group oppose you.', 28396, 0), (494809, '''Grandmother'' doesn''t mean that you have gray hair and you retire and stay home cooking cakes for your grandchildren.', 67000, 0), (494810, 'Housework is what a woman does that nobody notices unless she hasn''t done it.', 18694, 0), (494811, 'We live in downtown Manhattan and we have pretty big windows that looked right at the World Trade Center. I was home along with Kai and we watched it all happen. I was holding him in my arms and we were looking out the window when the second plane hit.', 76030, 0), (494812, 'I just moved into a new house, so I love spending time at home. Everything for me is all about self-care because I really feel that if I''m at my best, than I''m able to come to my job and really be feeling the best, so if I''m not working out or going on a hike, than I''m at home recharging and cooking dinner and hanging out with my cat.', 10135, 0), (494813, 'I always feel that when I come to Edinburgh, in many ways I am coming home.', 11118, 0), (494814, 'Home life''s great, man. The kids are great, happy and healthy. I''ve reached this sort of wonderful precipice.', 69152, 0), (494815, 'All I do is sit at home and watch Netflix.', 67660, 0), (494816, 'Baseball is like driving, it''s the one who gets home safely that counts.', 5198, 0), (494817, 'Your home is regarded as a model home, your life as a model life. But all this splendor, and you along with it... it''s just as though it were built upon a shifting quagmire. A moment may come, a word can be spoken, and both you and all this splendor will collapse.', 845, 0), (494818, 'I had only one superstition. I made sure to touch all the bases when I hit a home run.', 2470, 0), (494819, 'All good hotels tend to lead people to do things they wouldn''t necessarily do at home.', 72661, 0), (494820, 'The Westwood Cemetery is just a few blocks from my home, and a number of my very dear friends are buried there.', 38121, 0), (494821, 'On stage I make love to twenty five thousand people and then I go home alone. ', 12453, 0), (494822, 'Survival requires us to leave our prejudices at home. It''s about doing whatever it takes - and ultimately those with the biggest heart will win.', 9272, 0), (494823, 'A guy wants a classy girl who is smart and has goals - someone that he wouldn''t be afraid to bring home to his parents.', 16615, 0), (494824, 'Why would I retire? Sit at home and watch TV? No thanks. I''d rather be out playing.', 67, 0), (494825, 'The physician can bury his mistakes, but the architect can only advise his client to plant vines - so they should go as far as possible from home to build their first buildings.', 1836, 0), (494826, 'Going home must be like going to render an account.', 1241, 0), (494827, 'It was a show that you played at home and you''re saying to the contestant do this and do that. When you at home are involved in yelling at the screen, then you know you''ve got an audience.', 11250, 0), (494828, 'An artist has no home in Europe except in Paris.', 11, 0), (494829, 'If your parent is deployed and you are that young, you spend the whole time wondering where they are and waiting for them to come home. As time passes and the absence is longer and longer, you become more and more concerned - but you don''t really have the words to express your concern. There''s only this continued absence.', 18, 0), (494830, 'When you live far away, home looks a little different every time.', 76031, 0), (494831, 'I never learned hate at home, or shame. I had to go to school for that.', 39403, 0), (494832, 'The one thing that offends me the most is when I walk by a bank and see ads trying to convince people to take out second mortgages on their home so they can go on vacation. That''s approaching evil.', 22320, 0), (494833, 'When it was suggested that I write a memoir I said, ''I''m not old enough. I''m not distinguished enough.'' But I went home and sat down to write, and the material for the book just came flooding into my hands.', 3977, 0), (494834, 'I read the Odyssey because it was the story of a man who returned home after being absent for more than twenty years and was recognized only by his dog.', 40284, 0), (494835, 'I wish I could go home. I''ve been on the road since May. I wonder if my dogs still remember me.', 76032, 0), (494836, 'Potential home buyers have a two-step decision process. First, they determine whether they can afford to make a purchase - does their income safely cover their mortgage payment? Then they determine whether owning is a better financial choice than renting - are the costs of owning a home lower than the cost of renting it?', 71046, 0), (494837, 'Push-ups are seriously the best way to tone your arms - and they tone your abs at the same time! I like to do them when I''m home watching TV or listening to music.', 76033, 0), (494838, 'I consider myself a product of Alaska. The love and the debt that I feel to my home state, you always want your hometown to be the proudest of you.', 7655, 0), (494839, 'What motivates me is seeing people in the crowd and wondering what they''re going home to and what they''re dealing with, and knowing that for the time being we''re their escape.', 1029, 0), (494840, 'At home, I love reaching out into that absolute silence, when you can hear the owl or the wind.', 76034, 0), (494841, 'I''m very political. I''m not political in public I''m political at home. ', 67092, 0), (494842, 'Censorship, like charity, should begin at home, but, unlike charity, it should end there.', 21495, 0), (494843, 'Iowa is home to teachers, farmers, lawyers, factory workers, and many others who work hard every day to provide the best for their families and their future.', 71530, 0), (494844, 'Leaving home in a sense involves a kind of second birth in which we give birth to ourselves.', 76035, 0), (494845, 'I go home and stay there. I wash and scrub up each day, and that''s it. One month I actually grew a moustache, just so I could say that I''d done something.', 31358, 0), (494846, 'Building a proper wardrobe is like building a home. Indeed, you should think of it like a home, because it is something you''re going to live in. It must be comfortable and suit all your needs.', 72836, 0), (494847, 'At home, when the heating pipes made noises, I imagined a tiny person was in there skipping with a rope. The fantasy world of tiny things became my escape.', 72571, 0), (494848, 'There''s just no place like Scotland when the sun is out. I just love coming home.', 70279, 0), (494849, 'Heavenly Father has assigned us to a great variety of stations to strengthen and, when needed, to lead travelers to safety. Our most important and powerful assignments are in the family. They are important because the family has the opportunity at the start of a child''s life to put feet firmly on the path home.', 9158, 0), (494850, 'Phil Niekro and his brother were pitching against each other in Atlanta. Their parents were sitting right behind home plate. I saw their folks more that day than they did the whole weekend.', 68496, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (494851, 'Social and digital media is a bullet train, and that bullet train is not coming home.', 19506, 0), (494852, 'The mare set off for home with the speed of a swallow, and going as smoothly and silently. I never had dreamed of such a motion, fluent and graceful, and ambient, soft as the breeze flitting over the flowers, but swift as the summer lightening.', 76036, 0), (494853, 'I am more valuable to my team hitting .330 then swinging for home runs.', 72845, 0), (494854, 'Homesickness is nothing. Fifty percent of the people in the world are homesick all the time.', 1717, 0), (494855, 'To the former child migrants, who came to Australia from a home far away, led to believe this land would be a new beginning, when only to find it was not a beginning, but an end, an end of innocence - we apologise and we are sorry. To the mothers who lost the maternal right to love and care for their child - we apologise, and we are sorry.', 72454, 0), (494856, 'So I''m more at home with my backpack, sleeping in a hotel room or on a bus or on an airplane, than I am necessarily on a bed. It''s weird being here. It feels like I''m standing next to my real life.', 68, 0), (494857, 'The way to work with a bully is to take the ball and go home. First time, every time. When there''s no ball, there''s no game. Bullies hate that. So they''ll either behave so they can play with you or they''ll go bully someone else.', 2113, 0), (494858, 'Doesn''t the world see the suffering of millions of Palestinians who have been living in exile around the world or in refugee camps for the past 60 years? No state, no home, no identity, no right to work. Doesn''t the world see this injustice?', 71335, 0), (494859, 'Everybody aspires to an affordable home, a secure job, better living standards, reliable healthcare and a decent pension. My generation took those things for granted, and so should future generations.', 50602, 0), (494860, 'Coming home, we stopped for a bite to eat and ran into a confused waitress. Had a heart-rending time trying to speak the Words of Life to her, and as I think of all this country now, many just as confused, and more so, I realized that the 39th Street bus is as much a mission field as Africa ever was.', 1892, 0), (494861, 'My only concern was to get home after a hard day''s work.', 19482, 0), (494862, 'There is no sanctuary of virtue like home.', 73052, 0), (494863, 'If you want to be certain, you should never get married. You should never change jobs. In fact, you might as well just stay home. Because I don''t know anybody who is certain. That need to be certain is just procrastination.', 10164, 0), (494864, 'If one more ''journalist'' makes a cavalier statement about me and my band, I will personally or with my fans'' help, greet them at their home and discover just how much they believe in their freedom of speech.', 2519, 0), (494865, 'My idea of heaven used to be relaxing at home with a cheese plate and champagne.', 10135, 0), (494866, 'My first job was in a nursing home - a terrible place in retrospect. It was in an old house, and the residents were so lonely. People rarely visited them. I only stayed there a couple of months, but it made a strong impression on me.', 8033, 0), (494867, 'Fresh out of college, you tend to join a company because it''s a job. But, you tend to stay because it becomes a career; you start to feel at home. In the beginning of your career, you''re focused on you: ''I like this place because I''m doing rewarding work; they take good care of me; the people are nice; there''s runway for me,'' etc.', 66621, 0), (494868, 'I was teased if I brought my books home. I would take a paper bag to the library and put the books in the bag and bring them home. Not that I was that concerned about them teasing me - because I would hit them in a heartbeat. But I felt a little ashamed, having books.', 11749, 0), (494869, 'At home, we live on the beach, and it''s like every day is a date.', 74529, 0), (494870, 'It''s a miracle was the last track recorded for the album, we based it on the rhythm from the middle of ''Late Home Tonight, where there''s Graham Broad playing lots and lots of drums with me shouting in the background, pretending to be a mad Arab leader.', 16030, 0), (494871, 'If you reject the food, ignore the customs, fear the religion and avoid the people, you might better stay at home.', 2239, 0), (494872, 'One of the oldest human needs is having someone to wonder where you are when you don''t come home at night.', 992, 0), (494873, 'A house that does not have one warm, comfy chair in it is soulless.', 996, 0), (494874, 'When everyone goes home, you''re stuck with yourself.', 52964, 0), (494875, 'When the soldiers came home from Vietnam, there were no parades, no celebrations. So they built the Vietnam Memorial for themselves.', 68692, 0), (494876, 'When our thousands of Chinese students abroad return home, you will see how China will transform itself.', 51676, 0), (494877, 'I''m not going to go run and hide because I''m catching some heat. I''m not going to stay at home and pout.', 67530, 0), (494878, 'Even today, you get criticized if you''re staying at home, because you''re not doing enough with your life, but you get criticized for being a career woman because you''re not raising your kids.', 76037, 0), (494879, 'I love to eat cucumber sticks with yogurt. It''s a great snack to have at home, especially when I''m having house guests.', 74901, 0), (494880, 'I do become a recluse once in a while. It''s so nice to just be at home and to not have to deal with the outside world.', 67014, 0), (494881, 'Basically, when I get home I just do emails for around three hours, which stinks. I have a thing about getting into your inbox every night before going to bed. I''m usually working from my laptop or my phone, desperately trying to get my inbox to zero before I fall asleep.', 26172, 0), (494882, 'I love Africa, and Ulusaba, our home in South Africa, is pretty special. It''s on a rocky hill overlooking the bush, and from your room, you can see lions stalking zebras by the waterhole.', 5248, 0), (494883, 'I couldn''t be where I am today if I had children. My focus would be on my children and home. And you can do it later in life.', 68280, 0), (494884, 'Journalism''s ultimate purpose is to inform the reader, to bring him each day a letter from home and never to permit the serving of special interests.', 73753, 0), (494885, 'When I hit a home run I usually didn''t care where it went. So long as it was a home run was all that mattered.', 51167, 0), (494886, 'There are things they tell us that sound good to hear, but when they have accomplished their purpose they will go home and will not try to fulfill our agreements with them.', 48992, 0), (494887, 'I keep my own personality in a cupboard under the stairs at home so that no one else can see it or nick it.', 18101, 0), (494888, 'More fundamentally, it is a dream that does not die with the onset of manhood: the dream is to play endlessly, past the time when you are called home for dinner, past the time of doing chores, past the time when your body betrays you past time itself.', 67466, 0), (494889, 'We should be the natural home for young mothers. But we''re not. Because too often we sound like people who think the only good mother is a married mother.', 76038, 0), (494890, 'Who says Australia offers not a home for every poor Englishman, or any other countryman that finds his way to our shores? And what sort of thanks do we get for it?', 72509, 0), (494891, 'I also believed that our public at home would be strong enough to survive even the present crisis.', 76039, 0), (494892, 'A man would prefer to come home to an unmade bed and a happy woman than to a neatly made bed and an angry woman.', 5858, 0), (494893, 'However painful the process of leaving home, for parents and for children, the really frightening thing for both would be the prospect of the child never leaving home.', 76035, 0), (494894, 'For more than four decades, the Libyan people have been ruled by a tyrant - Moammar Gaddafi. He has denied his people freedom, exploited their wealth, murdered opponents at home and abroad, and terrorized innocent people around the world - including Americans who were killed by Libyan agents.', 1693, 0), (494895, 'Ladies and gentlemen, god bless America - land of the free, home of the brave.', 22301, 0), (494896, 'We have the insight and the tools to identify and bring to fruition the dormant talent that our artists possess. Favored Nations will be branded as the home base for inspired musical talent.', 67083, 0), (494897, 'Buy with your heart, not your head. You can look at all the aspects that make a purchase practical, but that kind of thinking makes it an investment rather than a home.', 34972, 0), (494898, 'I do 280 episodes of TV a year, write 15 recipes for the magazine, and publish an annual book. With all of that, we try to get one weekend a month with Isaboo at our home in the Adirondacks to relax and recharge.', 68489, 0), (494899, 'I''m an afternoon tea type of girl. I come from a Russian background where we love our teas. So between lunch and dinner after training I come home and I love a nice cup of tea with jam in it, as we drink it there. Black English Breakfast with raspberry jam is my favorite.', 68355, 0), (494900, 'I''ve never been a hands-on dad. I''m not ashamed to admit it, but you can''t run a restaurant and be home for tea at 4:30 and bath and change nappies.', 49687, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (494901, 'Because I''m a chef, I eat out frequently, so it''s hard for me to control what I consume in terms of calories. But when I''m at home, I eat what my wife cooks for me. She works hard to avoid making foods that are high in calories and cholesterol, so most of the time, she makes vegetarian dishes.', 68182, 0), (494902, 'I didn''t have nothin'' going for me... school, home... until I found something I loved, which was music, and that changed everything.', 392, 0), (494903, 'When I started editing on my home computer, I said to myself, ''Well, I could be at home studying for a class or I could be at home editing a video.''', 12986, 0), (494904, 'Maybe I should just go home and ride my tractor.', 72545, 0), (494905, 'My real fantasy if I was to drop out would be to live in a mobile home and be a hippie and drive around festivals and have millions of children - children with dreadlocks and nose rings - and play the flute.', 70684, 0), (494906, 'It is easier to take a position in the abstract than when it hits home.', 4608, 0), (494907, 'We need to rediscover the idea of the common good and work together to build a home.', 4059, 0), (494908, 'Well, I''m not good with sliminess. I hate the thought of creatures that have slime on them or creatures that leave a slimy trail. At home, the sight of a slug can bring up my breakfast.', 71840, 0), (494909, 'My idea of home is not necessarily a place.', 76040, 0), (494910, 'For many years I enjoyed the pleasure of cruising on my yacht all summer long and these were my best holidays. In mid-May, we''d start in St Tropez. I''d collect my bikinis from my home there and then we''d go up to Cannes for the Film Festival, on to Monte Carlo for the Grand Prix and then to Italy.', 22364, 0), (494911, 'You start realizing that maybe you''re the one night a month that people have out, and they don''t need to hear your political views or how dark you can get. They just want to laugh for an hour and go home. Once I wrapped my head around that, my act evolved accordingly.', 67394, 0), (494912, 'Paris is beautiful, but nothing beats home.', 69788, 0), (494913, 'Gimmicks come and go the cop show seems one genre that will never leave - not as long as people like to sit at home in the suburbs and see what awful things go on in the cities. ', 68498, 0), (494914, 'Most of the time, people look at a piece of art online when it is just a few blocks from their house. Changing the way you walk home everyday fills life with surprises.', 74296, 0), (494915, 'My homies in Gadsden aren''t as exposed as I am culturally, which is awesome - that''s why I love going home. I''m in the kitchen with people who don''t know anything but the simple life, what''s important to them, and what''s dope.', 71722, 0), (494916, 'I have a home in Orlando. That''s kind of my default ''getaway'' city.', 75417, 0), (494917, 'All I ever want is to return to either Bangladesh, my motherland, or India, my adopted home.', 10634, 0), (494918, 'Armed with nothing more than a Facebook user''s phone number and home address, anyone with an Internet connection and a few dollars can obtain personal information they should never have access to, including a user''s date of birth, e-mail address, or estimated income.', 11414, 0), (494919, 'I came from a Halloween-friendly home. My dad, Spencer, was a U.S. Marine captain. But when it came to Halloween, my dad had a soft spot. He would take his three sons and friends on escapades on Halloween night.', 76041, 0), (494920, 'There is nothing more important than a good, safe, secure home.', 19480, 0), (494921, 'Well, because I''m naturally a tomboy, when I have sleepovers with girls, they end up going home and crying.', 71583, 0), (494922, 'It was very much like Norman Rockwell: small town America. We walked to school or rode our bikes, stopped at the penny candy store on the way home from school, skated on the pond.', 67384, 0), (494923, 'I still close my eyes and go home - I can always draw from that.', 1300, 0), (494924, 'One of the best things to come out of the home computer revolution could be the general and widespread understanding of how severely limited logic really is.', 1265, 0), (494925, 'I really like having a life outside work. I sometimes wish I did more career stuff and was in that Hollywood scene a bit more. But Toronto''s my home.', 60126, 0), (494926, 'I actually do think you''re seeing this trend towards organizations just caring more about their brand and engaging. And so I think Home Depot will want to humanize itself. I think that''s a lot of why companies are starting blogs, are just giving more insight into what''s going on with them.', 5553, 0), (494927, 'The aesthetic came along the way, I think - just through experimenting, and going on tour, and trying stuff out on stage, having fun with it, and not taking it too seriously. If I had a ballgown at home, I''d wear it onstage. If I found something in a charity shop, I''d wear it. That''s where it grew from - just wanting to play dress-up.', 22790, 0), (494928, 'I''m the type who''d be happy not going anywhere as long as I was sure I knew exactly what was happening at the places I wasn''t going to. I''m the type who''d like to sit home and watch every party that I''m invited to on a monitor in my bedroom.', 321, 0), (494929, 'The fellow that owns his own home is always just coming out of a hardware store.', 14120, 0), (494930, 'Kindness goes a long ways lots of times when it ought to stay at home.', 14120, 0), (494931, 'I kiss the soil as if I placed a kiss on the hands of a mother, for the homeland is our earthly mother. I consider it my duty to be with my compatriots in this sublime and difficult moment.', 66871, 0), (494932, 'To be happy at home is the ultimate result of all ambition, the end to which every enterprise and labor tends, and of which every desire prompts the prosecution.', 2087, 0), (494933, 'People who have good relationships at home are more effective in the marketplace.', 1692, 0), (494934, 'I am not quite sure where home is right now. I do have places in London and Milan, and a house in Spain. I guess I would say home is where my mother is, and she lives in Spain.', 38241, 0), (494935, 'There is something permanent, and something extremely profound, in owning a home.', 48627, 0), (494936, 'In the mind, in the heart, I was always home. I always imagined, really, going back home.', 64289, 0), (494937, 'A heart makes a good home for the friend.', 8849, 0), (494938, 'The house has to please everyone, contrary to the work of art which does not. The work is a private matter for the artist. The house is not.', 30052, 0), (494939, 'I''m going to buy some green bananas because by the time I get home they''ll be ripe.', 67187, 0), (494940, 'Our home had many books due principally to the educational interests of my sister and two brothers, all of whom where serious students engaged in professional studies; my sister became a doctor of medicine and my brothers became lawyers.', 70475, 0), (494941, 'I noted that people are happy here in India. When I went back home, people had everything in the materialistic sense and were surrounded with abundance, but they were not happy.', 1245, 0), (494942, 'The thing I like about baseball is that it''s one-on-one. You stand up there alone, and if you make a mistake, it''s your mistake. If you hit a home run, it''s your home run.', 59444, 0), (494943, 'This stammer got me a home in Beverly Hills, and I''m not about to screw with it now.', 51805, 0), (494944, 'As they marched, the crowds lining the route broke into applause, a sweet and deeply felt spontaneous pattering that was a sort of communal embrace. Welcome home.', 16699, 0), (494945, 'I have become a queer mixture of the East and the West, out of place everywhere, at home nowhere.', 8325, 0), (494946, 'Reading makes immigrants of us all. It takes us away from home, but more important, it finds homes for us everywhere.', 1268, 0), (494947, 'This will remain the land of the free only so long as it is the home of the brave.', 51187, 0), (494948, 'Managing is getting paid for home runs that someone else hits.', 63919, 0), (494949, 'I''m hoping someday that some kid, black or white, will hit more home runs than myself. Whoever it is, I''d be pulling for him.', 59444, 0), (494950, 'I loved to make a great defensive play, I''d rather do that than hit a home run.', 76042, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (494951, 'No one is worthy of a good home here or in heaven that is not willing to be in peril for a good cause.', 9920, 0), (494952, 'Many a man who thinks to found a home discovers that he has merely opened a tavern for his friends.', 27345, 0), (494953, 'How much a dunce that has been sent to roam, excels a dunce that has been kept at home.', 8676, 0), (494954, 'You can be true to the character all you want but you''ve got to go home with yourself.', 64247, 0), (494955, 'One sweetly solemn thought, comes to me o''er and o''er; I am nearer home today, than I ever have been before.', 25857, 0), (494956, 'Beer is not a good cocktail-party drink, especially in a home where you don''t know where the bathroom is.', 76043, 0), (494957, 'Let''s just win it and go home.', 71921, 0), (494958, 'And remember don''t high post when you''re far from home, and high posting when you''re all alone.', 5050, 0), (494959, 'This is my idea of heaven, coming home and watching the news.', 68716, 0), (494960, 'I''ve gone very far, far away, but my character keeps me close to home.', 34619, 0), (494961, 'Then, after I came home from Europe, I found I was under condemnation; and I was condemned at that time because I did not endorse the financial policy of the General Conference.', 75470, 0), (494962, 'Aledo will always be home to me because I spent the first 27 years of my life there - it''s such a special place - and because of the experiences I had there, I''ve become the person I am today.', 70330, 0), (494963, 'I''m the type of woman you might say is too good. I''ll massage a man''s feet, have dinner cooked when he gets home. But once they leave, the door is closed, and the locks are changed.', 52738, 0), (494964, 'When I joined Custer I donned the uniform of a soldier. It was a bit awkward at first but I soon got to be perfectly at home in men''s clothes.', 76044, 0), (494965, 'I''m shocked at how early everything closes here. But people start earlier. I miss the late nightlife in NYC, but then again I sing and burn so much energy in the show that it''s probably good - I get to go home and sleep.', 36406, 0), (494966, 'I was born in London, and went to school in Scotland - I used to be dead tired when I got home at night.', 74942, 0), (494967, 'I was actually lost in Beirut on the way home.', 75643, 0), (494968, 'Say there''s a white kid who lives in a nice home, goes to an all-white school, and is pretty much having everything handed to him on a platter - for him to pick up a rap tape is incredible to me, because what that''s saying is that he''s living a fantasy life of rebellion.', 392, 0), (494969, 'I''m actually a pretty decent human being, and when I''m home I''m straight as an arrow.', 67013, 0), (494970, 'Although I managed my schedule to be home by late afternoon most days, basically, Roselle raised our children alone. And so I missed out on a lot of wonderful moments, missed watching my kids grow into the wonderful people they are today.', 76045, 0), (494971, 'It was the most pleasurable thing I''ve ever done, playing this character, and I just remember feeling so at home and so - I don''t know, I was just happy - and it just wasn''t ever work! It was like a sandbox for me, and I would crack myself up rehearsing.', 64950, 0), (494972, 'There was a military police brigade with over 3,400 soldiers getting ready to go home because their mission - prisoner-of-war operations - was finished.', 72178, 0), (494973, 'I have a dress-up chest at home. I love to create this fantasy kind of thing.', 12807, 0), (494974, 'How we are using up our home, how we are living and polluting the planet is frightening. It was evident when I was a child. It''s more evident now.', 58539, 0), (494975, 'On tour, you never have a home, you don''t get used to anything, and you''re always super busy.', 71042, 0), (494976, 'I never saw film stars at home. We had no maid, no cook, no swimming pool.', 18441, 0), (494977, 'I was often very, incredibly naughty, and if I didn''t come home at tea time I used to be sent to bed without any dinner. But people used to bring me things: I was better fed in bed.', 71597, 0), (494978, 'That said, my kids are at home right now with my husband and I''m missing something important at my daughter''s school which makes me feel sick inside. It''s a lot of balance and a lot of really hard decision making.', 61441, 0), (494979, 'More than anything else, I want the folks back at home to think right of me.', 1120, 0), (494980, 'Just because I managed to do a little something, I don''t want anyone back home to think I got the big head.', 1120, 0), (494981, 'On stage, I make love to 25,000 different people, then I go home alone.', 12453, 0), (494982, 'At home I am a nice guy: but I don''t want the world to know. Humble people, I''ve found, don''t get very far.', 1751, 0), (494983, 'My mother never gave up one me. I messed up in school so much they were sending me home, but my mother sent me right back.', 5253, 0), (494984, 'I''d rather rot on my own floor than be found by a bunch of bingo players in a nursing home.', 18125, 0), (494985, 'I have always brought home stray animals - everything from squirrels to wild rabbits to foxes and turtles.', 74466, 0), (494986, 'We ought to have more women in various management positions, because women are the ones who decide almost everything in the home.', 73748, 0), (494987, 'We have supported state terrorism against the Palestinians and black South Africans, and now we are indignant because the stuff we have done overseas is now brought right back to our own front yards. America''s chickens are coming home to roost.', 75381, 0), (494988, 'I''m kind of a dork. I don''t have much game. I''m not particularly comfortable in bars or clubs. I much prefer being home playing Scrabble, having dinner with a couple friends, going to see a movie, or losing a whole weekend to Season 14 of Law and Order or The Simpsons.', 38634, 0), (494989, 'It began to dawn on me that perhaps my country needed me more at home than overseas.', 51334, 0), (494990, 'Anytime you''re away from your home filming, it messes with your head.', 47254, 0), (494991, 'Today''s misery is real unemployment, home foreclosures and bankruptcies. This is the Obama Misery Index and its at a record high. Its going to take more than new rhetoric to put Americans back to work - its going to take a new president.', 52321, 0), (494992, 'So long as I can stay mentally alert - inquiring, curious - I want to keep going. I love my wife and my children, but I don''t want to sit around at home with them. We go on safaris and things like that. I can do that for a couple of weeks a year. I''m just not ready to stop, to die.', 15116, 0), (494993, 'I have a five year-old son and a three year-old daughter. I want my son to have a choice to contribute fully in the workforce or at home. And I want my daughter to have the choice to not just succeed, but to be liked for her accomplishments.', 1770, 0), (494994, 'It''s like, now you''re actually complaining because you''re making $9 million and guys are making more? If it makes you that upset, quit. Leave the game. Go home then and try finding another job that''s going to pay you that.', 67095, 0), (494995, 'The fans love the home runs, the home run competition between Mark McGwire and Sammy Sosa.', 73666, 0), (494996, 'I feel most at home in the water. I disappear. That''s where I belong.', 30837, 0), (494997, 'Sometimes I''m at home and I remember I''m supposed to do 100 push-ups and I don''t.', 76046, 0), (494998, 'Playing drums feels like coming home for me. Even during the White Stripes I thought: ''I''ll do this for now, but I''m really a drummer.'' That''s what I''ll put on my passport application.', 22686, 0), (494999, 'I feel an obligation to set the record straight. Actors that say they''re affected by something, that it changes their life, that they take it home with them, they''re just trying to get nominated for an Oscar!', 68461, 0), (495000, 'When I''m home, I cook my own dinner, all organic.', 58634, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (495001, 'These days, you have the option of staying home, blogging in your underwear, and not having your words mangled. I think I like the direction things are headed.', 21378, 0), (495002, 'I''m in this absolutely gorgeous manor house with acres of quite beautiful countryside. I''ve got trout in the river, an organic vegetable garden, I''ve got my work 40 yards from my home. I don''t mind being criticised, but where are they criticising from? Which hut are they criticising me from, exactly?', 67688, 0), (495003, 'Obviously, the easiest recipes are the most successful when it comes to the home cook, because they''re not intimidated by them. If I''m doing ''Boy Meets Grill,'' and I do something very simple like grilled hamburgers or steaks or chicken, those are the most sought-after recipes.', 66675, 0), (495004, 'I can''t grill vegetables, shellfish or steaks without tongs. Don''t bother with those long-handled grilling tongs normally found in the BBQ section of your home store. Get intimate with your grill and opt for the regular stainless steel tongs.', 66675, 0), (495005, 'I''m from a small town so, like, everyone''s married with children or about to have children. So it''s a little hard when you go home and people are like - and that''s why people think I''m gay - because they''re like ''Why aren''t you married?'' And I''m like, ''it doesn''t happen for everyone right off the bat.''', 9111, 0), (495006, 'My company is an extension of me, so when I designed my stores I wanted people to feel that they were in my home.', 74195, 0), (495007, 'For those who have come here illegally, they might have a transition time to allow them to set their affairs in order. And then go back home and get in line with everybody else. And if they get in line and they apply to become a citizen and get a green card, they will be treated like everybody else.', 52321, 0), (495008, 'Locally produced foods - defined as those harvested within a 100-mile radius of one''s home - have a lesser impact on the environment because of the decreased need for transportation from source to consumer.', 69849, 0), (495009, 'My father was always depressed. When he was home and sober, he was mostly in his room.', 360, 0), (495010, 'My father probably thought the capital of the world was wherever he was at the time. It couldn''t possibly be anyplace else. Where he and his wife were in their own home, that, for them, was the capital of the world.', 289, 0), (495011, 'I''m happy going home early and working out and just being a mother and being a wife.', 75955, 0), (495012, 'We have to judge politicians by their cumulative score. In one innings they make a great catch, in another they drop the ball. In one they score a home run, in another they strike out. But it is their cumulative batting average that we are interested in.', 23411, 0), (495013, 'There''s a continuity between what I care about in any form: I care about it in my music, in article-writing, in how I dress, in how I live, in my relationships, in how I navigate paparazzi, how I decorate my home. There''s such a continuity between everything that I don''t really care what form it shows up in.', 21687, 0), (495014, 'I mean, I suppose when I''m in London, I''m home so I''m more comfortable.', 68192, 0), (495015, 'Once I was gone for a month and I was just miserable, so I flew back from Florida for two hours just to be home and see my cats.', 6225, 0), (495016, 'I think any branding for me is band-related. It''s really weird to get used to the exposure, because I am a naturally introverted person, and I''m not exactly social. Occasionally I can get comfortable enough to talk, but I spend a lot of my days not talking, especially when I''m at home and not on tour.', 69375, 0), (495017, 'I don''t get to go home as much as I used to, which is a shame. But I don''t mind because my mum moved over to London to look after me. I rented her a house just around the corner.', 387, 0), (495018, 'I support workplace clean air. But a federal ban on smoking would mean that you couldn''t smoke in your own home. I don''t care what people do in their home.', 17681, 0), (495019, 'My sisters both are working mothers. I understand that my being an actress as well as being at home isn''t some heroic thing. That doesn''t mean it isn''t confusing or difficult - especially that question of how you find a balance.', 18389, 0), (495020, 'At times you feel like you''re the only voice speaking out to improve the working conditions of people, whether it''s to be able to collectively bargain, to get adequate pay, to know that you can come home safe out of a coal mine.', 72240, 0), (495021, 'The truth is, if anyone saw my home life, I''m pretty sure it would look like other families'' around the world. There''s a lot of juggling to be done.', 72272, 0), (495022, 'Illogical thinkers throw names and slurs around because they have no arguments with which to rebut their opponents. Rational people have to keep hammering their points home.', 1793, 0), (495023, 'I hate formal stuff. I love looking like a doll and all that stuff and playing dress up, but when I''m home, sweat pants, t-shirt. When I''m in the studio, sweat pants, t-shirt.', 2069, 0), (495024, 'The Second Amendment does protect the right to people to possess weapons for self-defense in the home. That''s what the Supreme Court said.', 71558, 0), (495025, 'I''d be totally exhausted by mid-afternoon, and I could barely climb the stairs at home. It was particularly alarming because all my life I''d enjoyed doing all my own stunts in shows, taking on every physical challenge. Yet suddenly, I''d become like a very old man. I knew something was wrong, but I had no idea what.', 68901, 0), (495026, 'Many women assume they can''t be good mothers and have challenging careers at the same time, so they might give up trying to do both as they get to a crucial point in their career. Although it can be hard at times, it''s important for women to recognize the benefits of working outside the home.', 69442, 0), (495027, 'I don''t think most analysts understand that whether I work a 70-hour week or an 80-hour week, I take my head with me when I go home.', 76047, 0), (495028, 'I try and eat really healthy when I''m home, but I certainly don''t eat worms and snakes.', 9272, 0), (495029, 'I''m happy to be at home with the kids, in my flannel pajamas; that''s a treat.', 74366, 0), (495030, 'I am not a home breaker and I can never be. I haven''t been brought up to create havoc in other people''s homes.', 68854, 0), (495031, 'Many Lexington natives believe they live in a special place, one impossible to leave. I''m not so sure about that - or it''s more accurate to say I think a more general truth exists beneath it: the place you first call home stays with you always, whether you remain or go.', 8033, 0), (495032, 'I''m a bachelor in the old sense of the word, meaning I flirt, I have very many close relationships, but then I come home and like to read my book.', 76048, 0), (495033, 'I live in a sort of insular world. It''s mostly my family, my house, staying home and working.', 70913, 0), (495034, 'It''s often discouraging sitting working at home, wondering whether to put the heating on, answering the doorbell to the gas board, feeling it''s all utterly pointless.', 76049, 0), (495035, 'In my home office, I have two large, 30-inch computer monitors - a Mac and a PC. They share the same mouse and keyboard, so I can type or copy and paste between them. I''ll typically do Web stuff on the Mac and e-mail and chat stuff on the PC.', 68429, 0), (495036, 'You don''t see me in Los Angeles a lot. I go back home. Because I can''t play the game. I can''t - my tolerance - I know I''m getting old I''ll be 50 this year. And you know how I know I''m getting old? ''Cause my tolerance level is low. ', 68423, 0), (495037, 'People are responsible adults at home. Why do we suddenly transform them into adolescents with no freedom when they reach the workplace?', 70587, 0), (495038, 'Those days of every child having a mummy and daddy who lived at home - Daddy went to work, and Mummy stayed at home and took care of everyone - those days have almost gone, and it''s so much more unconventional now.', 22748, 0), (495039, 'I think if you follow anyone home, whether they live in Houston or London, and you sit at their dinner table and talk to them about their mother who has cancer or their child who is struggling in school, and their fears about watching their lives go by, I think we''re all the same.', 247, 0), (495040, 'Let me put it this way: when I read, I learned the world was not as small as my house. And that everybody in my home town was not representative of the way people in the world were raised. And that was what saved me.', 9764, 0), (495041, 'Ladies love a soppy lyric. There''s a real winner in ''Carry You Home.''', 16022, 0), (495042, 'I''d never put all my chips anywhere, because I don''t want to close any doors, but I was raised in a very blue-collar family. I was raised by parents who said, ''If you don''t go to work every day, you''re not contributing'', so that''s my mentality. I have to work every day; I have to bring home a paycheck.', 72053, 0), (495043, 'You have to be very insensitive in order to have a cat, because I think they''re very independent. When they''re kittens, you think they''re going to have a dog temperament in that they''re going to run to the door when you get home, lick you on the face and cuddle with you all the time, but cats are not that way.', 2549, 0), (495044, 'People are easily intimidated when they decorate their home. They think it has to be one way. But there''s no one way. It''s your way, your style. At the end of the day, you have to live there. It''s your cocoon, your nest. You have to be happy in it.', 10716, 0), (495045, 'I live in Brooklyn, and I love all the hipsters and all the artisanal bacon you can get here now. I consider New York my home, and L.A. a place that I go. I always say I go with an empty sack and try to fill it with as much money as possible to bring back to New York.', 76050, 0), (495046, 'Runners and yogis are alike in lots of ways, and not just because some of us need yoga to unkink what running jams. Runners and yogis are also alike because of this tortoise shell idea, this ''home'' we can access inside ourselves.', 12208, 0), (495047, 'I think anybody who goes away finds you appreciate home more when you return.', 25711, 0), (495048, 'A drone is a high-tech version of an old army and a musket. It ought to be used in Somalia to hunt bad guys, but not in America. I don''t want to see it hovering over anybody''s home.', 45527, 0), (495049, 'As an actress, I get plenty of drama in my professional life. When I''m at home, I want a peaceful life.', 76051, 0), (495050, 'I''ve read everything Thomas Wolfe ever wrote; my brother and I memorized whole chapters of ''You Can''t Go Home Again'' and ''Look Homeward, Angel.''', 74, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (495051, 'I wouldn''t call myself a shut-in. I have the ability to leave my home; I just choose not to. But because I''m such a homebody, it''s important to be surrounded by things I love.', 274, 0), (495052, 'Early on, I played one or two disturbed people, and I guess I must have been good at it, because it stuck. But, you know, I''m a regular guy. I stay home a lot, I make an effort to keep a distance from the whole social thing, the openings, the parties. I try to live in a calm way.', 67388, 0), (495053, '''Feminist comedy,'' practically an oxymoron, had a couple of good years after WWII. Chalk it up to the forced female autonomy that occurred during wartime, when Rosie the Riveter went to work in the factories, constructing the Allies'' war machines while taking charge of the finances, the home, and the children.', 64763, 0), (495054, 'When I was about ten, I was very impressed by the way Tarzan could swing through the trees from vine to vine. No one ever told me, ''Don''t try this at home.''', 22081, 0), (495055, 'Home life is no more natural to us than a cage is natural to a cockatoo.', 266, 0), (495056, 'There are moments to indulge and enjoy, but I always know when it''s time to go home and wash my knickers.', 22748, 0), (495057, 'I''m not someone who''s led my life trying to get publicity I''d rather do my work and go home. ', 60302, 0), (495058, 'I''d much rather go out and have music randomly presented to me by different DJs than stay home and discover it on my own.', 67002, 0), (495059, 'Like your home''s closets, your financial clutter needs an overhaul every now and again, and the payoff will go far beyond the psychic satisfaction of neatening up.', 10090, 0), (495060, 'When I was eight, I would look at the cover of the ''Ghost Rider'' comic book in my little home in Long Beach, California, and I couldn''t get my head around how something that scary could also be good. To me it was my first philosophical awakening - ''How is this possible, this duality?''', 67437, 0), (495061, 'There''s no place like home. And I do miss my home.', 1851, 0), (495062, 'To be a queen of a household is a powerful thing.', 70444, 0), (495063, 'I didn''t leave home until 27. I was an only child raised in Philadelphia by my mother and grandmother. My grandmother controlled the stove. She made a lot of potato meals - mashed potato, potato souffle, potato pancakes. When we didn''t have electricity, we ate romantically by candlelight.', 70444, 0), (495064, 'There are people with otherwise chaotic and disorganized lives, a certain type of person that''s always found a home in the restaurant business in much the same way that a lot of people find a home in the military.', 6719, 0), (495065, 'He told me he was working as an interpreter in a doctor''s office in Brookline, Massachusetts, where I was living at the time, and he was translating for a doctor who had a number of Russian patients. On my way home, after running into him, I just heard this phrase in my head.', 1590, 0), (495066, 'It''s nice to have some continuity you can come back to. I feel that in coming home, coming back to London.', 69501, 0), (495067, 'Once I am in the square circle, I am in my home.', 67644, 0), (495068, 'My fiancee''s brother-in-law was recently paralysed in an accident and it really brought home the fact that thousands of young people live with spinal injuries. It''s an issue I wish had more coverage.', 69667, 0), (495069, 'I would love to have a robot at home.', 43985, 0), (495070, 'I feel like I''ve never had a home, you know? I feel related to the country, to this country, and yet I don''t know exactly where I fit in... There''s always this kind of nostalgia for a place, a place where you can reckon with yourself.', 9118, 0), (495071, 'I do not recall a Jewish home without a book on the table.', 10, 0), (495072, 'In our home there was always prayer - aloud, proud and unapologetic.', 1763, 0), (495073, 'Not much shocked me. You know, I worked in a home for Alzheimer''s patients and my dad used to be really into murders and stuff, so I saw dead bodies. It desensitised me to a lot of things.', 16756, 0), (495074, 'I have great childhood memories cow-tipping, going off and getting lost in the bog for hours, and coming home covered in dirt.', 67018, 0), (495075, 'Because I had my family, I felt like I could be a bird and fly and experience and do. Because I had roots somewhere, I knew that they would love me no matter what, and I could always go back home and they were going to love me.', 47135, 0), (495076, 'But now, being a parent, I go home and see my son and I forget about any mistake I ever made or the reason I''m upset. I get home and my son is smiling or he comes running to me. It has just made me grow as an individual and grow as a man.', 11158, 0), (495077, 'I like to stay home with my family.', 69339, 0), (495078, 'I don''t think I am that materialistic, actually. Obviously at home in the country the art collection is important, but we have one big room in the middle of the house where we do everything - the television, the kitchen, everything.', 24279, 0), (495079, 'In many college classes, laptops depict split screens - notes from a class, and then a range of parallel stimulants: NBA playoff statistics on ESPN.com, a flight home on Expedia, a new flirtation on Facebook.', 17792, 0), (495080, 'There''s a very real possibility in this industry of going out and leading your life and then going home and being a voyeur of your own life. You can literally go watch yourself - where you went last night, what you did, what the things that people presuppose about you. It''s kind of crazy.', 69249, 0), (495081, 'There''s only one thing harder than living in a home with an adolescent - and that''s being an adolescent. The moodiness, the volatility, the wholesale lack of impulse control, all would be close to clinical conditions if they occurred at another point in life. In adolescence, they''re just part of the behavioral portfolio.', 60048, 0), (495082, 'It''s not a joke: I really do like being at home.', 1566, 0), (495083, 'Yesterday, I did some painting then went out to buy an onion and came home and watched ''University Challenge.'' The onion was probably the highlight.', 1566, 0), (495084, 'I''d like to keep work work and life life. It means you''ve got your life to come back to, somewhere to come home to at night that isn''t invaded by your day.', 70221, 0), (495085, 'But, you know, you can''t be a star at home.', 14367, 0), (495086, 'I like being at home and cooking.', 32889, 0), (495087, 'When did it - When did it become okay for someone to hit home runs and forget how to play the rest of the game?', 66959, 0), (495088, 'Women work as much as men now, if not more. There''s a resurgence of dads in the home and moms working.', 76052, 0), (495089, 'I never really take shortcuts. I was always one of those people who, instead of cutting across someone''s yard on the way home from school, I would go to the end of the block and turn.', 274, 0), (495090, 'I want to go home at night and feel discomfort.', 754, 0), (495091, 'While I enjoy spending time in L.A., Britain is my home.', 69745, 0), (495092, 'I am a believer in nutrient timing and supplementation, through 8Zone. I love eggs, apples, wild fish, leafy greens, brown rice, pasta, oatmeal, home grown Washington Potatoes, and cooking with coconut and olive oils.', 68124, 0), (495093, 'I have a deep and passionate love of America. It is where I have always thought I would be happiest, and although I miss England desperately, I find that my heart definitely has its home over here.', 1396, 0), (495094, 'I remember when I came home from the hospital after having my son, I wore a Narciso Rodriguez black coat. Then, I was using this fragrance that I had created. I walk by that coat, and it still smells like that fragrance. It takes you right there.', 4816, 0), (495095, 'After hundreds of auditions and nothing, you''re sitting home and wondering, ''What am I doing?''', 271, 0), (495096, 'I seek to call America home to those principles that gave us birth.', 68665, 0), (495097, 'The worst feeling in the world is the homesickness that comes over a man occasionally when he is at home.', 13154, 0), (495098, 'The curious are always in some danger. If you are curious you might never come home.', 163, 0), (495099, 'Theatrical is fantastic. I don''t think anything will ever replace the big dark room, the screen and the popcorn. You can kind of do it in your home if you have a nice screen, but it''s not the same thing.', 68957, 0), (495100, 'Ever since viewing screens entered the home, many observers have worried that they put our brains into a stupor. An early strain of research claimed that when we watch television, our brains mostly exhibit slow alpha waves - indicating a low level of arousal, similar to when we are daydreaming.', 28478, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (495101, 'If I don''t get paid I''m going to take a whole lot of Marshall amps home with me on the plane.', 71577, 0), (495102, 'Nice to see your home fans boo you. That''s what loyal support is.', 68356, 0), (495103, 'I still watch ''Idol,'' and it''s still the No. 1 show, so obviously I''m not the only one who loves to sit at home and be entertained.', 9111, 0), (495104, 'I have two Golden Boot awards at home. It would be nice to win another, but I wouldn''t mind it if I didn''t.', 5874, 0), (495105, 'I want my home to look good, feel good, and smell good. I want it to be inclusive, to reflect the people who live there.', 18113, 0), (495106, 'A Jew without Jews, without Judaism, without Zionism, without Jewishness, without a temple or an army or even a pistol, a Jew clearly without a home, just the object itself, like a glass or an apple.', 398, 0), (495107, 'A ''Magik'' session is a journey through different stages of emotions and the ''Search for Sunrise'' is more chilling music for when you come home after a party or when you are just about to go to one.', 69210, 0), (495108, 'Home is the place we love best and grumble the most.', 2172, 0), (495109, 'I did not enjoy Cambridge. But I shouldn''t blame Cambridge alone. I wasn''t ready for university or for the wrench of leaving home. It was a big cultural shock.', 72950, 0), (495110, 'Imagine if you had baseball cards that showed all the performance stats for your people: batting averages, home runs, errors, ERAs, win/loss records. You could see what they did well and poorly and call on the right people to play the right positions in a very transparent way.', 29403, 0), (495111, 'Those men are most apt to be obsequious and conciliating abroad, who are under the discipline of shrews at home.', 944, 0), (495112, 'Greed has driven the world crazy. And I think I''m lucky that I have a place over here that I can call home.', 19782, 0), (495113, 'When I come home, it''s about my kid, who needs to eat, needs to do homework, and needs to get to basketball. I don''t have a lot of time to think about me.', 69103, 0), (495114, 'I tentatively believe in a god. I was brought up in a fairly religious home. I think the world is compatible with reincarnation, karma, all that stuff.', 72702, 0), (495115, 'We know that when people are safe in their homes, they are free to pursue their dream for a brighter economic future for themselves and their families.', 73779, 0), (495116, 'For me, and this may not be everybody, but because I do love country music so much, there''s such a feeling of home in Nashville, especially because it''s such a small town. You bring up one song, everybody knows who wrote it, everybody knows their mother and what their cell number is, and all of the stories.', 68804, 0), (495117, 'What really helps me is being able to record my albums at home - I have more fun experimenting that way, as opposed to working with an engineer, in which case I have to deal with the humiliation of doing take after take, and that can get frustrating.', 71660, 0), (495118, 'The mother-in-law came round last week. It was absolutely pouring down. So I opened the door and I saw her there and I said, ''Mother, don''t just stand there in the rain. Go home.''', 64396, 0), (495119, 'I grew up in a household where everybody lived at the top of his lungs.', 72113, 0), (495120, 'I grew up in the Cayman Islands. I didn''t play video games or watch TV. I would basically come home from school, throw down my backpack, grab my machete, and go hike and chop down trees to make a fort.', 73222, 0), (495121, 'Unless you have been to boarding-school when you are very young, it is absolutely impossible to appreciate the delights of living at home.', 222, 0), (495122, 'I''m not squeamish at all. As a child I dragged a dead squirrel home on my skateboard and cut it open and tried to look at its brain.', 69216, 0), (495123, 'I like my home to be somewhere where my friends can feel like they can put their feet up on the couch and for it to feel like really easy living. I really love to have my friends over, cook dinner for them, catch up, and spend quality time with quality people in my life.', 69836, 0), (495124, 'My days in hostel were tough. I was ragged by my seniors. We were asked to wash their dirty clothes, do their odd jobs, etc. When it came to eating, we would be often given burnt rotis and milk that had awful odour. But, never once did I call home. I knew if I had to become a tough cricketer, I would have to handle the pressure.', 67900, 0), (495125, 'The thing about being at home versus being out in the world working is, it''s a whole different vibe. When I''m home with my kids and partner, I will cook - even though she''s a very good cook. She''s learned over the years. We started with basics, you know, how to saute onions, how to saute mushrooms.', 71078, 0), (495126, 'Charity should begin at home, but should not stay there.', 22130, 0), (495127, 'My mother was a churchgoing lady, so I always heard about God at home.', 68013, 0), (495128, 'When I''m not on tour, I love to have a long breakfast at home in my garden.', 68426, 0), (495129, 'Kids in a home with grandparents are healthier.', 4994, 0), (495130, 'If you are a writer you''re at home, which means you''re out of touch. You have to make excuses to get out there and look at how the world is changing.', 27393, 0), (495131, 'I would like not only to have a successful band, but I want to have children, a home, and a husband. Two or three. Children, not husbands!!!', 76053, 0), (495132, 'Home, nowadays, is a place where part of the family waits till the rest of the family brings the car back.', 25666, 0), (495133, 'You''re in a combat zone one day. You come home, and then you have to readjust, and it takes a few days. We just sit in the house, hang with the family and then things get better.', 2455, 0), (495134, 'If anyone thinks that Jews can steal into the land of their fathers, he is deceiving either himself or others. Nowhere is the coming of Jews so promptly noted as in the historic home of the Jews, for the very reason that it is the historic home.', 17762, 0), (495135, 'I thought I''d love to be a gardener because I grew up with a vegetable garden and I love being close to the Earth and growing things. At my home in L.A., I have a great garden and I grow all kinds of things. I even have a worm farm! The worms help create organic compost out of kitchen scraps.', 72668, 0), (495136, 'When I go home, its an easy way to be grounded. You learn to realize what truly matters.', 66946, 0), (495137, 'The bees learn where they live by landmarks. If they''re moved within their home range, they get confused.', 73359, 0), (495138, 'Christian values were important at home. Cleanliness. Don''t steal. Don''t lie. Those were the rules, and they were strictly enforced. Especially the stealing and lying. When you broke the rules, you got a beating. I always broke the rules a lot.', 68096, 0), (495139, 'I didn''t have time for my children much. I wasn''t a very good parent I had a pretty unhappy home life. ', 66976, 0), (495140, 'I''m a real Suzy Homemaker.', 70330, 0), (495141, 'For an economic recovery program to be effective, it must not only create a short-term economic boost but also generate lasting value. Home Star would accomplish that by breaking down the key barrier between homeowners and money-saving retrofits: upfront costs.', 76054, 0), (495142, 'Our favorite: a former garbage dump converted into a riverside park. I first ran there more than 30 years ago when a marathon passed through this park that later became home to Pre''s Trail.', 76055, 0), (495143, 'Where there is a mother in the home, matters go well.', 13866, 0), (495144, 'Life is composed of different inventions. I have continued to work at different things and rebuilt my home all by myself. I did it for the sake of satisfaction at doing something.', 74301, 0), (495145, 'I come from a broken home. My parents split up when I was nine. Everyone gave me a good wallop. But I come from a time when you just put up with that, you got on with things rather than sitting moaning about them.', 76056, 0), (495146, 'I am an old sinner; and if God had designed mercy for me, he would have called me home to himself before now.', 67770, 0), (495147, 'Having leveled my palace, don''t erect a hovel and complacently admire your own charity in giving me that for a home.', 55, 0), (495148, 'I think standing and fighting and working alongside all of these people that raise their right hand and serve their nation... really wipes away the distractions of some of the petty things we think are important at home.', 70835, 0), (495149, 'Of all the passions of mankind, the love of novelty most rules the mind. In search of this, from realm to realm we roam. Our fleets come loaded with every folly home.', 32421, 0), (495150, 'I''m attached to my land in Pantelleria as if I''d inherited it. Acting is my job, Pantelleria is my home.', 76057, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (495151, 'The spirit is at home, if not entirely satisfied, in America.', 2791, 0), (495152, 'The reader need not be told that John Bull never leaves home without encumbering himself with the greatest possible load of luggage. Our companions were no exception to the rule.', 20837, 0), (495153, 'I like to stay home and watch television. The Game Show channel, mostly.', 70921, 0), (495154, 'I''ve been in Hamburg for about ten years and I just feel at home.', 75032, 0), (495155, 'What good to me is the festive garment of freedom when I am in a slave''s smock at home?', 59770, 0), (495156, 'The home ownership process for Native Americans has been hobbled by bureaucratic delays and regulations.', 76020, 0), (495157, 'My parents took an interest in nothing, at home no books, no records. My mother and my father are the emblem of indifference, dryness and bad taste. My father is also terribly stingy, in life as well as in feelings: I have never seen him filling up the bathtub.', 17177, 0), (495158, 'Now that I have a 16-month-old son, my weekend ritual has changed - but it''s better than ever. We get up early and go for a walk on one of the hiking trails near my home in Los Angeles, then meet up with friends at a diner. There''s nothing better than sipping coffee, eating scrambled eggs, and taking three hours to do it.', 71666, 0), (495159, 'My situation is different from Mark''s. I''m not looking for home runs, I''m looking for the playoffs.', 66608, 0), (495160, 'I escaped to New York, and then L.A., but when I dream of home, I still dream of my old house in Holmdel.', 74523, 0), (495161, 'Home - that blessed word, which opens to the human heart the most perfect glimpse of Heaven, and helps to carry it thither, as on an angel''s wings.', 59119, 0), (495162, 'The home to everyone is to him his castle and fortress, as well for his defence against injury and violence, as for his repose.', 62809, 0), (495163, 'I have no reason to sit home and write songs all day without going out and playing for the folks. And I have no reason to go play for the folks unless I''m writing new songs so they can sort of feed off one another. And I just try to do the best I can.', 16932, 0), (495164, 'I think to be in exile is a curse, and you need to turn it into a blessing. You''ve been thrown into exile to die, really, to silence you so that your voice cannot come home. And so my whole life has been dedicated to saying, ''I will not be silenced.''', 51638, 0), (495165, 'In 1979, when I was toddler, the Russians invaded Afghanistan, and my whole family fled to Vienna, Virginia. Far from home, my parents were determined to raise my two sisters and me according to Afghan traditions.', 72503, 0), (495166, 'I left home because I was hungry.', 62651, 0), (495167, 'I have an awesome church home and an awesome Pastor down in L.A., and I couldn''t be happier.', 6467, 0), (495168, 'Television is an invention that permits you to be entertained in your living room by people you wouldn''t have in your home.', 5472, 0), (495169, 'Be grateful for the home you have, knowing that at this moment, all you have is all you need.', 7175, 0), (495170, 'Strength of character may be learned at work, but beauty of character is learned at home.', 45086, 0), (495171, 'Never make your home in a place. Make a home for yourself inside your own head. You''ll find what you need to furnish it - memory, friends you can trust, love of learning, and other such things. That way it will go with you wherever you journey.', 2226, 0), (495172, 'Run a home like you would a small business and treat it with the same seriousness.', 69425, 0), (495173, 'We''re having a good time. That''s what I did last year. If you can''t have a good time, you might as well stay home. I feel real good.', 76058, 0), (495174, 'Consultant: any ordinary guy more than fifty miles from home.', 54832, 0), (495175, 'Our nation was built by pioneers - pioneers who accepted untold risks in pursuit of freedom, not by pioneers seeking offshore profits at the expense of American workers here at home.', 72294, 0), (495176, 'I knew everything in the forest. I had a secret home tree, where I pretty much lived. I also liked rooftops and streetlamps. My parents would get calls saying ''He''s out there again.''', 76059, 0), (495177, 'Home interprets heaven. Home is heaven for beginners.', 42648, 0), (495178, 'A home is more than just where you live it reflects who you are. ', 76060, 0), (495179, 'We managed to write chapter one. Chapter two, we will have a child a parent can take home and raise as a cloned child.', 70650, 0), (495180, 'Home is the most popular, and will be the most enduring of all earthly establishments.', 9956, 0), (495181, 'I would not change my blest estate for all the world calls good or great.', 10868, 0), (495182, 'Seek home for rest, for home is best.', 12910, 0), (495183, 'Sometimes when I get home at night in Washington I feel as though I had been in a great traffic jam.', 71906, 0), (495184, 'I really try to take care of myself. I really put forth the effort to make a regimen just a part of my life. When I can''t, for instance if I''m in a location someplace and I can''t work out because of the schedule of the picture or whatever it is, as much as I normally do when I''m home, I still do something.', 73821, 0), (495185, 'When I got home from hospital, and I was in a wheelchair in a plaster body cast, an aeroplane flew over. And I thought to myself, ''Well, if I can''t walk, then I might as well fly.'' And I was lifted into the aeroplane for the first time. And when I took the controls of the aeroplane, I knew this was something I could do. I thought, ''I can fly.''', 76061, 0), (495186, 'There''s a magical tie to the land of our home, which the heart cannot break, though the footsteps may roam.', 23259, 0), (495187, 'I haven''t had a stationary home since going with the circus, but since my parents lived in Lafayette about 25 years ago and my sister lives here now, I always claim it as home.', 68650, 0), (495188, 'I always clean before the cleaning lady comes. If not, when I come home, I can''t find anything. Cleaning ladies are always hiding things you leave out.', 76062, 0), (495189, 'I think even when homeowners love their room, it''s still a shock, because you left your house, went to sleep, came home and your room was dramatically and drastically different.', 76063, 0), (495190, 'These rooms are decorated in two days. It''s all kept secret. The neighbors spend the night in each other''s home. They don''t see their finished room until the end of the second day. They have no say what happens in their own home.', 76063, 0), (495191, 'So, my sweetheart back home writes to me and wants to know what this gal in Bombay''s got that she hasn''t got. So I just write back to her and says, Nothin'', honey. Only she''s got it here.', 76064, 0), (495192, 'I''m a huge Wonder Woman fan - I have about 12 coffee mugs at home!', 76065, 0), (495193, 'My fingers are not as fast as my brain - which isn''t that much to type home about anyway.', 64884, 0), (495194, 'Home wasn''t built in a day.', 76066, 0), (495195, 'When a writer knows home in his heart, his heart must remain subtly apart from it.', 51400, 0), (495196, 'Loneliness expresses the pain of being alone and solitude expresses the glory of being alone.', 2750, 0), (495197, 'Alone we can do so little together we can do so much. ', 701, 0), (495198, 'It is far better to be alone, than to be in bad company.', 3161, 0), (495199, 'I restore myself when I''m alone.', 1, 0), (495200, 'As I get older I''m more and more comfortable being alone.', 67853, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (495201, 'Being alone & actually sitting with our own thoughts can lead to such growth and realizations that are rare in our everyday busy lives.', 67014, 0), (495202, 'To go out with the setting sun on an empty beach is to truly embrace your solitude.', 52500, 0), (495203, 'What a lovely surprise to finally discover how unlonely being alone can be.', 72672, 0), (495204, 'The strong man is strongest when alone.', 1988, 0), (495205, 'Loneliness is the poverty of self solitude is the richness of self. ', 996, 0), (495206, 'Justice cannot be for one side alone, but must be for both.', 141, 0), (495207, 'No phone. No pool. No pets. No cigarettes. Ultimate freedom... No longer to be poisoned by civilization, he flees, and walks alone upon the land to become Lost in the Wild.', 1344, 0), (495208, 'It''s better to be unhappy alone than unhappy with someone - so far.', 1, 0), (495209, 'I have so many different personalities in me and I still feel lonely.', 1549, 0), (495210, 'I only go out to get me a fresh appetite for being alone.', 62558, 0), (495211, 'If you would have your son to walk honourably through the world, you must not attempt to clear the stones from his path, but teach him to walk firmly over them - not insist upon leading him by the hand, but let him learn to go alone.', 3187, 0), (495212, 'Being alone is very difficult.', 1121, 0), (495213, 'A man is born alone and dies alone and he experiences the good and bad consequences of his karma alone and he goes alone to hell or the Supreme abode. ', 25555, 0), (495214, 'Every man must do two things alone he must do his own believing and his own dying. ', 1746, 0), (495215, 'Language... has created the word ''loneliness'' to express the pain of being alone. And it has created the word ''solitude'' to express the glory of being alone.', 2750, 0), (495216, 'Every person remembers some moment in their life where they witnessed some injustice, big or small, and looked away because the consequences of intervening seemed too intimidating. But there''s a limit to the amount of incivility and inequality and inhumanity that each individual can tolerate. I crossed that line. And I''m no longer alone.', 25121, 0), (495217, 'It is strange to be known so universally and yet to be so lonely.', 104, 0), (495218, 'Who knows what true loneliness is - not the conventional word but the naked terror? To the lonely themselves it wears a mask. The most miserable outcast hugs some memory or some illusion.', 1241, 0), (495219, 'Yes, I guess you could say I am a loner, but I feel more lonely in a crowed room with boring people than I feel on my own.', 68, 0), (495220, 'I was a queen, and you took away my crown; a wife, and you killed my husband; a mother, and you deprived me of my children. My blood alone remains: take it, but do not make me suffer long.', 19731, 0), (495221, 'Grant that I may not pray alone with the mouth help me that I may pray from the depths of my heart. ', 1746, 0), (495222, 'Remember that the revolution is what is important, and each one of us, alone, is worth nothing.', 68679, 0), (495223, 'Life could be wonderful if people would leave you alone.', 454, 0), (495224, 'Getting through the nights is the toughest part. Being alone. Not having her there to talk to.', 75600, 0), (495225, 'Too many Christians have a commitment of convenience. They''ll stay faithful as long as it''s safe and doesn''t involve risk, rejection, or criticism. Instead of standing alone in the face of challenge or temptation, they check to see which way their friends are going.', 67762, 0), (495226, 'Singing provides a true sense of lightheartedness. If I sing when I am alone, I feel wonderful. It''s freedom.', 67812, 0), (495227, 'Freedom of being alone is intoxicating.', 67017, 0), (495228, 'Don''t go away. I don''t want to be alone. I can''t stand being alone.', 76067, 0), (495229, 'I never have tantrums. If anything makes me mad, I''m silent. If I''m not talking, leave me alone.', 76068, 0), (495230, 'It is true that integrity alone won''t make you a leader, but without integrity you will never be one.', 1692, 0), (495231, 'The lonely become either thoughtful or empty.', 12469, 0), (495232, 'The drive toward Life is protective, thoughtful, vulnerable, and invested in immaculate love. It is this last that marks the difference between a wise heart muddy with real life experiences in the trenches and a dry heart that functions on rote concepts alone.', 625, 0), (495233, 'Solitude vivifies isolation kills. ', 563, 0), (495234, 'Being solitary is being alone well: being alone luxuriously immersed in doings of your own choice, aware of the fullness of your won presence rather than of the absence of others. Because solitude is an achievement.', 24969, 0), (495235, 'The flesh endures the storms of the present alone; the mind, those of the past and future as well as the present. Gluttony is a lust of the mind.', 2593, 0), (495236, 'I''m calculating, self-sufficient, reserved, and I enjoy being alone.', 76069, 0), (495237, 'I was born alone, I''m gonna die alone. I have my own identity. I''m my own person, and no two people are the same.', 71437, 0), (495238, 'I would rather be a beggar and single than a queen and married.', 1401, 0), (495239, 'I''m fascinated with myself and love hearing the sound of my own voice. I''d like to hear what I have to say. A lot of people don''t like being alone because they truly don''t like themselves, but I love me.', 11192, 0), (495240, 'However much I might try to expound or explain Love, when I come to Love itself, I am ashamed of my explanations... Love alone can explain the mysteries of love and lovers.', 20453, 0), (495241, 'Nothing we do, however virtuous, can be accomplished alone; therefore we are saved by love.', 1779, 0), (495242, 'Smart businesses do not look at labor costs alone anymore. They do look at market access, transportation, telecommunications infrastructure and the education and skill level of the workforce, the development of capital and the regulatory market.', 70324, 0), (495243, 'I like video games, but they are very violent. I want to create a video game in which you have to help all the characters who have died in the other games. ''Hey, man, what are you playing?'' ''Super Busy Hospital. Could you leave me alone? I''m performing surgery! This guy got shot in the head, like, 27 times!''', 2315, 0), (495244, 'Remember, you and you alone are responsible for maintaining your energy. Give up blaming, complaining and excuse making, and keep taking action in the direction of your goals - however mundane or lofty they may be.', 1834, 0), (495245, 'I''m fiercely independent, but I''m also terrified of being alone.', 70717, 0), (495246, 'One man alone can be pretty dumb sometimes, but for real bona fide stupidity, there ain''t nothin'' can beat teamwork.', 1370, 0), (495247, 'I finally faced the fact that it isn''t a crime not having friends. Being alone means you have fewer problems.', 15469, 0), (495248, 'I don''t treat the band like I''m above them or that they''re a hired hand for me. We''ve never worked that way. So I''m a team player. I would be very uncomfortable having to do this alone.', 21291, 0), (495249, 'What a child can do in cooperation today, he can do alone tomorrow.', 72105, 0), (495250, 'Aim high and don''t sell yourself short. Know that you''re capable. Understand that a lot of people battle with a lot of things - depression, body image or whatever else - so know that it''s not just you. You''re not alone.', 71932, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (495251, 'If we were to wipe out insects alone on this planet, the rest of life and humanity with it would mostly disappear from the land. Within a few months.', 44747, 0), (495252, 'Virtue is not left to stand alone. He who practices it will have neighbors.', 819, 0), (495253, 'And if you don''t believe the sun will rise, stand alone and greet the coming night in the last remaining light.', 49828, 0), (495254, 'A lot of people prefer to be alone. They would rather be a palm tree on an island. I don''t get it.', 67848, 0), (495255, 'I rise to taste the dawn, and find that love alone will shine today.', 3365, 0), (495256, 'I try to find 15 minutes a day to just be alone without any distractions just for headspace to meditate and get my Zen on. I think that helps me get through the hecticness of the day on tour with the interviews, the sound check, the meet and greets, the show and the post-show meet and greets.', 69372, 0), (495257, 'I must study alone, as I am condemned to do every thing alone, I believe, in this life.', 3921, 0), (495258, 'It is not a liberty of circumstance, conceded to us alone, that we wish; it is the adoption absolute of the principle that no man, born red, black or white, can be the property of his fellow man.', 67780, 0), (495259, 'I am free because I know that I alone am morally responsible for everything I do. I am free, no matter what rules surround me. If I find them tolerable, I tolerate them; if I find them too obnoxious, I break them. I am free because I know that I alone am morally responsible for everything I do.', 17, 0), (495260, 'The light of lights looks always on the motive, not the deed, the shadow of shadows on the deed alone.', 62867, 0), (495261, 'Still and all, why bother? Here''s my answer. Many people need desperately to receive this message: I feel and think much as you do, care about many of the things you care about, although most people do not care about them. 