able when I''m alone. As a kid, I was very much a loner. I love long distance running and long distance biking. A director once pointed out that those are all very isolated exercises you do for hours at a time.', 75657, 0), (495376, 'For example, for me, my brother helped me get a manager, which I don''t take for granted. It''s tough getting a manager, let alone one that actually cares about you and is smart. But from there, no one''s going to cast me just because I''m James Franco''s little brother.', 75322, 0), (495377, 'The universe is almost 14 billion years old, and, wow! Life had no problem starting here on Earth! I think it would be inexcusably egocentric of us to suggest that we''re alone in the universe.', 404, 0), (495378, 'I can''t stand to watch anything that I''m in. I tear it apart. The worst thing you can do is leave me alone and let me watch what I''m in. It''s abusive.', 76074, 0), (495379, 'The mortal mind alone cannot devise an answer to the Israeli-Palestinian conflict, because the true answer lies on a level of consciousness that''s beyond our mortal thinking. Quite simply, when it comes to Israel and the Palestinians, we need a miracle.', 534, 0), (495380, 'Musical theater is great; you get painted up, you get to play princesses and witches, and you sing. The joy alone of that can really carry a lot.', 12497, 0), (495381, 'Lifestyle changes may help reduce risk, but no study has shown that lifestyle changes alone can eliminate the risk of breast cancer, especially in those carrying the BRCA mutation.', 45749, 0), (495382, 'Perhaps I know best why it is man alone who laughs he alone suffers so deeply that he had to invent laughter. ', 11, 0), (495383, 'Often we can help each other most by leaving each other alone at other times we need the hand-grasp and the word of cheer. ', 4, 0), (495384, 'All we ask is to be let alone.', 16075, 0), (495385, 'I never did anything alone. Whatever was accomplished in this country was accomplished collectively.', 12971, 0), (495386, 'Our language has wisely sensed the two sides of being alone. It has created the word loneliness to express the pain of being alone. And it has created the word solitude to express the glory of being alone.', 2750, 0), (495387, 'Let me alone: I have yet my legs and one arm. Tell the surgeon to make haste and his instruments. I know I must lose my right arm, so the sooner it''s off the better.', 20802, 0), (495388, 'By being friends with all, we are not alone.', 73760, 0), (495389, 'If there''s anything worse than a woman living alone, it''s a woman saying she likes it.', 76075, 0), (495390, 'Can anyone understand how it is to have lived in the White House and then, suddenly, to be living alone as the President''s widow?', 27555, 0), (495391, 'It is said that man doesn''t live by bread alone. Sometimes this is unfortunate, because people who cannot live by bread alone too often kill other people in consequence of the fights they get into.', 67111, 0), (495392, 'Why is it you feel like a dope if you laugh alone, but that''s usually how you end up crying?', 30, 0), (495393, 'Unhappy, let alone angry, religious people provide more persuasive arguments for atheism and secularism than do all the arguments of atheists.', 4608, 0), (495394, 'The conductor must breathe life into the score. It is you and you alone who must expose it to the understanding, reveal the hidden jewel to the sun at the most flattering angles.', 71801, 0), (495395, 'You aren''t going to leave me alone are you?', 76076, 0), (495396, 'If you go long enough without a bath, even the fleas will leave you alone.', 9247, 0), (495397, 'It''s very hard to write a song alone. It''s only by jamming that you can get a song together.', 74800, 0), (495398, 'Costumes and scenery alone will not attract audiences.', 55096, 0), (495399, 'Acquire the habit of speaking to God as if you were alone with Him, familiarly and with confidence and love, as to the dearest and most loving of friends.', 67483, 0), (495400, 'Early on, if I was alone two three nights in a row, I''d start writing poems about suicide.', 26129, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (495401, 'Man''s ultimate concern must be expressed symbolically, because symbolic language alone is able to express the ultimate.', 2750, 0), (495402, 'We learn about life not from plusses alone, but from minuses as well.', 1390, 0), (495403, 'A great source of calamity lies in regret and anticipation; therefore a person is wise who thinks of the present alone, regardless of the past or future.', 2204, 0), (495404, 'This avidity alone, of acquiring goods and possessions for ourselves and our nearest friends, is insatiable, perpetual, universal, and directly destructive of society.', 2498, 0), (495405, 'To the press alone, chequered as it is with abuses, the world is indebted for all the triumphs which have been gained by reason and humanity over error and oppression.', 2514, 0), (495406, 'Let me alone, and go in search of someone else.', 1925, 0), (495407, 'Say not that honor is the child of boldness, nor believe thou that the hazard of life alone can pay the price of it: it is not to the action that it is due, but to the manner of performing it.', 43279, 0), (495408, 'Life is so impermanent that it''s not about somebody else or things around me, it''s about knowing you are completely alone in this world and being content inside.', 29301, 0), (495409, 'Here in Cameroon, football is our leading political party. It''s football alone that that unites us, it''s football alone that brings us good things - football is the window into our country - so we don''t mess around with it.', 76077, 0), (495410, 'The radiation left over from the Big Bang is the same as that in your microwave oven but very much less powerful. It would heat your pizza only to minus 271.3*C - not much good for defrosting the pizza, let alone cooking it.', 1222, 0), (495411, 'Good acting is all in the writing. If it isn''t on the page, then it really won''t make any difference. You cannot act on force of personality alone.', 64769, 0), (495412, 'When the last red man shall have perished from the earth and his memory among the white men shall have become a myth, these shores will swarm with the invisible dead of my tribe. The white man will never be alone. Let him be just and deal kindly with my people, for the dead are not powerless.', 15779, 0), (495413, 'No one is good but God alone. What is good is therefore divine, what is divine is therefore good.', 69072, 0), (495414, 'Night-time is when I brainstorm; last thing, when the family''s asleep and I''m alone, I think about the next day''s writing and plan a strategy for my assault on the blank page.', 9896, 0), (495415, 'We are nothing if we walk alone we are everything when we walk together in step with other dignified feet. ', 31210, 0), (495416, 'The strange anthropological lesson of social media is that human beings, if given a choice, often prefer to socialize alone.', 9818, 0), (495417, 'Personally, I do not know whether humankind is alone in this vast universe. But I do know that we should cherish our existence on this precious speck of matter... the greatest gift that could be bestowed upon us. For all practical purposes, there is only one planet Earth.', 21719, 0), (495418, 'No pill can help me deal with the problem of not wanting to take pills; likewise, no amount of psychotherapy alone can prevent my manias and depressions. I need both.', 1631, 0), (495419, 'The surest way to be alone is to get married.', 1739, 0), (495420, 'It''s almost impossible to get a movie all together when there are two main cast members, let alone an ensemble cast with everyone''s schedules. It''s crazy if it works out.', 68181, 0), (495421, 'If a bacterium is trying to infect you, it won''t secrete alone, because your immune system will block it. Bacteria will hide until they can all act together and make an impact.', 68701, 0), (495422, 'Anything that makes you feel the most alone also has the greatest power to connect you.', 54900, 0), (495423, 'I know that when I''m standing alone below a thousand-foot wall, looking up and considering a climb, my sponsors are the furthest thing from my mind. If I''m going to take risks, they are going to be for myself - not for any company.', 69700, 0), (495424, 'I have been given a list of 35 white farmers in Mashonaland West alone. We say no to whites owning our land, and they should go... They can own companies and apartments... but not the soil. It is ours, and that message should ring loud and clear in Britain and the United States.', 32803, 0), (495425, 'You alone are enough.', 588, 0), (495426, 'We need someone with superb judgement in their own right because, yes, a president can hire the best advisors on Earth, but I guarantee you this: Five advisors will give five different opinions. And it is the president - and the president alone - who always makes the final call.', 1997, 0), (495427, 'Adolescents show off. That''s another way of wanting to connect with people. It''s not an aspect of human behavior that we generally consider to be very admirable, but it is, in some way, a means of connecting with someone else and not being alone.', 69452, 0), (495428, 'I don''t even know how to use a parking meter, let alone a phone box.', 68145, 0), (495429, 'When they are alone they want to be with others, and when they are with others they want to be alone. After all, human beings are like that.', 1267, 0), (495430, 'I adore art... when I am alone with my notes, my heart pounds and the tears stream from my eyes, and my emotion and my joys are too much to bear.', 65523, 0), (495431, 'I''m the most gregarious of men and love good company, but never less alone when alone.', 18244, 0), (495432, 'You would hardly believe how difficult it is to place a figure alone on a canvas, and to concentrate all the interest on this single and universal figure and still keep it living and real.', 19835, 0), (495433, 'God created man and, finding him not sufficiently alone, gave him a companion to make him feel his solitude more keenly.', 3087, 0), (495434, 'I grew up in a very large family in a very small house. I never slept alone until after I was married.', 60319, 0), (495435, 'If words are not things, or maps are not the actual territory, then, obviously, the only possible link between the objective world and the linguistic world is found in structure, and structure alone.', 2507, 0), (495436, 'As a farm girl, even when I was quite young, I had my ''farm chores'' - but I had time also to be alone, to explore the fields, woods and creek side. And to read.', 852, 0), (495437, 'Telling stories with visuals is an ancient art. We''ve been drawing pictures on cave walls for centuries. It''s like what they say about the perfect picture book. The art and the text stand alone, but together, they create something even better. Kids who need to can grab onto those graphic elements and find their way into the story.', 15616, 0), (495438, '''Option B'' draws not just on my story but on the research and stories of many people overcoming all kinds of adversity. No one should have to go through challenges and trauma alone.', 1770, 0), (495439, 'There''s a feeling sometimes in motherhood that you''re alone in what you''re going through, and none of us are alone. We''re all going through the same thing.', 13031, 0), (495440, 'During the first couple of years at school... I used to take my lunch and go down by the old fair grounds & sit alone by the side of the road & eat it... Those lovely, lonely lunches stick deep in my memory as unhappy times.', 66945, 0), (495441, 'There''s a lot of people out there who go through hard times, and they feel alone. They feel like nobody is there. But I''m in the same boat.', 73348, 0), (495442, 'When you are a successful business person, you are only as good as your team. No one can do every deal alone.', 67024, 0), (495443, 'No individual is alone responsible for a single stepping stone along the path of progress, and where the path is smooth progress is most rapid.', 67493, 0), (495444, 'Getting stress out of your life takes more than prayer alone. You must take action to make changes and stop doing whatever is causing the stress. You can learn to calm down in the way you handle things.', 1206, 0), (495445, 'As human beings, we need to know that we are not alone, that we are not crazy or completely out of our minds, that there are other people out there who feel as we do, live as we do, love as we do, who are like us.', 1502, 0), (495446, 'You''re only lonely if you''re not there for you.', 68937, 0), (495447, 'I am alone I am always alone no matter what. ', 1, 0), (495448, 'Genius begins great works labor alone finishes them. ', 8895, 0), (495449, 'You know, one of my fears about living alone so long is that you get used to doing everything your own way.', 9764, 0), (495450, 'I have dogs, and it''s no secret that I find reptiles interesting, but the thing about reptiles is that they really just wanna be left alone, and I understand them. It''s, ''Don''t pick me up, stop holding me, don''t look at me, just leave me alone.'' I have to admit, sometimes I feel like that.', 67437, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (495451, 'It is only the forcible propagation of conventional Christianity that makes the agnostic so bitter toward the church. He knows that all the doctrines cannot possibly be true, but he would view them with toleration if he were asked merely to let them alone for the benefit of the masses whom they can help and succour.', 1060, 0), (495452, 'Man alone is born crying, lives complaining, and dies disappointed.', 2087, 0), (495453, 'A young girl reached out to me to be her mentor one day, which I didn''t really know anything about. What I did remember was what it was to be alone as an African-American dancer in the ballet world and wanting to connect with someone who looks like me.', 50400, 0), (495454, 'The ability to reflect is associated with critical thinking and reasoning ability. And the capacity to be alone is one of the highest levels of development. It''s important to know how to self-soothe and be confident of other people''s love even when they''re not there in front of you.', 29006, 0), (495455, 'I have three phobias which, could I mute them, would make my life as slick as a sonnet, but as dull as ditch water: I hate to go to bed, I hate to get up, and I hate to be alone.', 755, 0), (495456, 'I must try and break through the cliches about Latin America. Superpowers and other outsiders have fought over us for centuries in ways that have nothing to do with our problems. In reality we are all alone.', 183, 0), (495457, 'I have an internal protectiveness where it''s like, if it comes to just me, as frightened as I am of losing someone I love or things going sour or simply being alone, there is a dark place in my brain where I''m like, It could happen and I''m okay, I''m prepared.', 72470, 0), (495458, 'Grave security concerns can arise as a result of demographic trends, chronic poverty, economic inequality, environmental degradation, pandemic diseases, organized crime, repressive governance and other developments no state can control alone. Arms can''t address such concerns.', 21719, 0), (495459, 'I know to win a championship, you''re not going to do it alone. You''re going to have to have a great supporting cast.', 76078, 0), (495460, 'A man is rich in proportion to the number of things he can afford to let alone.', 1049, 0), (495461, 'The right to be let alone is indeed the beginning of all freedoms.', 3784, 0), (495462, 'It is the fight alone that pleases us, not the victory.', 144, 0), (495463, 'I have never been able to grasp the meaning of time. I don''t believe it exists. I''ve felt this again and again, when alone and out in nature. On such occasions, time does not exist. Nor does the future exist.', 35520, 0), (495464, 'The only time I commit to conspiracy theories is when something way retarded happens. Like Lee Harvey Oswald acting alone.', 43216, 0), (495465, 'I can''t really define it in sexual terms alone although our sexuality is so energizing why not enjoy it too?', 897, 0), (495466, 'Using simple equipment and daylight alone is for me a pleasure and a replenishment.', 58258, 0), (495467, 'Compassion alone stands apart from the continuous traffic between good and evil proceeding within us.', 2567, 0), (495468, 'Democracy is liberty - a liberty which does not infringe on the liberty nor encroach on the rights of others; a liberty which maintains strict discipline, and makes law its guarantee and the basis of its exercise. This alone is true liberty; this alone can produce true democracy.', 67633, 0), (495469, 'I have always worked better alone and from my own impressions.', 19729, 0), (495470, 'I would be married, but I''d have no wife, I would be married to a single life.', 78, 0), (495471, 'An artist is always alone - if he is an artist. No, what the artist needs is loneliness.', 497, 0), (495472, 'It seems that when you have cancer you are a brave battler against the disease, but when you have Alzheimer''s you are an old fart. That''s how people see you. It makes you feel quite alone.', 195, 0), (495473, 'Experiencing those moments of being alone... is a very, very weird flooring and exposing position to be in when you''re just not used to it... But I''ve never been lonely. And with my kids Mia and Joe that remains the case.', 22748, 0), (495474, 'One night some short weeks ago, for the first time in her not always happy life, Marilyn Monroe''s soul sat down alone to a quiet supper from which it did not rise.', 7785, 0), (495475, 'Doubt, of whatever kind, can be ended by action alone.', 3061, 0), (495476, 'Happy the man, and happy he alone, he who can call today his own; he who, secure within, can say, tomorrow do thy worst, for I have lived today.', 8695, 0), (495477, 'When thinking about companions gone, we feel ourselves doubly alone.', 972, 0), (495478, 'I like being alone and I think this movie, as much as it is an investigation of connection and people bonding, I also think it''s just as much about loneliness.', 67917, 0), (495479, 'I tend to stay up late, not because I''m partying but because it''s the only time of the day when I''m alone and don''t have to be performing.', 14367, 0), (495480, 'No one is alone, and each change here brings about another change there.', 8633, 0), (495481, 'I wasn''t perfect and didn''t have it together. I felt alone. So through acting, I decided to be a shape shifter and with every role become the character instead of being myself. It meant about 10 years of no one knowing I was the same person in every movie.', 46525, 0), (495482, 'Twenty years ago, I wrote a book called ''It Takes a Village.'' And a lot of people looked at the title and asked, ''What the heck do you mean by that?'' This is what I mean. None of us can raise a family, build a business, heal a community or lift a country totally alone.', 66567, 0), (495483, 'Photography can never grow up if it imitates some other medium. It has to walk alone it has to be itself. ', 50257, 0), (495484, 'To awaken quite alone in a strange town is one of the pleasantest sensations in the world.', 21457, 0), (495485, 'Remember, the burden of sorrow is doubled when it is borne alone.', 73028, 0), (495486, 'Very few people are original. There''s very little original anything out there. Because to be original means you have to stand alone.', 65236, 0), (495487, 'Woman is fine for her own satisfaction alone. No man will admire her the more, no woman will like her the better for it. Neatness and fashion are enough for the former, and a something of shabbiness or impropriety will be most endearing to the latter.', 24, 0), (495488, 'Others indeed may talk, and write, and fight about liberty, and make an outward pretence to it; but the free-thinker alone is truly free.', 43455, 0), (495489, 'It''s time to end the cruel slaughter of whales and leave these magnificent creatures alone.', 67, 0), (495490, 'Hip-hop definitely taught me a lot. Having to create your own identity and become known and respected in a male-dominated field - it requires some guts. There are times you have to be strong, and times when you have to stand alone for what you believe in.', 10195, 0), (495491, 'He was thinking alone, and seriously racking his brain to find a direction for this single force four times multiplied, with which he did not doubt, as with the lever for which Archimedes sought, they should succeed in moving the world, when some one tapped gently at his door.', 319, 0), (495492, 'Still, intuitive assumptions about behavior is only the starting point of systematic analysis, for alone they do not yield many interesting implications.', 76079, 0), (495493, 'By far the greatest part of those goods which are the objects of desire, are procured by labour; and they may be multiplied, not in one country alone, but in many, almost without any assignable limit, if we are disposed to bestow the labour necessary to obtain them.', 73899, 0), (495494, 'And what''s more I''ve got no need for anyone to tell me how to do it. I am not interested. You act how you want to and leave me alone to do my own thing.', 68190, 0), (495495, 'And I find - I''m 63, and my capacity to be by myself and just spend time by myself hasn''t diminished any. That''s the necessary part of being a writer, you better like being alone.', 850, 0), (495496, 'Never to lie is to have no lock on your door, you are never wholly alone.', 6481, 0), (495497, 'Love turns, with a little indulgence, to indifference or disgust; hatred alone is immortal.', 8948, 0), (495498, 'I try to push ideas away, and the ones that will not leave me alone are the ones that ultimately end up happening.', 32870, 0), (495499, 'When I joined Ford, in the late 1970s, I felt strongly we could not forever be a huge user of natural resources without there being consequences. But I was alone in my thinking in those days.', 66700, 0), (495500, 'You can''t call me a Twitter phenomenon or a YouTube one. These things are useful, but so''s hard gigging. One year I did 311 shows. I did six in one night alone.', 1451, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (495501, 'We''re born alone. We do need each other. It''s lonely to really effectively live your life, and anyone you can get help from or give help to; that''s part of your obligation.', 31358, 0), (495502, 'I''ve always loved scuba diving and the cell-tickling feel of being underwater, though it poses unique frustrations. Alone, but with others, you may share the same sights and feelings, but you can''t communicate well.', 8213, 0), (495503, 'The first thought that I had about really trying to get sober was, ''Man, I could do a lot of good in the world. I can lead by example and just be this heroic recovery guy.'' And that''s just a bad reason to get sober. You can''t get sober for anybody''s benefit, let alone the world at large. You really got to do it for yourself.', 72760, 0), (495504, 'David - the man after God''s own heart - was a man of war and a mighty man of valour. When all Israel were on the run, David faced Goliath - alone... with God - and he but a stripling, and well scolded, too, by his brother for having come to see the battle.', 74658, 0), (495505, 'The thing about markets, and I think the thing people don''t understand about that, is markets are not kind, but they''re very efficient. So when the marketplace determines an inefficiency in the system, it corrects that, and a market system that''s left alone will reward good behavior and punish bad behavior.', 76015, 0), (495506, 'I''m very open and honest, and I feel like it''s important for women to hear that we''re not perfect; none of us are perfect. And sometimes we aspire to have these ideas in our heads of what perfection is, and I probably would''ve been better off if I''d left myself alone.', 70739, 0), (495507, 'When I''m writing, I separate from everyone. Even my band. I push myself, and I''m alone with my thoughts. Separating from friends and comforts and family lets you think a lot deeper about subject matter. Working alone drives me a little crazy, but it makes the writing as honest as possible.', 76080, 0), (495508, 'All the goodness I have within me is totally from the Lord alone. When I sin, it is from me and is done on my own, but when I act righteously, it is wholly and completely of God.', 36532, 0), (495509, 'I used to spend a lot of time alone as a kid, creating characters and doing voices in my room, and I thought to myself, I''m either going to go absolutely nuts, or I''m going to find something to put that energy into.', 71113, 0), (495510, 'No books ever go into my laboratory. The thing I am to do and the way are revealed to me the moment I am inspired to create something new. Without God to draw aside the curtain, I would be helpless. Only alone can I draw close enough to God to discover His secrets.', 14728, 0), (495511, 'My reputation as a ladies'' man was a joke. It caused me to laugh bitterly through the 10,000 nights I spent alone.', 571, 0), (495512, 'I have a characteristic since my childhood. I don''t like living together with my mother, sister, or friends at my home. I have always preferred to be alone and independent and lived according to that.', 10472, 0), (495513, 'I think some people are good at being alone, and some people aren''t, and as a child, I really liked it.', 28327, 0), (495514, 'In 2014, having children is complicated and daunting and fraught - as much as it''s always been, but now we''re talking about it. And the more we talk about it, the more of us will realize that we''re not going through it alone. Far from it.', 67865, 0), (495515, 'I have a strong belief that there is a god or a higher power. I think that if you have a strong belief in that, then you won''t feel alone in life and you will feel you can get through anything.', 68855, 0), (495516, 'This is how many people become artists, musicians, writers, computer programmers, record-holding athletes, scientists... by spending time alone practicing what they love.', 910, 0), (495517, 'I believe if the white and colored people could get together and be let alone, they would understand each other and consequently love each other.', 52279, 0), (495518, 'People eat duck and you think, well, we''ve got loads of chickens, leave the ducks alone!', 1566, 0), (495519, 'Solitude is very different from a ''time-out'' from our busy lives. Solitude is the very ground from which community grows. Whenever we pray alone, study, read, write, or simply spend quiet time away from the places where we interact with each other directly, we are potentially opened for a deeper intimacy with each other.', 19097, 0), (495520, 'Writing music and lyrics, you tend to become a control freak - sitting alone in your room with a bare light bulb over your head, writing communist manifestos.', 42196, 0), (495521, 'If I''m alone, I tend to cook for myself. I do a pretty good job of preparing healthful foods. My go-to is everything in a bowl like quinoa, avocado. Later in the day, scrambled eggs. I''m not a gourmet chef. I cook in bulk very well.', 71045, 0), (495522, 'Years of standing in the limelight portraying other people for large amounts of money does not usually lead to a high degree of self-examination, let alone self-criticism.', 14083, 0), (495523, 'We are for the most part more lonely when we go abroad among men than when we stay in our chambers. A man thinking or working is always alone, let him be where he will.', 1049, 0), (495524, 'All of our unhappiness comes from our inability to be alone.', 5879, 0), (495525, 'In Genesis, it says that it is not good for a man to be alone; but sometimes it is a great relief.', 26603, 0), (495526, 'Solitude is the profoundest fact of the human condition. Man is the only being who knows he is alone.', 8633, 0), (495527, 'The person who tries to live alone will not succeed as a human being. His heart withers if it does not answer another heart. His mind shrinks away if he hears only the echoes of his own thoughts and finds no other inspiration.', 442, 0), (495528, 'Every animal leaves traces of what it was man alone leaves traces of what he created. ', 2921, 0), (495529, 'It is not necessary that you leave the house. Remain at your table and listen. Do not even listen, only wait. Do not even wait, be wholly still and alone. The world will present itself to you for its unmasking, it can do no other, in ecstasy it will writhe at your feet.', 629, 0), (495530, 'Fashion is like the ashes left behind by the uniquely shaped flames of the fire, the trace alone revealing that a fire actually took place.', 41038, 0), (495531, 'If you''re a painter, you''re not alone. There''s no way to be alone.', 70869, 0), (495532, 'The words of the Bible, and the Bible alone, should be heard from the pulpit.', 4150, 0), (495533, 'I''m never less at leisure than when at leisure, or less alone than when alone.', 76081, 0), (495534, 'Too small is our world to allow discrimination, bigotry and intolerance to thrive in any corner of it, let alone in the United States of America.', 67500, 0), (495535, 'When you work alone, you need to socialize at some level.', 3207, 0), (495536, 'I''d like to state that Spike Lee is not saying that African American culture is just for black people alone to enjoy and cherish. Culture is for everybody.', 68155, 0), (495537, 'For so long as the Jew has even one ally, he will be convinced - in his smallness of mind - that his salvation came from that ally. It is only when he is alone - against all of his own efforts and frantic attempts - that he will, through no choice, be compelled to turn to G-d.', 67417, 0), (495538, 'Social democracy seeks and finds the ways, and particular slogans, of the workers'' struggle only in the course of the development of this struggle, and gains directions for the way forward through this struggle alone.', 8683, 0), (495539, 'I just don''t want to die alone, that''s all. That''s not too much to ask for, is it It would be nice to have someone care about me, for who I am, not about my wallet.', 2259, 0), (495540, 'Like they say, you can learn more from a guide in one day than you can in three months fishing alone.', 67470, 0), (495541, 'Human beings do not live in the objective world alone, nor alone in the world of social activity as ordinarily understood, but are very much at the mercy of the particular language which has become the medium of expression for their society.', 66996, 0), (495542, 'For people who are really talented, what you don''t say becomes extremely important. You have to judge what to say and what to leave alone so you can let the talent develop.', 30191, 0), (495543, 'If I have freedom in my love, And in my soul am free, - Angels alone that soar above, Enjoy such liberty.', 8724, 0), (495544, 'The revolution in Russia was victorious with the help of the poor peasants. This should always be borne in mind here in Western Europe and all the world over. But the workers in Western Europe stand alone: this should never be forgotten in Russia.', 76082, 0), (495545, 'The secret to being a writer is that you have to write. It''s not enough to think about writing or to study literature or plan a future life as an author. You really have to lock yourself away, alone, and get to work.', 888, 0), (495546, 'The Holy Spirit alone can do this, the Holy Spirit alone can establish this link with one''s neighbor.', 4387, 0), (495547, 'I''m a workaholic. Before long I''m traveling on my nervous energy alone. This is incredibly exhausting.', 69104, 0), (495548, 'But more important than personal awards is winning the World Series. That''s the max that anyone could ask for. Let alone to have the ball in your in your glove for the final out of the World Series. That was the ultimate.', 67200, 0), (495549, 'Is it not careless to become too local when there are four hundred billion stars in our galaxy alone.', 7259, 0), (495550, 'The law was made for one thing alone, for the exploitation of those who don''t understand it, or are prevented by naked misery from obeying it.', 1140, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (495551, 'I believe that no man who holds a leader''s position should ever accept favors from either side. He is then committed to show favors. A leader must stand alone.', 65862, 0), (495552, 'In the first 50 years of the filibuster, it was used only 35 times. But the last Congress alone had 112 cloture motions filed, plus threats of more. This is the tyranny of the minority.', 76083, 0), (495553, 'I think it''s interesting that ''cologne'' rhymes with ''alone.''', 2315, 0), (495554, 'When you stand alone and sell yourself, you can''t please everyone. But when you''re different, you can last.', 53024, 0), (495555, 'Just remember, you are not alone, in fact you are in a very common place with millions of others. We need to help each other and keep striving to reach our goals.', 76084, 0), (495556, 'I like to race, not to do laps alone.', 76085, 0), (495557, 'These are fountains of salvation that they who thirst may be satisfied with the living words they contain. In these alone is proclaimed the doctrine of godliness. Let no man add to these, neither let him take out from these.', 72754, 0), (495558, 'One person alone can''t do anything as important as bringing genuine democracy to a country.', 5358, 0), (495559, 'Buddhism notes that it is always a mistake to think your soul can go it alone.', 1173, 0), (495560, 'I''ve been left alone, even by the paparazzi, because what sells is sex and scandal. Absent that, they really don''t have much interest in you. I''m still married, still working, still happy.', 51243, 0), (495561, 'I''m so secluded. Very alone.', 18052, 0), (495562, 'When I decided to be a singer, my mother warned me I''d be alone a lot. Basically we all are.', 15469, 0), (495563, 'The question of whether or to what extent human activities are causing global warming is not a matter of ideology, let alone of belief. The issue is simply one of risk management.', 72454, 0), (495564, 'If you are in a movie theater, you can look two people down and they are laughing while you are laughing or you can look three people down and they love that song that you love. It is living proof that you are not alone.', 6, 0), (495565, 'When you see a struggle that you may be having personally put on a big screen and in a roomful of people, then it makes you feel less crazy or alone, because you''re seeing that other people are dealing with it too. You get to see in this imaginary scenario how people might try and answer some questions or deal with some problems.', 76086, 0), (495566, 'In America, the dreamers, the disabled and the disadvantaged are not left to defend themselves, alone in their struggles.', 76087, 0), (495567, 'You gotta bear in mind, the youth - and this is just in Britain alone - have nowhere to go in the evenings. They''ve closed all the social centers. There''s not even a patch of grass to kick a ball on.', 14227, 0), (495568, 'We are increasingly open to understanding how we are all connected and that if we sink the ship that we are all on, we all drown. However, we have simultaneously become so focused on our own life experiences that we think we are alone.', 11977, 0), (495569, 'My version of Superman is essentially of a guy who has spent his whole life alone.', 68865, 0), (495570, 'Understand that everybody has their own struggles, regardless of whether you can see it or not. Just surround yourself with the people who love you, and know you''re not really alone.', 76088, 0), (495571, 'No dream is ever chased alone.', 69228, 0), (495572, 'Blackness is a state of mind, and I identify with the black community. Mainly, because I realized, early on, when I walk into a room, people see a black woman, they don''t see a white woman. So out of that reason alone, I identify more with the black community.', 69081, 0), (495573, 'I like the idea of being a sculptor. Just me alone, making something - that solitary existence.', 7878, 0), (495574, '''The Creative Habit'' is basically about how you work alone, how you survive as a solitary artist. ''The Collaborative Habit'' is obviously about surviving with other people.', 7842, 0), (495575, 'In my better sense of mind, I know that I''m far from alone and far from the worst, and the earth keeps spinning. Everything keeps moving, with or without me.', 68483, 0), (495576, 'When I first started writing, it was me alone with a computer in my apartment. I hated the time away from other people, and my writing sucked. Now I have a laptop; I can do the most tedious part of my job in a public place.', 30, 0), (495577, 'I''m an introvert. I get my energy by spending time alone. I need that hour or two to myself every day.', 76089, 0), (495578, 'The word of the oldest of the old of our peoples didn''t stop. It spoke the truth, saying that our feet couldn''t walk alone, that our history of pain and shame was repeated and multiplied in the flesh and blood of the brothers and sisters of other lands and skies.', 31210, 0), (495579, 'Sparky Anderson taught me this a long time ago: ''There''s three ways you can treat a person. You can pat ''em on the butt, you can kick ''em in the butt, or you can leave ''em alone.''', 63429, 0), (495580, 'We try to live by the secret of sevens. A friend, who has been married for over 40 years, told us about this magic. Make and keep a date every seven days, take a night away alone, for yourself, every seven weeks, and schedule an adult-only vacation every seven months.', 67751, 0), (495581, 'I remember when I was very young, I had a fever - a long rheumatic fever in bed for four months. And in the days, I stayed alone with the maid. I only had my father''s books with me. They were fantasy books about ghosts, and also books by Edgar Allen Poe that made a forever impression on me.', 68232, 0), (495582, 'I believe that if it were possible to scrap the whole of existing literature, all writers would find themselves inevitably producing something very close to SF ... No other form of fiction has the vocabulary of ideas and images to deal with the present, let alone the future.', 2312, 0), (495583, 'As powerful as is our soul''s call, so potent are the forces of Resistance arrayed against it. We''re not alone if we''ve been mowed down by Resistance; millions of good men and women have bitten the dust before us.', 2339, 0), (495584, 'A trustee is held to something stricter than the morals of the market place. Not honesty alone, but the punctilio of an honor the most sensitive, is then the standard of behavior.', 49682, 0), (495585, 'I spend most of my time in a room alone where eight hours go by, and I have no sense of time. I work seven days a week, and I live in this sort of vague subconscious fog a lot.', 74916, 0), (495586, 'If a gigantic asteroid were barreling toward impact with our planet, you can bet there would be at least a few members of Congress who would insist on leaving it alone, either because they would see it as a warning shot from the Almighty or because a mining company with a savvy team of lobbyists had laid claim to the big rock.', 67465, 0), (495587, 'I never feel more alone than when I''m traveling. Alone and, to some extent, helpless. The world expects a certain level of competence and can be merciless when this expectation is unmet.', 22390, 0), (495588, 'Time alone is irreplaceable. Waste it not.', 76090, 0), (495589, 'Eventually, when I started studying Egyptology, I realized that seeing with my naked eyes alone wasn''t enough. Because all of the sudden, in Egypt, my beach had grown from a tiny beach in Maine to one eight hundred miles long, next to the Nile.', 69935, 0), (495590, 'The darkest moments for me weren''t necessarily winding up in the hospital or anything like that. It was those quiet moments alone when I just hated the person I had become.', 38171, 0), (495591, 'I feel alone and safe in public.', 3212, 0), (495592, 'I like to write about the solitary things people do. Humans seem to function best when they''re alone.', 4685, 0), (495593, 'The irony is that the more specific you are in the portrayal of character, the more like other people you are. In the same way, the more you think about how alone you are in this life, you realise how much a brother and sister everyone else is.', 67061, 0), (495594, 'I actually like spending time alone - it doesn''t bother me at all.', 73447, 0), (495595, 'My drummer, bass player, and guitar player sing backgrounds. They play and sing. I can sing all the harmonies, but I can''t do it alone.', 67027, 0), (495596, 'What I want is a sort of new political realignment on libertarian/authoritarian lines, and I want a new consensus to emerge of disaffected liberals, classical liberals, dissident minorities like gays, small-state conservatives, libertarians, people who basically want to be left alone.', 8420, 0), (495597, 'Everyone thinks I live alone, but I don''t. My characters all live with me.', 535, 0), (495598, 'Just think: in all the clean, beautiful reaches of the solar system, our planet alone is a blot; our planet alone has death.', 1173, 0), (495599, 'Man cannot live by incompetence alone.', 28270, 0), (495600, 'Being a child at home alone in the summer is a high-risk occupation. If you call your mother at work thirteen times an hour, she can hurt you.', 152, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (495601, 'Judaism is much more communal, and partly as a consequence of my religious switch, I am increasingly more suspicous of my previous view that what people do in the privacy of their own home is their business alone.', 75918, 0), (495602, 'When you sit down and watch something alone, you''re going to watch it for what it is.', 76091, 0), (495603, 'Very much alone in my work, I am almost jealous of it.', 76092, 0), (495604, 'The best of artists has no conception that the marble alone does not contain within itself.', 12364, 0), (495605, 'Sensual love deceives one as to the nature of heavenly love; it could not do so alone, but since it unconsciously has the element of heavenly love within it, it can do so.', 629, 0), (495606, 'But we cannot rely on memorials and museums alone. We can tell ourselves we will never forget and we likely won''t. But we need to make sure that we teach history to those who never had the opportunity to remember in the first place.', 12782, 0), (495607, 'We''re not a fragile people. We''re not a frightful people. Our power doesn''t come from some self-declared savior promising that he alone can restore order as long as we do things his way. We don''t look to be ruled.', 1693, 0), (495608, 'Even though I love solar and love wind, like most people do, I like the renewable sources, they alone are not going to get America energy independent.', 52321, 0), (495609, 'The capacity for not feeling lonely can carry a very real price, that of feeling nothing at all.', 1002, 0), (495610, 'What is uttered from the heart alone, Will win the hearts of others to your own.', 282, 0), (495611, 'Time, which alone makes the reputation of men, ends by making their defects respectable.', 808, 0), (495612, 'People used what they called a telephone because they hated being close together and they were scared of being alone.', 30, 0), (495613, 'The most boring scenes are the scenes where a character is alone.', 30, 0), (495614, 'Writers may be disreputable, incorrigible, early to decay or late to bloom but they dare to go it alone.', 135, 0), (495615, 'The good thing about working alone is I get a lot done and I can experiment more. The bad thing is I miss out on the gregarious, social way that most musicians work.', 67002, 0), (495616, 'BLT Prime at Trump National Doral is essential after a long day on the golf course. The popover bread alone is enough to keep me coming back!', 26172, 0), (495617, 'We can never prove that we''re alone in the universe. But the Allen Telescope Array could prove that we''re not.', 13839, 0), (495618, 'Casseroles don''t have to be about canned ingredients and vegetables you normally wouldn''t even think of eating alone, much less stuck in between layers of sauce and breadcrumbs. They can vary from everyone''s favorite all-time casserole, macaroni and cheese, to the ultimate English casserole, Shepherd''s Pie.', 32425, 0), (495619, 'I think one can easily make a case for taking out Saddam Hussein. In fact, one could probably be made on humanitarian grounds alone. But just as there''s a downside risk to doing nothing about this man, there is a very serious downside risk to invading the country.', 2253, 0), (495620, 'As a child, I was this record collector/listener that would sit in a room and listen to the entire Beatles catalog alone, over and over and over again.', 49828, 0), (495621, 'What is the worst of woes that wait on age? What stamps the wrinkle deeper on the brow? To view each loved one blotted from life''s page, And be alone on earth, as I am now.', 62558, 0), (495622, 'Whoever thinks that he alone has speech, or possesses speech or mind above others, when unfolded such men are seen to be empty.', 139, 0), (495623, 'Time alone reveals the just man but you might discern a bad man in a single day. ', 139, 0), (495624, 'All our efforts to guard and guide our children may just get in the way of the one thing they need most from us: to be deeply loved yet left alone so they can try a new skill, new slang, new style, new flip-flops. So they can trip a few times, make mistakes, cross them out, try again, with no one keeping score.', 36805, 0), (495625, 'Absolutely lonely people have few personal interactions of any kind.', 29471, 0), (495626, 'On the Net, the bell curve reclaims its tails. The uncommon is as accessible as the common. The very fragmentation of the Internet allows us to find ourselves in other people - and to know that we are not alone.', 68175, 0), (495627, 'When ''Buffy the Vampire Slayer'' premiered on the WB Network in 1996, American culture was in trouble. Americans were bowling alone, pursuing individual interests to the detriment of the communal good. Business leaders were celebrating creativity and neglecting discipline. Nike''s ''Just do it'' ads were teaching young people to break the rules.', 68175, 0), (495628, 'One sign of a great actor is when he can be alone by himself on the screen, doing almost nothing, and producing one of a film''s defining moments.', 3723, 0), (495629, 'The claim that too many criminals are being jailed, that there is over-incarceration, ignores an unfortunate fact: For the vast majority of crimes, a perpetrator is never identified or arrested, let alone prosecuted, convicted and jailed.', 67008, 0), (495630, 'Love alone is capable of uniting living beings in such a way as to complete and fulfill them, for it alone takes them and joins them by what is deepest in themselves.', 531, 0), (495631, 'I don''t think nationalism is alone holding the field it''s in contention with a lot of different things. ', 2537, 0), (495632, 'I tried acupuncture, the patch, and hypnosis, but found that I needed to do it alone - when the time was right for me.', 69119, 0), (495633, 'I think sometimes if you are alone, you are freer because your time is your own.', 5358, 0), (495634, '''The Desolation of Smaug'' stands alone as an action/adventure epic movie. It''s visually stunning, and the 3D is incredible. Plus, it''s directed by Peter Jackson, and he''s extraordinary.', 69302, 0), (495635, 'U2 is an original species... there are colours and feelings and emotional terrain that we occupy that is ours and ours alone.', 1397, 0), (495636, 'We never need feel we are alone or unloved in the Lord''s service because we never are. The Savior has promised angels on our left and on our right to bear us up, and he always keeps his word.', 9158, 0), (495637, 'Most actions derive not from your own initiative but from your family circumstances, your education, your calling, and so on. You must therefore give up a little time to performing actions which derive from yourself alone. They need not be important; quite insignificant actions fulfill the same purpose.', 14254, 0), (495638, 'I want to be alone and work until the day my heads hits the drawing table and I''m dead. Kaput. I feel very much like I want to be with my brother and sister again. They''re nowhere. I know they''re nowhere and they don''t exist, but if nowhere means that''s where they are, that''s where I want to be.', 585, 0), (495639, 'As much as we Egyptians treasure our military, acting alone it cannot provide the legitimacy to lay the foundations for democracy.', 67468, 0), (495640, 'I have always been a bit of an introvert. In fact, my dad used to force me to meet people so that my interpersonal skills improve. As an individual, I was happiest when left alone.', 22495, 0), (495641, 'The best part about being with a group is that you don''t have to do everything alone. You''re with your friends.', 58477, 0), (495642, 'To be labelled a cheat - it''s not fair. If I''m a cheat, then prove I''m a cheat or just leave me alone and let me do what I do best.', 67746, 0), (495643, 'My sister Naomi and I always wanted to go to Tahiti. We planned a fantastic holiday to visit several islands, but at the last moment, Naomi cancelled. It was the first time I''d holidayed alone, and it was absolutely the best.', 72054, 0), (495644, 'Connected to the collective heart, you can be certain in every cell of your being that you are never alone, and you will experience the grace, guidance and ease that comes when you are one with all there is.', 5671, 0), (495645, 'All men''s misfortunes spring from their hatred of being alone.', 5879, 0), (495646, 'Were there no contrariety of interests, nothing would be more simple and easy than to form and preserve free institutions. The right of suffrage alone would be a sufficient guarantee. It is the conflict of opposing interests which renders it the most difficult work of man.', 63147, 0), (495647, 'True thoughts are those alone which do not understand themselves.', 18848, 0), (495648, 'Music was like my first real toy. I was an only child for a while, and I was alone a lot of the time - and I liked it. I still like being alone.', 3572, 0), (495649, 'One of the happier ironies of recent history is that even as Tibet is being wiped off the map in Tibet itself, here it is in California, in Switzerland, in Japan. All over the world, Tibetan Buddhism is now part of the neighborhood. In 1968, there were two Tibetan Buddhist centers in the West. By 2000, there were 40 in New York alone.', 711, 0), (495650, 'We were alone. Where, I could not say, hardly imagine. All was black, and such a dense black that, after some minutes, my eyes had not been able to discern even the faintest glimmer.', 3205, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (495651, 'One of the places where we lived when I was growing up had this big wood out the back. And starting when I was about 8, I used to enjoy just walking alone through the wood late. Eleven p.m. Midnight. Later.', 67054, 0), (495652, 'I am not the most courageous guy in the world outside of the court. Being alone in the dark is something I don''t like.', 27470, 0), (495653, 'Alone I''m nothing.', 22771, 0), (495654, 'Stories can encourage us and embolden us to face ourselves and to feel. Stories can make us feel less alone. If we''re reading a story that moves us, we can feel that emotion that I feel towards my father or mother or girlfriend. So they can give us late-night company.', 3159, 0), (495655, 'When I realized I was depressed, then I started reading up about it. When I read that one in four people are depressed, I felt that I''m not the only one. I also felt that how many people must be feeling suffocated to fight this battle all alone. I just wanted to reach out and tell them that even I''m like you, and it''s okay if you feel like that.', 69743, 0), (495656, 'I''m a big fan of Daniel Day-Lewis. He''s a marvelous actor. He stands alone, I think.', 12702, 0), (495657, 'Solitude is un-American.', 405, 0), (495658, 'I thought about how we need to make children feel that there are times in their lives when they need to be alone and quiet and to be able to accept their aloneness.', 218, 0), (495659, 'Man does not live by words alone, despite the fact that sometimes he has to eat them.', 69260, 0), (495660, 'Somehow, since I became a family, every minute in which I am alone and not listening to two kids screaming in stereo feels like a vacation.', 68456, 0), (495661, 'History, whether sacred or profane, hides her teaching from those who study her through coloured glasses. She only reveals truth to those who look through the cold clear medium of passionless inquiry, who seek the Truth without determining first the masquerade in which alone they will receive it.', 62897, 0), (495662, 'We cannot remember too often that when we observe nature, and especially the ordering of nature, it is always ourselves alone we are observing.', 68283, 0), (495663, 'Sometimes I think we''re alone. Sometimes I think we''re not. In either case, the thought is staggering.', 11496, 0), (495664, 'No one chooses to raise children alone.', 964, 0), (495665, 'The desire to get married, which - I regret to say, I believe is basic and primal in women - is followed almost immediately by an equally basic and primal urge - which is to be single again.', 301, 0), (495666, 'You need a whole community to raise a child. I have raised two children, alone.', 171, 0), (495667, 'All art stems from a place of alienation. Intimate and alone. Most people are oppressed by the opinion of others, but I was not that way. I was afraid of the repercussions of not doing what I was told to do, what I was called to do by a creator.', 58187, 0), (495668, 'I cannot live under pressures from patrons, let alone paint.', 12364, 0), (495669, 'I like my life alone. I mean, I love being with friends, and I love kissing and loving someone to pieces. But it''s hard to find someone who doesn''t ultimately start judging you and your choices.', 18382, 0), (495670, 'He that can live alone resembles the brute beast in nothing, the sage in much, and God in everything.', 1255, 0), (495671, 'If you''re going to put yourself above everybody else, you might end up alone.', 12986, 0), (495672, 'It is true that when you''re in the White House alone, it is a lonely place. Big and lonely.', 7879, 0), (495673, 'We gave up some of our country to the white men, thinking that then we could have peace. We were mistaken. The white man would not let us alone.', 4664, 0), (495674, 'If I''m alone too long I think too much, and I''m not interested in doing that. That won''t lead anywhere good, I''m sure. If I''m busy I tend to stay out of trouble. An idle mind is the devil''s playground.', 68955, 0), (495675, 'It is wonderful to contemplate how the planetary forces balance each other so perfectly that universal equilibrium is maintained despite the disturbances of the 1,500 millions which inhabit the Earth alone, not to speak of other spheres.', 22756, 0), (495676, 'I know what men want. Men want to be really, really close to someone who will leave them alone.', 28346, 0), (495677, 'It is not the soul alone that should be healthy; if the mind is healthy in a healthy body, all will be healthy and much better prepared to give God greater service.', 70538, 0), (495678, 'I hope this will help new moms not feel alone or desperate, and that there is no shame in their feelings. PPD is out of their control, but the treatment and healing process is not.', 65022, 0), (495679, 'Perhaps if we all subscribed to the African concept of Ubuntu - that we all become people through other people, and that we cannot be fully human alone, we could learn a lot. There''d be less hatred and more harmony.', 67571, 0), (495680, 'For the first time, I lived alone... in a luxury apartment on Sunset Strip. For a few days I loved the idea, but I got lonely and restless.', 57186, 0), (495681, 'The Fur Company may be called the exterminating medium of these wild and almost uninhabitable regions, which cupidity or the love of money alone would induce man to venture into. Where can I now go and find nature undisturbed?', 13434, 0), (495682, 'My learning process is by eye alone it''s not at all scientific. ', 57414, 0), (495683, 'The progress of evolution from President Washington to President Grant was alone evidence to upset Darwin.', 2796, 0), (495684, 'Remember we''re all in this alone.', 1059, 0), (495685, 'Unknown in Paris, I was lost in the great city, but the feeling of living there alone, taking care of myself without any aid, did not at all depress me. If sometimes I felt lonesome, my usual state of mind was one of calm and great moral satisfaction.', 1036, 0), (495686, 'This, then, is the test we must set for ourselves; not to march alone but to march in such a way that others will wish to join us.', 15498, 0), (495687, 'I''m very happy alone.', 3278, 0), (495688, 'Professional players work almost every day, for hours on end, and the emphasis is on the word ''work.'' It can be with a partner or it can be alone, but professional chess is always a pursuit of something new and surprising.', 72572, 0), (495689, 'To be adult is to be alone.', 3404, 0), (495690, 'To be absolutely alone for the first time in the cockpit of a plane hundreds of feet above the ground is an experience never to be forgotten.', 37323, 0), (495691, 'I''m ultimately a widow and a single mother, who''s not even getting to be a mother right now. I am so alone, it''s freaky.', 601, 0), (495692, 'To those seniors, and especially elderly veterans like myself, I want to tell you this: You are not alone, and you having nothing to be ashamed of. If elder abuse happened to me, it can happen to anyone. I want you to know that you deserve better.', 64620, 0), (495693, 'The biggest opportunity in 2013 is in Africa. It has seven out of the ten fastest-growing economies in the world. In Nigeria alone there are 100 million people with mobile phones. In total, 300 million Africans - five times the population of Britain - are in the middle class.', 72771, 0), (495694, 'People talk about the conscience, but it seems to me one must just bring it up to a certain point and leave it there. You can let your conscience alone if you''re nice to the second housemaid.', 561, 0), (495695, 'My dad grew up in a mud hut and studied by candlelight. He was 14 when he got a scholarship to Russia. He was super clever - the cleverest person. He landed in 5ft of snow, and was alone at 14, studying science and engineering. He didn''t have a bed, and he slept on a table.', 67100, 0), (495696, 'I''m happily single.', 41969, 0), (495697, 'You can work on the saxophone alone, but ultimately you must perform with others.', 70833, 0), (495698, 'I hate being alone, even for 10 minutes.', 52120, 0), (495699, 'The Fuhrer alone is the present and future German reality and its law. Learn to know ever more deeply: from now on every single thing demands decision, and every action responsibility.', 2500, 0), (495700, 'Now suddenly there was nothing but a world of cloud, and we three were there alone in the middle of a great white plain with snowy hills and mountains staring at us; and it was very still; but there were whispers.', 2576, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (495701, 'Politicians usually get the blame for dragging their feet on environmental issues. And fair enough. Most of them do just that. But the blame isn''t theirs alone. For politicians afraid of losing votes, a bristling media waiting to transform good green ideas into monsters is a colossal disincentive.', 70949, 0), (495702, 'There is no one looking out for us. We are all alone.', 73706, 0), (495703, 'There have been a few friends who have taught me some great lessons in life. I wouldn''t like to name them. They did things that I never expected out of them that left me heart-broken. It was during these rough patches in life that they left me alone. I know now that it was only my position that they were interested in.', 69674, 0), (495704, 'But there is a discomfort that surrounds grief. It makes even the most well-intentioned people unsure of what to say. And so many of the freshly bereaved end up feeling even more alone.', 7796, 0), (495705, 'The more decisions that you are forced to make alone, the more you are aware of your freedom to choose.', 744, 0), (495706, 'The employee is regarded by the employer merely in the light of his value as an operative. His productive capacity alone is taken into account.', 66810, 0), (495707, 'Thank you for leaving us alone but giving us enough attention to boost our egos.', 20225, 0), (495708, 'I was never less alone than when by myself.', 7427, 0), (495709, 'The Bible was a consolation to a fellow alone in the old cell. The lovely thin paper with a bit of matress stuffing in it, if you could get a match, was as good a smoke as I ever tasted.', 9701, 0), (495710, 'However, anyone to whom this happens should not leave his room upon awakening, should speak to no-one, but remain alone and sober until everything comes back to him, and he recalls the dream.', 2652, 0), (495711, 'I seek the Will of the Spirit of God through, or in connection with, the Word of God. The Spirit and the Word must be combined. If I look to the Spirit alone without the Word, I lay myself open to great delusions also.', 19001, 0), (495712, 'Your Majesty, I took the liberty because I was so desirous of visiting alone with you for a few minutes before the rest of the other peasants arrived.', 67745, 0), (495713, 'Once you grow past Mommy and Daddy coming running when you''re hurt, you''re really on your own. You''re alone, and there''s no one to help you.', 67420, 0), (495714, 'I am convinced that living in an enclave shapes the personality, and living alone shapes the personality too.', 70952, 0), (495715, 'Almost everyone who reaches a plateau where he or she is happy and comfortable says it''s because of finding balance between work, relaxation, exercise, socialising and family - plus some alone time to do something contemplative, creative, or educational.', 1881, 0), (495716, 'Your actions, and your action alone, determines your worth.', 399, 0), (495717, 'And we never got the mule, let alone the forty acres.', 72480, 0), (495718, 'Alone let him constantly meditate in solitude on that which is salutary for his soul, for he who meditates in solitude attains supreme bliss.', 4201, 0), (495719, 'The power of a book lies in its power to turn a solitary act into a shared vision. As long as we have books, we are not alone.', 11480, 0), (495720, 'Go on thinking that you don''t need to be read and you''ll find that it may become quite true: no one will feel the need tom read it because it is written for yourself alone and the public won''t feel any impulse to gate crash such a private party. ', 300, 0), (495721, 'The power that is supported by force alone will have cause often to tremble.', 68795, 0), (495722, 'Most photographers work best alone, myself included.', 58221, 0), (495723, 'Largely this is a class thing - writers tend to be cosseted little middle-class kiddies who think that the world owes them a royalty cheque. But just doing it - being in your room for years on end, locked in your head, alone with invented ghosts - it weakens and softens the body. And I know I can''t just live in my head.', 927, 0), (495724, 'In a household tragedy, you are very much aware of being alone. It is something that is possible to grasp, and that is why it hurts so much. Because you are alone. I know a little about this.', 8142, 0), (495725, 'Young people discovering their sexuality must know they walk with a strong tradition and that they are not alone. They have a right to information without being pressured.', 67666, 0), (495726, 'Men find it more difficult than women to be alone. They function better with someone in their lives. Being married, they are rooted, so they feel safe to go and do what they want to do.', 57451, 0), (495727, 'I felt alone out there, like I was on a desert island. I felt like Gilligan.', 2665, 0), (495728, 'This is nourishing, redemptive; we become less alone inside.', 209, 0), (495729, 'A man is never completely alone in this world. At the worst, he has the company of a boy, a youth, and by and by a grown man - the one he used to be.', 1078, 0), (495730, 'Even though I have often recorded alone, I still feel the best music is made by musicians playing off each other.', 22780, 0), (495731, 'Sometimes I feel very alone. I am a bit of a nomad. Many people in sort of emerging countries, emerging economies, find themselves displaced. So there is that sense, and so I''m part of a whole, I think, group of displaced people.', 21160, 0), (495732, 'A celibate, like the fly in the heart of an apple, dwells in a perpetual sweetness, but sits alone, and is confined and dies in singularity.', 3943, 0), (495733, 'The fathers, if they got me alone, would try to kiss and fondle me. I hated it.', 73080, 0), (495734, 'All my fans tell me what a glamorous life I have, but I tell them how hard I work and how many nights I spend alone with my dogs, eating chicken pot pie in my bedroom.', 68886, 0), (495735, 'I think one challenge is that having few women in your work environment makes you feel a little isolated and alone. I''m an extrovert; I like talking to people, and I make friends easily, but if your personality is somewhat different, I think you would struggle to connect with people.', 48341, 0), (495736, 'There is a destiny which makes us brothers none goes his way alone. All that we send into the lives of others comes back into our own. ', 545, 0), (495737, 'You can''t fake it when you''re alone with God, you know.', 68142, 0), (495738, 'The devil had as good have let Paul alone, for he no sooner comes into prison but he falls a preaching, at which the gates of Satan''s prison fly open, and poor sinners come forth.', 14542, 0), (495739, 'But Socialism, alone, can bring self-determination of their peoples.', 68731, 0), (495740, 'If you make friends with yourself you will never be alone.', 1572, 0), (495741, 'And then when all around grows dark, when we feel utterly alone, when all men right and left pass us by and know us not, a forgotten feeling rises in the breast.', 69005, 0), (495742, 'I want to be alone.', 1599, 0), (495743, 'The amount of coordination it takes to shoot a television show is mind-numbing. There are so many things that have to be exactly right to create the correct environment for a single shot, let alone a whole scene or the full episode.', 75924, 0), (495744, 'But I like to know that someone is stronger than I am. I want to be able to know that if I get tired, somebody is there to hold up the fort. I like knowing that I can''t pick a refrigerator alone. God did not make me strong enough to do that.', 72797, 0), (495745, 'It''s a terrible thing to be alone - yes it is - it is - but don''t lower your mask until you have another mask prepared beneath - as terrible as you like - but a mask.', 3172, 0), (495746, 'After all, it is style alone by which posterity will judge of a great work, for an author can have nothing truly his own but his style.', 9893, 0), (495747, 'I am alone, some people help me, but, basically, I can do what I want.', 75491, 0), (495748, 'Shockingly, a University of Pennsylvania study says the number of young people addicted to gambling - largely due to increased exposure to the Internet and Internet gambling - grew by an alarming 20 percent between 2004 and 2005 alone.', 67596, 0), (495749, 'To hike out alone in the desert; to sleep on the valley floor on a night with no moon, in the pitch black, just listening to the boom of silence: you can''t imagine what that''s like.', 44, 0), (495750, 'Painting is the only universal language. All nature is creation''s picture book. Painting alone can describe every thing which can be seen, and suggest every emotion which can be felt. Art reaches back into the babyhood of time, and is man''s only lasting monument.', 70856, 0);
