 dare read the Torah, let alone attempt a witty observation on the Torah.', 74526, 0), (495775, 'In the 20th century alone, there have been 1,600 books about the circus. My adding one more would be superfluous unless I do something totally new and different.', 12794, 0), (495776, 'The VCR is to the American film producer and the American public as the Boston Strangler is to the woman alone.', 76093, 0), (495777, 'If I have the choice of traveling to Russia, India or New Zealand alone for a week for preliminary discussions or to spend that week with my family, I routinely choose my family.', 76094, 0), (495778, 'Sometimes I get lonely, but it''s nice to be alone.', 76095, 0), (495779, 'Industry entirely left to itself, would soon fall to ruin, and a nation letting everything alone would commit suicide.', 75401, 0), (495780, 'I think my comparison with Shane would be a loner. I always got the impression that she wasn''t scared to be alone. She enjoys it. I can relate to that.', 76096, 0), (495781, 'The things that drive me are poverty, and pain, and knowing that I don''t want to end up being alone and I want to do something with my life and I want the name Dobson to remain in everyone''s heads. Basically, just to rock and be the best performer I can be, and be true, and be real, and give people the real Fefe, nothing fake, all real.', 76097, 0), (495782, 'You do stand alone sometimes. But my mother stood by me through all this.', 71488, 0), (495783, 'He never is alone that is accompanied with noble thoughts.', 63341, 0), (495784, 'But let her remember, that it is in Britain alone, that laws are equally favourable to liberty and humanity; that it is in Britain the sacred rights of nature have received their most awful ratification.', 76098, 0), (495785, 'Here in Denmark, you can easily just be left alone. This is my ''hood, and people leave me alone; it''s nice.', 76099, 0), (495786, 'I am alone here in New York, no longer a we.', 9951, 0), (495787, 'Lord of myself, accountable to none, but to my conscience, and my God alone.', 76100, 0), (495788, 'The idea of determinism combined with complete human responsibility struck me as very hard to reconcile with an idea of justice, let alone mercy.', 19122, 0), (495789, 'Disorder makes me feel at ease if I''m alone, embarrassed if I''m not.', 31035, 0), (495790, 'An Englishman, even if he is alone, forms an orderly queue of one.', 17191, 0), (495791, 'A man content to go to heaven alone will never go to heaven.', 3096, 0), (495792, 'My kitchen linoleum is so black and shiny that I waltz while I wait for the kettle to boil. This pleasure is for the old who live alone.', 12526, 0), (495793, 'Is it possible that I am not alone in believing that in the dispute between Galileo and the Church, the Church was right and the centre of man''s universe is the earth?', 28234, 0), (495794, 'Hiking is the best workout!... You can hike for three hours and not even realize you''re working out. And, hiking alone lets me have some time to myself.', 73273, 0), (495795, 'The dream, alone, is of interest. What is life, without a dream?', 2208, 0), (495796, 'To sit alone in the lamplight with a book spread out before you, and hold intimate converse with men of unseen generations - such is a pleasure beyond compare.', 76101, 0), (495797, 'It''s hard to get everybody to recycle paper and plastic, let alone.', 76102, 0), (495798, 'In the total expanse of human life there is not a single square inch of which the Christ, who alone is sovereign, does not declare, ''That is mine!''.', 11822, 0), (495799, 'Nothing is so envied as genius, nothing so hopeless of attainment by labor alone. Though labor always accompanies the greatest genius, without the intellectual gift labor alone will do little.', 71419, 0), (495800, 'What I am afraid of is the first thing I was ever aware of being afraid of and what I have told my daughter countless times she need not fear: being alone in the dark. It is a small prison of emotion from which there is no escape. It is also, in its own way, a shattering revelation.', 21007, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (495801, 'I could prove God statistically. Take the human body alone - the chances that all the functions of an individual would just happen is a statistical monstrosity.', 64027, 0), (495802, 'Higher education must lead the march back to the fundamentals of human relationships, to the old discovery that is ever new, that man does not live by bread alone.', 15867, 0), (495803, 'Sooner or later, we will have to recognise that the Earth has rights, too, to live without pollution. What mankind must know is that human beings cannot live without Mother Earth, but the planet can live without humans.', 67744, 0), (495804, 'We won''t have a society if we destroy the environment.', 992, 0), (495805, 'Sustainable development is the pathway to the future we want for all. It offers a framework to generate economic growth, achieve social justice, exercise environmental stewardship and strengthen governance.', 21719, 0), (495806, 'The Earth does not belong to us: we belong to the Earth.', 67063, 0), (495807, 'The future will either be green or not at all.', 21415, 0), (495808, 'Environmental pollution is an incurable disease. It can only be prevented.', 63450, 0), (495809, 'Try to leave the Earth a better place than when you arrived.', 1115, 0), (495810, 'The only way forward, if we are going to improve the quality of the environment, is to get everybody involved.', 69885, 0), (495811, 'Plans to protect air and water, wilderness and wildlife are in fact plans to protect man.', 69098, 0), (495812, 'We don''t have to sacrifice a strong economy for a healthy environment.', 76103, 0), (495813, 'When we try to pick out anything by itself, we find it hitched to everything else in the universe.', 1402, 0), (495814, 'Sadly, it''s much easier to create a desert than a forest.', 56748, 0), (495815, 'The environment is everything that isn''t me.', 104, 0), (495816, 'Raising awareness on the most pressing environmental issues of our time is more important than ever.', 68700, 0), (495817, 'Every drop in the ocean counts.', 1121, 0), (495818, 'We could have saved the Earth but we were too damned cheap.', 13666, 0), (495819, 'Economic growth and environmental protection are not at odds. They''re opposite sides of the same coin if you''re looking at longer-term prosperity.', 68961, 0), (495820, 'Develop resilience and be brave. There are days when it is very discouraging. You have to develop personal resilience to environmental things that come along. If you let every single environmental challenge knock you off your game, it''s going to be very, very hard.', 75282, 0), (495821, 'Destroying rainforest for economic gain is like burning a Renaissance painting to cook a meal.', 44747, 0), (495822, 'Birds are indicators of the environment. If they are in trouble, we know we''ll soon be in trouble.', 70825, 0), (495823, 'The Chinese have figured out that they have a giant environmental problem. Folks in Beijing, some days, literally can''t breathe. Over a million Chinese die prematurely every year because of air pollution.', 17532, 0), (495824, 'Environmental protection and economic development are not in conflict. Environmental protection is not a burden but a source for innovation. It can increase competition, create jobs, and lifts the economy.', 54708, 0), (495825, 'Population, when unchecked, goes on doubling itself every 25 years or increases in a geometrical ratio.', 71479, 0), (495826, 'We are using resources as if we had two planets, not one. There can be no ''plan B'' because there is no ''planet B.''', 21719, 0), (495827, 'The most meaningful engine of change, powerful enough to confront corporate power, may be not so much environmental quality, as the economic development and growth associated with the effort to improve it.', 63450, 0), (495828, 'Harmony with land is like harmony with a friend you cannot cherish his right hand and chop off his left. ', 1954, 0), (495829, 'Good environmental policy is good economic policy.', 40174, 0), (495830, 'We firmly believe the environmental issues cannot be addressed without extensive public participation, but people need to be informed before they can get involved.', 75003, 0), (495831, 'The Endangered Species Act is the strongest and most effective tool we have to repair the environmental harm that is causing a species to decline.', 74827, 0), (495832, 'My lens of choice was always the 35 mm. It was more environmental. You can''t come in closer with the 35 mm.', 58263, 0), (495833, 'Every time I have some moment on a seashore, or in the mountains, or sometimes in a quiet forest, I think this is why the environment has to be preserved.', 65802, 0), (495834, 'I think the environment should be put in the category of our national security. Defense of our resources is just as important as defense abroad. Otherwise what is there to defend?', 20594, 0), (495835, 'I''m anti-tax, but I''m pro-carbon tax.', 10864, 0), (495836, 'The environmental problems of developing countries are not the side effects of excessive industrialisation but reflect the inadequacy of development.', 2002, 0), (495837, 'Clinton understands that climate change is real, is caused by human activity and is one of the great environmental crises facing our planet. She knows that we must transform our energy system away from fossil fuels and move aggressively to energy efficiency and sustainable energy.', 40174, 0), (495838, 'You will die but the carbon will not; its career does not end with you. It will return to the soil, and there a plant may take it up again in time, sending it once more on a cycle of plant and animal life.', 2921, 0), (495839, 'No one is an environmentalist by birth. It is only your path, your life, your travels that awaken you.', 19728, 0), (495840, 'Our globe is under new dramatic environmental pressure: our globe is warming, our ice caps melting, our glaciers receding, our coral is dying, our soils are eroding, our water tables